45 enum TypeDiagSelector {
46  TDS_Function,
47  TDS_Pointer,
48  TDS_ObjCObjOrBlock
49 };
50 
51 /// isOmittedBlockReturnType - Return true if this declarator is missing a
52 /// return type because this is a omitted return type on a block literal.
53 static bool isOmittedBlockReturnType(const Declarator &D) {
54  if (D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteral ||
55  D.getDeclSpec().hasTypeSpecifier())
56  return false;
57 
58  if (D.getNumTypeObjects() == 0)
59  return true; // ^{ ... }
60 
61  if (D.getNumTypeObjects() == 1 &&
62  D.getTypeObject(0).Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Function)
63  return true; // ^(int X, float Y) { ... }
64 
65  return false;
66 }
67 
68 /// diagnoseBadTypeAttribute - Diagnoses a type attribute which
69 /// doesn't apply to the given type.
70 static void diagnoseBadTypeAttribute(Sema &S, const ParsedAttr &attr,
71  QualType type) {
72  TypeDiagSelector WhichType;
73  bool useExpansionLoc = true;
74  switch (attr.getKind()) {
75  case ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCGC:
76  WhichType = TDS_Pointer;
77  break;
78  case ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership:
79  WhichType = TDS_ObjCObjOrBlock;
80  break;
81  default:
82  // Assume everything else was a function attribute.
83  WhichType = TDS_Function;
84  useExpansionLoc = false;
85  break;
86  }
87 
88  SourceLocation loc = attr.getLoc();
89  StringRef name = attr.getAttrName()->getName();
90 
91  // The GC attributes are usually written with macros; special-case them.
92  IdentifierInfo *II = attr.isArgIdent(0) ? attr.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident
93  : nullptr;
94  if (useExpansionLoc && loc.isMacroID() && II) {
95  if (II->isStr("strong")) {
96  if (S.findMacroSpelling(loc, "__strong")) name = "__strong";
97  } else if (II->isStr("weak")) {
98  if (S.findMacroSpelling(loc, "__weak")) name = "__weak";
99  }
100  }
101 
102  S.Diag(loc, diag::warn_type_attribute_wrong_type) << name << WhichType
103  << type;
104 }
105 
106 // objc_gc applies to Objective-C pointers or, otherwise, to the
107 // smallest available pointer type (i.e. 'void*' in 'void**').
108 #define OBJC_POINTER_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST \
109  case ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCGC: \
110  case ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership
111 
112 // Calling convention attributes.
113 #define CALLING_CONV_ATTRS_CASELIST \
114  case ParsedAttr::AT_CDecl: \
115  case ParsedAttr::AT_FastCall: \
116  case ParsedAttr::AT_StdCall: \
117  case ParsedAttr::AT_ThisCall: \
118  case ParsedAttr::AT_RegCall: \
119  case ParsedAttr::AT_Pascal: \
120  case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftCall: \
121  case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftAsyncCall: \
122  case ParsedAttr::AT_VectorCall: \
123  case ParsedAttr::AT_AArch64VectorPcs: \
124  case ParsedAttr::AT_MSABI: \
125  case ParsedAttr::AT_SysVABI: \
126  case ParsedAttr::AT_Pcs: \
127  case ParsedAttr::AT_IntelOclBicc: \
128  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveMost: \
129  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveAll
130 
131 // Function type attributes.
132 #define FUNCTION_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST \
133  case ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained: \
134  case ParsedAttr::AT_NoReturn: \
135  case ParsedAttr::AT_Regparm: \
136  case ParsedAttr::AT_CmseNSCall: \
137  case ParsedAttr::AT_AnyX86NoCallerSavedRegisters: \
138  case ParsedAttr::AT_AnyX86NoCfCheck: \
139  CALLING_CONV_ATTRS_CASELIST
140 
141 // Microsoft-specific type qualifiers.
142 #define MS_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST \
143  case ParsedAttr::AT_Ptr32: \
144  case ParsedAttr::AT_Ptr64: \
145  case ParsedAttr::AT_SPtr: \
146  case ParsedAttr::AT_UPtr
147 
148 // Nullability qualifiers.
149 #define NULLABILITY_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST \
150  case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNonNull: \
151  case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullable: \
152  case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullableResult: \
153  case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullUnspecified

155 namespace {
156  /// An object which stores processing state for the entire
157  /// GetTypeForDeclarator process.
158  class TypeProcessingState {
159  Sema &sema;
160 
161  /// The declarator being processed.
162  Declarator &declarator;
163 
164  /// The index of the declarator chunk we're currently processing.
165  /// May be the total number of valid chunks, indicating the
166  /// DeclSpec.
167  unsigned chunkIndex;
168 
169  /// Whether there are non-trivial modifications to the decl spec.
170  bool trivial;
171 
172  /// Whether we saved the attributes in the decl spec.
173  bool hasSavedAttrs;
174 
175  /// The original set of attributes on the DeclSpec.
176  SmallVector<ParsedAttr *, 2> savedAttrs;
177 
178  /// A list of attributes to diagnose the uselessness of when the
179  /// processing is complete.
180  SmallVector<ParsedAttr *, 2> ignoredTypeAttrs;
181 
182  /// Attributes corresponding to AttributedTypeLocs that we have not yet
183  /// populated.
184  // FIXME: The two-phase mechanism by which we construct Types and fill
185  // their TypeLocs makes it hard to correctly assign these. We keep the
186  // attributes in creation order as an attempt to make them line up
187  // properly.
188  using TypeAttrPair = std::pair<const AttributedType*, const Attr*>;
189  SmallVector<TypeAttrPair, 8> AttrsForTypes;
190  bool AttrsForTypesSorted = true;
191 
192  /// MacroQualifiedTypes mapping to macro expansion locations that will be
193  /// stored in a MacroQualifiedTypeLoc.
194  llvm::DenseMap<const MacroQualifiedType *, SourceLocation> LocsForMacros;
195 
196  /// Flag to indicate we parsed a noderef attribute. This is used for
197  /// validating that noderef was used on a pointer or array.
198  bool parsedNoDeref;
199 
200  public:
201  TypeProcessingState(Sema &sema, Declarator &declarator)
202  : sema(sema), declarator(declarator),
203  chunkIndex(declarator.getNumTypeObjects()), trivial(true),
204  hasSavedAttrs(false), parsedNoDeref(false) {}
205 
206  Sema &getSema() const {
207  return sema;
208  }
209 
210  Declarator &getDeclarator() const {
211  return declarator;
212  }
213 
214  bool isProcessingDeclSpec() const {
215  return chunkIndex == declarator.getNumTypeObjects();
216  }
217 
218  bool isProcessingLambdaExpr() const {
219  return declarator.isFunctionDeclarator() &&
220  declarator.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr;
221  }
222 
223  unsigned getCurrentChunkIndex() const {
224  return chunkIndex;
225  }
226 
227  void setCurrentChunkIndex(unsigned idx) {
228  assert(idx <= declarator.getNumTypeObjects());
229  chunkIndex = idx;
230  }
231 
232  ParsedAttributesView &getCurrentAttributes() const {
233  if (isProcessingDeclSpec())
234  return getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes();
235  return declarator.getTypeObject(chunkIndex).getAttrs();
236  }
237 
238  /// Save the current set of attributes on the DeclSpec.
239  void saveDeclSpecAttrs() {
240  // Don't try to save them multiple times.
241  if (hasSavedAttrs) return;
242 
243  DeclSpec &spec = getMutableDeclSpec();
244  llvm::append_range(savedAttrs,
245  llvm::make_pointer_range(spec.getAttributes()));
246  trivial &= savedAttrs.empty();
247  hasSavedAttrs = true;
248  }
249 
250  /// Record that we had nowhere to put the given type attribute.
251  /// We will diagnose such attributes later.
252  void addIgnoredTypeAttr(ParsedAttr &attr) {
253  ignoredTypeAttrs.push_back(&attr);
254  }
255 
256  /// Diagnose all the ignored type attributes, given that the
257  /// declarator worked out to the given type.
258  void diagnoseIgnoredTypeAttrs(QualType type) const {
259  for (auto *Attr : ignoredTypeAttrs)
260  diagnoseBadTypeAttribute(getSema(), *Attr, type);
261  }
262 
263  /// Get an attributed type for the given attribute, and remember the Attr
264  /// object so that we can attach it to the AttributedTypeLoc.
265  QualType getAttributedType(Attr *A, QualType ModifiedType,
266  QualType EquivType) {
267  QualType T =
268  sema.Context.getAttributedType(A->getKind(), ModifiedType, EquivType);
269  AttrsForTypes.push_back({cast<AttributedType>(T.getTypePtr()), A});
270  AttrsForTypesSorted = false;
271  return T;
272  }
273 
274  /// Get a BTFTagAttributed type for the btf_type_tag attribute.
275  QualType getBTFTagAttributedType(const BTFTypeTagAttr *BTFAttr,
276  QualType WrappedType) {
277  return sema.Context.getBTFTagAttributedType(BTFAttr, WrappedType);
278  }
279 
280  /// Completely replace the \c auto in \p TypeWithAuto by
281  /// \p Replacement. Also replace \p TypeWithAuto in \c TypeAttrPair if
282  /// necessary.
283  QualType ReplaceAutoType(QualType TypeWithAuto, QualType Replacement) {
284  QualType T = sema.ReplaceAutoType(TypeWithAuto, Replacement);
285  if (auto *AttrTy = TypeWithAuto->getAs<AttributedType>()) {
286  // Attributed type still should be an attributed type after replacement.
287  auto *NewAttrTy = cast<AttributedType>(T.getTypePtr());
288  for (TypeAttrPair &A : AttrsForTypes) {
289  if (A.first == AttrTy)
290  A.first = NewAttrTy;
291  }
292  AttrsForTypesSorted = false;
293  }
294  return T;
295  }
296 
297  /// Extract and remove the Attr* for a given attributed type.
298  const Attr *takeAttrForAttributedType(const AttributedType *AT) {
299  if (!AttrsForTypesSorted) {
300  llvm::stable_sort(AttrsForTypes, llvm::less_first());
301  AttrsForTypesSorted = true;
302  }
303 
304  // FIXME: This is quadratic if we have lots of reuses of the same
305  // attributed type.
306  for (auto It = std::partition_point(
307  AttrsForTypes.begin(), AttrsForTypes.end(),
308  [=](const TypeAttrPair &A) { return A.first < AT; });
309  It != AttrsForTypes.end() && It->first == AT; ++It) {
310  if (It->second) {
311  const Attr *Result = It->second;
312  It->second = nullptr;
313  return Result;
314  }
315  }
316 
317  llvm_unreachable("no Attr* for AttributedType*");
318  }
319 
320  SourceLocation
321  getExpansionLocForMacroQualifiedType(const MacroQualifiedType *MQT) const {
322  auto FoundLoc = LocsForMacros.find(MQT);
323  assert(FoundLoc != LocsForMacros.end() &&
324  "Unable to find macro expansion location for MacroQualifedType");
325  return FoundLoc->second;
326  }
327 
328  void setExpansionLocForMacroQualifiedType(const MacroQualifiedType *MQT,
329  SourceLocation Loc) {
330  LocsForMacros[MQT] = Loc;
331  }
332 
333  void setParsedNoDeref(bool parsed) { parsedNoDeref = parsed; }
334 
335  bool didParseNoDeref() const { return parsedNoDeref; }
336 
337  ~TypeProcessingState() {
338  if (trivial) return;
339 
340  restoreDeclSpecAttrs();
341  }
342 
343  private:
344  DeclSpec &getMutableDeclSpec() const {
345  return const_cast<DeclSpec&>(declarator.getDeclSpec());
346  }
347 
348  void restoreDeclSpecAttrs() {
349  assert(hasSavedAttrs);
350 
351  getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes().clearListOnly();
352  for (ParsedAttr *AL : savedAttrs)
353  getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes().addAtEnd(AL);
354  }
355  };
356 } // end anonymous namespace
357 
358 static void moveAttrFromListToList(ParsedAttr &attr,
359  ParsedAttributesView &fromList,
360  ParsedAttributesView &toList) {
361  fromList.remove(&attr);
362  toList.addAtEnd(&attr);
363 }

365 /// The location of a type attribute.
366 enum TypeAttrLocation {
367  /// The attribute is in the decl-specifier-seq.
368  TAL_DeclSpec,
369  /// The attribute is part of a DeclaratorChunk.
370  TAL_DeclChunk,
371  /// The attribute is immediately after the declaration's name.
372  TAL_DeclName
373 };
374 
375 static void processTypeAttrs(TypeProcessingState &state, QualType &type,
376  TypeAttrLocation TAL,
377  const ParsedAttributesView &attrs);
378 
379 static bool handleFunctionTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state, ParsedAttr &attr,
380  QualType &type);
381 
382 static bool handleMSPointerTypeQualifierAttr(TypeProcessingState &state,
383  ParsedAttr &attr, QualType &type);
384 
385 static bool handleObjCGCTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state, ParsedAttr &attr,
386  QualType &type);
387 
388 static bool handleObjCOwnershipTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state,
389  ParsedAttr &attr, QualType &type);
390 
391 static bool handleObjCPointerTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state,
392  ParsedAttr &attr, QualType &type) {
393  if (attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCGC)
394  return handleObjCGCTypeAttr(state, attr, type);
395  assert(attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership);
396  return handleObjCOwnershipTypeAttr(state, attr, type);
397 }
398 
399 /// Given the index of a declarator chunk, check whether that chunk
400 /// directly specifies the return type of a function and, if so, find
401 /// an appropriate place for it.
402 ///
403 /// \param i - a notional index which the search will start
404 /// immediately inside
405 ///
406 /// \param onlyBlockPointers Whether we should only look into block
407 /// pointer types (vs. all pointer types).
408 static DeclaratorChunk *maybeMovePastReturnType(Declarator &declarator,
409  unsigned i,
410  bool onlyBlockPointers) {
411  assert(i <= declarator.getNumTypeObjects());
412 
413  DeclaratorChunk *result = nullptr;
414 
415  // First, look inwards past parens for a function declarator.
416  for (; i != 0; --i) {
417  DeclaratorChunk &fnChunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i-1);
418  switch (fnChunk.Kind) {
419  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
420  continue;
421 
422  // If we find anything except a function, bail out.
423  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
424  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
425  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
426  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
427  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
428  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
429  return result;
430 
431  // If we do find a function declarator, scan inwards from that,
432  // looking for a (block-)pointer declarator.
433  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
434  for (--i; i != 0; --i) {
435  DeclaratorChunk &ptrChunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i-1);
436  switch (ptrChunk.Kind) {
437  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
438  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
439  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
440  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
441  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
442  continue;
443 
444  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
445  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
446  if (onlyBlockPointers)
447  continue;
448 
449  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
450 
451  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
452  result = &ptrChunk;
453  goto continue_outer;
454  }
455  llvm_unreachable("bad declarator chunk kind");
456  }
457 
458  // If we run out of declarators doing that, we're done.
459  return result;
460  }
461  llvm_unreachable("bad declarator chunk kind");
462 
463  // Okay, reconsider from our new point.
464  continue_outer: ;
465  }
466 
467  // Ran out of chunks, bail out.
468  return result;
469 }
470 
471 /// Given that an objc_gc attribute was written somewhere on a
472 /// declaration *other* than on the declarator itself (for which, use
473 /// distributeObjCPointerTypeAttrFromDeclarator), and given that it
474 /// didn't apply in whatever position it was written in, try to move
475 /// it to a more appropriate position.
476 static void distributeObjCPointerTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state,
477  ParsedAttr &attr, QualType type) {
478  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
479 
480  // Move it to the outermost normal or block pointer declarator.
481  for (unsigned i = state.getCurrentChunkIndex(); i != 0; --i) {
482  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i-1);
483  switch (chunk.Kind) {
484  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
485  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer: {
486  // But don't move an ARC ownership attribute to the return type
487  // of a block.
488  DeclaratorChunk *destChunk = nullptr;
489  if (state.isProcessingDeclSpec() &&
490  attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership)
491  destChunk = maybeMovePastReturnType(declarator, i - 1,
492  /*onlyBlockPointers=*/true);
493  if (!destChunk) destChunk = &chunk;
494 
495  moveAttrFromListToList(attr, state.getCurrentAttributes(),
496  destChunk->getAttrs());
497  return;
498  }
499 
500  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
501  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
502  continue;
503 
504  // We may be starting at the return type of a block.
505  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
506  if (state.isProcessingDeclSpec() &&
507  attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership) {
508  if (DeclaratorChunk *dest = maybeMovePastReturnType(
509  declarator, i,
510  /*onlyBlockPointers=*/true)) {
511  moveAttrFromListToList(attr, state.getCurrentAttributes(),
512  dest->getAttrs());
513  return;
514  }
515  }
516  goto error;
517 
518  // Don't walk through these.
519  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
520  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
521  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
522  goto error;
523  }
524  }
525  error:
526 
527  diagnoseBadTypeAttribute(state.getSema(), attr, type);
528 }
529 
530 /// Distribute an objc_gc type attribute that was written on the
531 /// declarator.
532 static void distributeObjCPointerTypeAttrFromDeclarator(
533  TypeProcessingState &state, ParsedAttr &attr, QualType &declSpecType) {
534  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
535 
536  // objc_gc goes on the innermost pointer to something that's not a
537  // pointer.
538  unsigned innermost = -1U;
539  bool considerDeclSpec = true;
540  for (unsigned i = 0, e = declarator.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
541  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i);
542  switch (chunk.Kind) {
543  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
544  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
545  innermost = i;
546  continue;
547 
548  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
549  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
550  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
551  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
552  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
553  continue;
554 
555  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
556  considerDeclSpec = false;
557  goto done;
558  }
559  }
560  done:
561 
562  // That might actually be the decl spec if we weren't blocked by
563  // anything in the declarator.
564  if (considerDeclSpec) {
565  if (handleObjCPointerTypeAttr(state, attr, declSpecType)) {
566  // Splice the attribute into the decl spec. Prevents the
567  // attribute from being applied multiple times and gives
568  // the source-location-filler something to work with.
569  state.saveDeclSpecAttrs();
570  declarator.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes().takeOneFrom(
571  declarator.getAttributes(), &attr);
572  return;
573  }
574  }
575 
576  // Otherwise, if we found an appropriate chunk, splice the attribute
577  // into it.
578  if (innermost != -1U) {
579  moveAttrFromListToList(attr, declarator.getAttributes(),
580  declarator.getTypeObject(innermost).getAttrs());
581  return;
582  }
583 
584  // Otherwise, diagnose when we're done building the type.
585  declarator.getAttributes().remove(&attr);
586  state.addIgnoredTypeAttr(attr);
587 }
588 
589 /// A function type attribute was written somewhere in a declaration
590 /// *other* than on the declarator itself or in the decl spec. Given
591 /// that it didn't apply in whatever position it was written in, try
592 /// to move it to a more appropriate position.
593 static void distributeFunctionTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state,
594  ParsedAttr &attr, QualType type) {
595  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
596 
597  // Try to push the attribute from the return type of a function to
598  // the function itself.
599  for (unsigned i = state.getCurrentChunkIndex(); i != 0; --i) {
600  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i-1);
601  switch (chunk.Kind) {
602  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
603  moveAttrFromListToList(attr, state.getCurrentAttributes(),
604  chunk.getAttrs());
605  return;
606 
607  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
608  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
609  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
610  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
611  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
612  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
613  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
614  continue;
615  }
616  }
617 
618  diagnoseBadTypeAttribute(state.getSema(), attr, type);
619 }
620 
621 /// Try to distribute a function type attribute to the innermost
622 /// function chunk or type. Returns true if the attribute was
623 /// distributed, false if no location was found.
624 static bool distributeFunctionTypeAttrToInnermost(
625  TypeProcessingState &state, ParsedAttr &attr,
626  ParsedAttributesView &attrList, QualType &declSpecType) {
627  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
628 
629  // Put it on the innermost function chunk, if there is one.
630  for (unsigned i = 0, e = declarator.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
631  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i);
632  if (chunk.Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Function) continue;
633 
634  moveAttrFromListToList(attr, attrList, chunk.getAttrs());
635  return true;
636  }
637 
638  return handleFunctionTypeAttr(state, attr, declSpecType);
639 }
640 
641 /// A function type attribute was written in the decl spec. Try to
642 /// apply it somewhere.
643 static void distributeFunctionTypeAttrFromDeclSpec(TypeProcessingState &state,
644  ParsedAttr &attr,
645  QualType &declSpecType) {
646  state.saveDeclSpecAttrs();
647 
648  // C++11 attributes before the decl specifiers actually appertain to
649  // the declarators. Move them straight there. We don't support the
650  // 'put them wherever you like' semantics we allow for GNU attributes.
651  if (attr.isStandardAttributeSyntax()) {
652  moveAttrFromListToList(attr, state.getCurrentAttributes(),
653  state.getDeclarator().getAttributes());
654  return;
655  }
656 
657  // Try to distribute to the innermost.
658  if (distributeFunctionTypeAttrToInnermost(
659  state, attr, state.getCurrentAttributes(), declSpecType))
660  return;
661 
662  // If that failed, diagnose the bad attribute when the declarator is
663  // fully built.
664  state.addIgnoredTypeAttr(attr);
665 }
666 
667 /// A function type attribute was written on the declarator. Try to
668 /// apply it somewhere.
669 static void distributeFunctionTypeAttrFromDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &state,
670  ParsedAttr &attr,
671  QualType &declSpecType) {
672  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
673 
674  // Try to distribute to the innermost.
675  if (distributeFunctionTypeAttrToInnermost(
676  state, attr, declarator.getAttributes(), declSpecType))
677  return;
678 
679  // If that failed, diagnose the bad attribute when the declarator is
680  // fully built.
681  declarator.getAttributes().remove(&attr);
682  state.addIgnoredTypeAttr(attr);
683 }
684 
685 /// Given that there are attributes written on the declarator
686 /// itself, try to distribute any type attributes to the appropriate
687 /// declarator chunk.
688 ///
689 /// These are attributes like the following:
690 /// int f ATTR;
691 /// int (f ATTR)();
692 /// but not necessarily this:
693 /// int f() ATTR;
694 static void distributeTypeAttrsFromDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &state,
695  QualType &declSpecType) {
696  // Collect all the type attributes from the declarator itself.
697  assert(!state.getDeclarator().getAttributes().empty() &&
698  "declarator has no attrs!");
699  // The called functions in this loop actually remove things from the current
700  // list, so iterating over the existing list isn't possible. Instead, make a
701  // non-owning copy and iterate over that.
702  ParsedAttributesView AttrsCopy{state.getDeclarator().getAttributes()};
703  for (ParsedAttr &attr : AttrsCopy) {
704  // Do not distribute [[]] attributes. They have strict rules for what
705  // they appertain to.
706  if (attr.isStandardAttributeSyntax())
707  continue;
708 
709  switch (attr.getKind()) {
710  OBJC_POINTER_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST:
711  distributeObjCPointerTypeAttrFromDeclarator(state, attr, declSpecType);
712  break;
713 
714  FUNCTION_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST:
715  distributeFunctionTypeAttrFromDeclarator(state, attr, declSpecType);
716  break;
717 
718  MS_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST:
719  // Microsoft type attributes cannot go after the declarator-id.
720  continue;
721 
722  NULLABILITY_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST:
723  // Nullability specifiers cannot go after the declarator-id.
724 
725  // Objective-C __kindof does not get distributed.
726  case ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCKindOf:
727  continue;
728 
729  default:
730  break;
731  }
732  }
733 }
734 
735 /// Add a synthetic '()' to a block-literal declarator if it is
736 /// required, given the return type.
737 static void maybeSynthesizeBlockSignature(TypeProcessingState &state,
738  QualType declSpecType) {
739  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
740 
741  // First, check whether the declarator would produce a function,
742  // i.e. whether the innermost semantic chunk is a function.
743  if (declarator.isFunctionDeclarator()) {
744  // If so, make that declarator a prototyped declarator.
745  declarator.getFunctionTypeInfo().hasPrototype = true;
746  return;
747  }
748 
749  // If there are any type objects, the type as written won't name a
750  // function, regardless of the decl spec type. This is because a
751  // block signature declarator is always an abstract-declarator, and
752  // abstract-declarators can't just be parentheses chunks. Therefore
753  // we need to build a function chunk unless there are no type
754  // objects and the decl spec type is a function.
755  if (!declarator.getNumTypeObjects() && declSpecType->isFunctionType())
756  return;
757 
758  // Note that there *are* cases with invalid declarators where
759  // declarators consist solely of parentheses. In general, these
760  // occur only in failed efforts to make function declarators, so
761  // faking up the function chunk is still the right thing to do.
762 
763  // Otherwise, we need to fake up a function declarator.
764  SourceLocation loc = declarator.getBeginLoc();
765 
766  // ...and *prepend* it to the declarator.
767  SourceLocation NoLoc;
768  declarator.AddInnermostTypeInfo(DeclaratorChunk::getFunction(
769  /*HasProto=*/true,
770  /*IsAmbiguous=*/false,
771  /*LParenLoc=*/NoLoc,
772  /*ArgInfo=*/nullptr,
773  /*NumParams=*/0,
774  /*EllipsisLoc=*/NoLoc,
775  /*RParenLoc=*/NoLoc,
776  /*RefQualifierIsLvalueRef=*/true,
777  /*RefQualifierLoc=*/NoLoc,
778  /*MutableLoc=*/NoLoc, EST_None,
779  /*ESpecRange=*/SourceRange(),
780  /*Exceptions=*/nullptr,
781  /*ExceptionRanges=*/nullptr,
782  /*NumExceptions=*/0,
783  /*NoexceptExpr=*/nullptr,
784  /*ExceptionSpecTokens=*/nullptr,
785  /*DeclsInPrototype=*/None, loc, loc, declarator));
786 
787  // For consistency, make sure the state still has us as processing
788  // the decl spec.
789  assert(state.getCurrentChunkIndex() == declarator.getNumTypeObjects() - 1);
790  state.setCurrentChunkIndex(declarator.getNumTypeObjects());
791 }
792 
793 static void diagnoseAndRemoveTypeQualifiers(Sema &S, const DeclSpec &DS,
794  unsigned &TypeQuals,
795  QualType TypeSoFar,
796  unsigned RemoveTQs,
797  unsigned DiagID) {
798  // If this occurs outside a template instantiation, warn the user about
799  // it; they probably didn't mean to specify a redundant qualifier.
800  typedef std::pair<DeclSpec::TQ, SourceLocation> QualLoc;
801  for (QualLoc Qual : {QualLoc(DeclSpec::TQ_const, DS.getConstSpecLoc()),
802  QualLoc(DeclSpec::TQ_restrict, DS.getRestrictSpecLoc()),
803  QualLoc(DeclSpec::TQ_volatile, DS.getVolatileSpecLoc()),
804  QualLoc(DeclSpec::TQ_atomic, DS.getAtomicSpecLoc())}) {
805  if (!(RemoveTQs & Qual.first))
806  continue;
807 
808  if (!S.inTemplateInstantiation()) {
809  if (TypeQuals & Qual.first)
810  S.Diag(Qual.second, DiagID)
811  << DeclSpec::getSpecifierName(Qual.first) << TypeSoFar
812  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Qual.second);
813  }
814 
815  TypeQuals &= ~Qual.first;
816  }
817 }
818 
819 /// Return true if this is omitted block return type. Also check type
820 /// attributes and type qualifiers when returning true.
821 static bool checkOmittedBlockReturnType(Sema &S, Declarator &declarator,
822  QualType Result) {
823  if (!isOmittedBlockReturnType(declarator))
824  return false;
825 
826  // Warn if we see type attributes for omitted return type on a block literal.
827  SmallVector<ParsedAttr *, 2> ToBeRemoved;
828  for (ParsedAttr &AL : declarator.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes()) {
829  if (AL.isInvalid() || !AL.isTypeAttr())
830  continue;
831  S.Diag(AL.getLoc(),
832  diag::warn_block_literal_attributes_on_omitted_return_type)
833  << AL;
834  ToBeRemoved.push_back(&AL);
835  }
836  // Remove bad attributes from the list.
837  for (ParsedAttr *AL : ToBeRemoved)
838  declarator.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes().remove(AL);
839 
840  // Warn if we see type qualifiers for omitted return type on a block literal.
841  const DeclSpec &DS = declarator.getDeclSpec();
842  unsigned TypeQuals = DS.getTypeQualifiers();
843  diagnoseAndRemoveTypeQualifiers(S, DS, TypeQuals, Result, (unsigned)-1,
844  diag::warn_block_literal_qualifiers_on_omitted_return_type);
845  declarator.getMutableDeclSpec().ClearTypeQualifiers();
846 
847  return true;
848 }
849 
850 /// Apply Objective-C type arguments to the given type.
851 static QualType applyObjCTypeArgs(Sema &S, SourceLocation loc, QualType type,
852  ArrayRef<TypeSourceInfo *> typeArgs,
853  SourceRange typeArgsRange,
854  bool failOnError = false) {
855  // We can only apply type arguments to an Objective-C class type.
856  const auto *objcObjectType = type->getAs<ObjCObjectType>();
857  if (!objcObjectType || !objcObjectType->getInterface()) {
858  S.Diag(loc, diag::err_objc_type_args_non_class)
859  << type
860  << typeArgsRange;
861 
862  if (failOnError)
863  return QualType();
864  return type;
865  }
866 
867  // The class type must be parameterized.
868  ObjCInterfaceDecl *objcClass = objcObjectType->getInterface();
869  ObjCTypeParamList *typeParams = objcClass->getTypeParamList();
870  if (!typeParams) {
871  S.Diag(loc, diag::err_objc_type_args_non_parameterized_class)
872  << objcClass->getDeclName()
873  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(typeArgsRange);
874 
875  if (failOnError)
876  return QualType();
877 
878  return type;
879  }
880 
881  // The type must not already be specialized.
882  if (objcObjectType->isSpecialized()) {
883  S.Diag(loc, diag::err_objc_type_args_specialized_class)
884  << type
885  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(typeArgsRange);
886 
887  if (failOnError)
888  return QualType();
889 
890  return type;
891  }
892 
893  // Check the type arguments.
894  SmallVector<QualType, 4> finalTypeArgs;
895  unsigned numTypeParams = typeParams->size();
896  bool anyPackExpansions = false;
897  for (unsigned i = 0, n = typeArgs.size(); i != n; ++i) {
898  TypeSourceInfo *typeArgInfo = typeArgs[i];
899  QualType typeArg = typeArgInfo->getType();
900 
901  // Type arguments cannot have explicit qualifiers or nullability.
902  // We ignore indirect sources of these, e.g. behind typedefs or
903  // template arguments.
904  if (TypeLoc qual = typeArgInfo->getTypeLoc().findExplicitQualifierLoc()) {
905  bool diagnosed = false;
906  SourceRange rangeToRemove;
907  if (auto attr = qual.getAs<AttributedTypeLoc>()) {
908  rangeToRemove = attr.getLocalSourceRange();
909  if (attr.getTypePtr()->getImmediateNullability()) {
910  typeArg = attr.getTypePtr()->getModifiedType();
911  S.Diag(attr.getBeginLoc(),
912  diag::err_objc_type_arg_explicit_nullability)
913  << typeArg << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(rangeToRemove);
914  diagnosed = true;
915  }
916  }
917 
918  if (!diagnosed) {
919  S.Diag(qual.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_objc_type_arg_qualified)
920  << typeArg << typeArg.getQualifiers().getAsString()
921  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(rangeToRemove);
922  }
923  }
924 
925  // Remove qualifiers even if they're non-local.
926  typeArg = typeArg.getUnqualifiedType();
927 
928  finalTypeArgs.push_back(typeArg);
929 
930  if (typeArg->getAs<PackExpansionType>())
931  anyPackExpansions = true;
932 
933  // Find the corresponding type parameter, if there is one.
934  ObjCTypeParamDecl *typeParam = nullptr;
935  if (!anyPackExpansions) {
936  if (i < numTypeParams) {
937  typeParam = typeParams->begin()[i];
938  } else {
939  // Too many arguments.
940  S.Diag(loc, diag::err_objc_type_args_wrong_arity)
941  << false
942  << objcClass->getDeclName()
943  << (unsigned)typeArgs.size()
944  << numTypeParams;
945  S.Diag(objcClass->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
946  << objcClass;
947 
948  if (failOnError)
949  return QualType();
950 
951  return type;
952  }
953  }
954 
955  // Objective-C object pointer types must be substitutable for the bounds.
956  if (const auto *typeArgObjC = typeArg->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
957  // If we don't have a type parameter to match against, assume
958  // everything is fine. There was a prior pack expansion that
959  // means we won't be able to match anything.
960  if (!typeParam) {
961  assert(anyPackExpansions && "Too many arguments?");
962  continue;
963  }
964 
965  // Retrieve the bound.
966  QualType bound = typeParam->getUnderlyingType();
967  const auto *boundObjC = bound->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
968 
969  // Determine whether the type argument is substitutable for the bound.
970  if (typeArgObjC->isObjCIdType()) {
971  // When the type argument is 'id', the only acceptable type
972  // parameter bound is 'id'.
973  if (boundObjC->isObjCIdType())
974  continue;
975  } else if (S.Context.canAssignObjCInterfaces(boundObjC, typeArgObjC)) {
976  // Otherwise, we follow the assignability rules.
977  continue;
978  }
979 
980  // Diagnose the mismatch.
981  S.Diag(typeArgInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
982  diag::err_objc_type_arg_does_not_match_bound)
983  << typeArg << bound << typeParam->getDeclName();
984  S.Diag(typeParam->getLocation(), diag::note_objc_type_param_here)
985  << typeParam->getDeclName();
986 
987  if (failOnError)
988  return QualType();
989 
990  return type;
991  }
992 
993  // Block pointer types are permitted for unqualified 'id' bounds.
994  if (typeArg->isBlockPointerType()) {
995  // If we don't have a type parameter to match against, assume
996  // everything is fine. There was a prior pack expansion that
997  // means we won't be able to match anything.
998  if (!typeParam) {
999  assert(anyPackExpansions && "Too many arguments?");
1000  continue;
1001  }
1002 
1003  // Retrieve the bound.
1004  QualType bound = typeParam->getUnderlyingType();
1005  if (bound->isBlockCompatibleObjCPointerType(S.Context))
1006  continue;
1007 
1008  // Diagnose the mismatch.
1009  S.Diag(typeArgInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
1010  diag::err_objc_type_arg_does_not_match_bound)
1011  << typeArg << bound << typeParam->getDeclName();
1012  S.Diag(typeParam->getLocation(), diag::note_objc_type_param_here)
1013  << typeParam->getDeclName();
1014 
1015  if (failOnError)
1016  return QualType();
1017 
1018  return type;
1019  }
1020 
1021  // Dependent types will be checked at instantiation time.
1022  if (typeArg->isDependentType()) {
1023  continue;
1024  }
1025 
1026  // Diagnose non-id-compatible type arguments.
1027  S.Diag(typeArgInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
1028  diag::err_objc_type_arg_not_id_compatible)
1029  << typeArg << typeArgInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange();
1030 
1031  if (failOnError)
1032  return QualType();
1033 
1034  return type;
1035  }
1036 
1037  // Make sure we didn't have the wrong number of arguments.
1038  if (!anyPackExpansions && finalTypeArgs.size() != numTypeParams) {
1039  S.Diag(loc, diag::err_objc_type_args_wrong_arity)
1040  << (typeArgs.size() < typeParams->size())
1041  << objcClass->getDeclName()
1042  << (unsigned)finalTypeArgs.size()
1043  << (unsigned)numTypeParams;
1044  S.Diag(objcClass->getLocation(), diag::note_previous_decl)
1045  << objcClass;
1046 
1047  if (failOnError)
1048  return QualType();
1049 
1050  return type;
1051  }
1052 
1053  // Success. Form the specialized type.
1054  return S.Context.getObjCObjectType(type, finalTypeArgs, { }, false);
1055 }
1056 
1057 QualType Sema::BuildObjCTypeParamType(const ObjCTypeParamDecl *Decl,
1058  SourceLocation ProtocolLAngleLoc,
1059  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> Protocols,
1060  ArrayRef<SourceLocation> ProtocolLocs,
1061  SourceLocation ProtocolRAngleLoc,
1062  bool FailOnError) {
1063  QualType Result = QualType(Decl->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
1064  if (!Protocols.empty()) {
1065  bool HasError;
1066  Result = Context.applyObjCProtocolQualifiers(Result, Protocols,
1067  HasError);
1068  if (HasError) {
1069  Diag(SourceLocation(), diag::err_invalid_protocol_qualifiers)
1070  << SourceRange(ProtocolLAngleLoc, ProtocolRAngleLoc);
1071  if (FailOnError) Result = QualType();
1072  }
1073  if (FailOnError && Result.isNull())
1074  return QualType();
1075  }
1076 
1077  return Result;
1078 }
1079 
1080 QualType Sema::BuildObjCObjectType(QualType BaseType,
1081  SourceLocation Loc,
1082  SourceLocation TypeArgsLAngleLoc,
1083  ArrayRef<TypeSourceInfo *> TypeArgs,
1084  SourceLocation TypeArgsRAngleLoc,
1085  SourceLocation ProtocolLAngleLoc,
1086  ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> Protocols,
1087  ArrayRef<SourceLocation> ProtocolLocs,
1088  SourceLocation ProtocolRAngleLoc,
1089  bool FailOnError) {
1090  QualType Result = BaseType;
1091  if (!TypeArgs.empty()) {
1092  Result = applyObjCTypeArgs(*this, Loc, Result, TypeArgs,
1093  SourceRange(TypeArgsLAngleLoc,
1094  TypeArgsRAngleLoc),
1095  FailOnError);
1096  if (FailOnError && Result.isNull())
1097  return QualType();
1098  }
1099 
1100  if (!Protocols.empty()) {
1101  bool HasError;
1102  Result = Context.applyObjCProtocolQualifiers(Result, Protocols,
1103  HasError);
1104  if (HasError) {
1105  Diag(Loc, diag::err_invalid_protocol_qualifiers)
1106  << SourceRange(ProtocolLAngleLoc, ProtocolRAngleLoc);
1107  if (FailOnError) Result = QualType();
1108  }
1109  if (FailOnError && Result.isNull())
1110  return QualType();
1111  }
1112 
1113  return Result;
1114 }
1115 
1116 TypeResult Sema::actOnObjCProtocolQualifierType(
1117  SourceLocation lAngleLoc,
1118  ArrayRef<Decl *> protocols,
1119  ArrayRef<SourceLocation> protocolLocs,
1120  SourceLocation rAngleLoc) {
1121  // Form id<protocol-list>.
1122  QualType Result = Context.getObjCObjectType(
1123  Context.ObjCBuiltinIdTy, { },
1124  llvm::makeArrayRef(
1125  (ObjCProtocolDecl * const *)protocols.data(),
1126  protocols.size()),
1127  false);
1128  Result = Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(Result);
1129 
1130  TypeSourceInfo *ResultTInfo = Context.CreateTypeSourceInfo(Result);
1131  TypeLoc ResultTL = ResultTInfo->getTypeLoc();
1132 
1133  auto ObjCObjectPointerTL = ResultTL.castAs<ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc>();
1134  ObjCObjectPointerTL.setStarLoc(SourceLocation()); // implicit
1135 
1136  auto ObjCObjectTL = ObjCObjectPointerTL.getPointeeLoc()
1137  .castAs<ObjCObjectTypeLoc>();
1138  ObjCObjectTL.setHasBaseTypeAsWritten(false);
1139  ObjCObjectTL.getBaseLoc().initialize(Context, SourceLocation());
1140 
1141  // No type arguments.
1142  ObjCObjectTL.setTypeArgsLAngleLoc(SourceLocation());
1143  ObjCObjectTL.setTypeArgsRAngleLoc(SourceLocation());
1144 
1145  // Fill in protocol qualifiers.
1146  ObjCObjectTL.setProtocolLAngleLoc(lAngleLoc);
1147  ObjCObjectTL.setProtocolRAngleLoc(rAngleLoc);
1148  for (unsigned i = 0, n = protocols.size(); i != n; ++i)
1149  ObjCObjectTL.setProtocolLoc(i, protocolLocs[i]);
1150 
1151  // We're done. Return the completed type to the parser.
1152  return CreateParsedType(Result, ResultTInfo);
1153 }
1154 
1155 TypeResult Sema::actOnObjCTypeArgsAndProtocolQualifiers(
1156  Scope *S,
1157  SourceLocation Loc,
1158  ParsedType BaseType,
1159  SourceLocation TypeArgsLAngleLoc,
1160  ArrayRef<ParsedType> TypeArgs,
1161  SourceLocation TypeArgsRAngleLoc,
1162  SourceLocation ProtocolLAngleLoc,
1163  ArrayRef<Decl *> Protocols,
1164  ArrayRef<SourceLocation> ProtocolLocs,
1165  SourceLocation ProtocolRAngleLoc) {
1166  TypeSourceInfo *BaseTypeInfo = nullptr;
1167  QualType T = GetTypeFromParser(BaseType, &BaseTypeInfo);
1168  if (T.isNull())
1169  return true;
1170 
1171  // Handle missing type-source info.
1172  if (!BaseTypeInfo)
1173  BaseTypeInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, Loc);
1174 
1175  // Extract type arguments.
1176  SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 4> ActualTypeArgInfos;
1177  for (unsigned i = 0, n = TypeArgs.size(); i != n; ++i) {
1178  TypeSourceInfo *TypeArgInfo = nullptr;
1179  QualType TypeArg = GetTypeFromParser(TypeArgs[i], &TypeArgInfo);
1180  if (TypeArg.isNull()) {
1181  ActualTypeArgInfos.clear();
1182  break;
1183  }
1184 
1185  assert(TypeArgInfo && "No type source info?");
1186  ActualTypeArgInfos.push_back(TypeArgInfo);
1187  }
1188 
1189  // Build the object type.
1190  QualType Result = BuildObjCObjectType(
1191  T, BaseTypeInfo->getTypeLoc().getSourceRange().getBegin(),
1192  TypeArgsLAngleLoc, ActualTypeArgInfos, TypeArgsRAngleLoc,
1193  ProtocolLAngleLoc,
1194  llvm::makeArrayRef((ObjCProtocolDecl * const *)Protocols.data(),
1195  Protocols.size()),
1196  ProtocolLocs, ProtocolRAngleLoc,
1197  /*FailOnError=*/false);
1198 
1199  if (Result == T)
1200  return BaseType;
1201 
1202  // Create source information for this type.
1203  TypeSourceInfo *ResultTInfo = Context.CreateTypeSourceInfo(Result);
1204  TypeLoc ResultTL = ResultTInfo->getTypeLoc();
1205 
1206  // For id<Proto1, Proto2> or Class<Proto1, Proto2>, we'll have an
1207  // object pointer type. Fill in source information for it.
1208  if (auto ObjCObjectPointerTL = ResultTL.getAs<ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc>()) {
1209  // The '*' is implicit.
1210  ObjCObjectPointerTL.setStarLoc(SourceLocation());
1211  ResultTL = ObjCObjectPointerTL.getPointeeLoc();
1212  }
1213 
1214  if (auto OTPTL = ResultTL.getAs<ObjCTypeParamTypeLoc>()) {
1215  // Protocol qualifier information.
1216  if (OTPTL.getNumProtocols() > 0) {
1217  assert(OTPTL.getNumProtocols() == Protocols.size());
1218  OTPTL.setProtocolLAngleLoc(ProtocolLAngleLoc);
1219  OTPTL.setProtocolRAngleLoc(ProtocolRAngleLoc);
1220  for (unsigned i = 0, n = Protocols.size(); i != n; ++i)
1221  OTPTL.setProtocolLoc(i, ProtocolLocs[i]);
1222  }
1223 
1224  // We're done. Return the completed type to the parser.
1225  return CreateParsedType(Result, ResultTInfo);
1226  }
1227 
1228  auto ObjCObjectTL = ResultTL.castAs<ObjCObjectTypeLoc>();
1229 
1230  // Type argument information.
1231  if (ObjCObjectTL.getNumTypeArgs() > 0) {
1232  assert(ObjCObjectTL.getNumTypeArgs() == ActualTypeArgInfos.size());
1233  ObjCObjectTL.setTypeArgsLAngleLoc(TypeArgsLAngleLoc);
1234  ObjCObjectTL.setTypeArgsRAngleLoc(TypeArgsRAngleLoc);
1235  for (unsigned i = 0, n = ActualTypeArgInfos.size(); i != n; ++i)
1236  ObjCObjectTL.setTypeArgTInfo(i, ActualTypeArgInfos[i]);
1237  } else {
1238  ObjCObjectTL.setTypeArgsLAngleLoc(SourceLocation());
1239  ObjCObjectTL.setTypeArgsRAngleLoc(SourceLocation());
1240  }
1241 
1242  // Protocol qualifier information.
1243  if (ObjCObjectTL.getNumProtocols() > 0) {
1244  assert(ObjCObjectTL.getNumProtocols() == Protocols.size());
1245  ObjCObjectTL.setProtocolLAngleLoc(ProtocolLAngleLoc);
1246  ObjCObjectTL.setProtocolRAngleLoc(ProtocolRAngleLoc);
1247  for (unsigned i = 0, n = Protocols.size(); i != n; ++i)
1248  ObjCObjectTL.setProtocolLoc(i, ProtocolLocs[i]);
1249  } else {
1250  ObjCObjectTL.setProtocolLAngleLoc(SourceLocation());
1251  ObjCObjectTL.setProtocolRAngleLoc(SourceLocation());
1252  }
1253 
1254  // Base type.
1255  ObjCObjectTL.setHasBaseTypeAsWritten(true);
1256  if (ObjCObjectTL.getType() == T)
1257  ObjCObjectTL.getBaseLoc().initializeFullCopy(BaseTypeInfo->getTypeLoc());
1258  else
1259  ObjCObjectTL.getBaseLoc().initialize(Context, Loc);
1260 
1261  // We're done. Return the completed type to the parser.
1262  return CreateParsedType(Result, ResultTInfo);
1263 }

1265 static OpenCLAccessAttr::Spelling
1266 getImageAccess(const ParsedAttributesView &Attrs) {
1267  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : Attrs)
1268  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLAccess)
1269  return static_cast<OpenCLAccessAttr::Spelling>(AL.getSemanticSpelling());
1270  return OpenCLAccessAttr::Keyword_read_only;
1271 }
1272 
1273 /// Convert the specified declspec to the appropriate type
1274 /// object.
1275 /// \param state Specifies the declarator containing the declaration specifier
1276 /// to be converted, along with other associated processing state.
1277 /// \returns The type described by the declaration specifiers. This function
1278 /// never returns null.
1279 static QualType ConvertDeclSpecToType(TypeProcessingState &state) {
1280  // FIXME: Should move the logic from DeclSpec::Finish to here for validity
1281  // checking.
1282 
1283  Sema &S = state.getSema();
1284  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
1285  DeclSpec &DS = declarator.getMutableDeclSpec();
1286  SourceLocation DeclLoc = declarator.getIdentifierLoc();
1287  if (DeclLoc.isInvalid())
1288  DeclLoc = DS.getBeginLoc();
1289 
1290  ASTContext &Context = S.Context;
1291 
1292  QualType Result;
1293  switch (DS.getTypeSpecType()) {
1294  case DeclSpec::TST_void:
1295  Result = Context.VoidTy;
1296  break;
1297  case DeclSpec::TST_char:
1298  if (DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unspecified)
1299  Result = Context.CharTy;
1300  else if (DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Signed)
1301  Result = Context.SignedCharTy;
1302  else {
1303  assert(DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unsigned &&
1304  "Unknown TSS value");
1305  Result = Context.UnsignedCharTy;
1306  }
1307  break;
1308  case DeclSpec::TST_wchar:
1309  if (DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unspecified)
1310  Result = Context.WCharTy;
1311  else if (DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Signed) {
1312  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecSignLoc(), diag::ext_wchar_t_sign_spec)
1313  << DS.getSpecifierName(DS.getTypeSpecType(),
1314  Context.getPrintingPolicy());
1315  Result = Context.getSignedWCharType();
1316  } else {
1317  assert(DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unsigned &&
1318  "Unknown TSS value");
1319  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecSignLoc(), diag::ext_wchar_t_sign_spec)
1320  << DS.getSpecifierName(DS.getTypeSpecType(),
1321  Context.getPrintingPolicy());
1322  Result = Context.getUnsignedWCharType();
1323  }
1324  break;
1325  case DeclSpec::TST_char8:
1326  assert(DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unspecified &&
1327  "Unknown TSS value");
1328  Result = Context.Char8Ty;
1329  break;
1330  case DeclSpec::TST_char16:
1331  assert(DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unspecified &&
1332  "Unknown TSS value");
1333  Result = Context.Char16Ty;
1334  break;
1335  case DeclSpec::TST_char32:
1336  assert(DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unspecified &&
1337  "Unknown TSS value");
1338  Result = Context.Char32Ty;
1339  break;
1340  case DeclSpec::TST_unspecified:
1341  // If this is a missing declspec in a block literal return context, then it
1342  // is inferred from the return statements inside the block.
1343  // The declspec is always missing in a lambda expr context; it is either
1344  // specified with a trailing return type or inferred.
1345  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 &&
1346  declarator.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr) {
1347  // In C++1y, a lambda's implicit return type is 'auto'.
1348  Result = Context.getAutoDeductType();
1349  break;
1350  } else if (declarator.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr ||
1351  checkOmittedBlockReturnType(S, declarator,
1352  Context.DependentTy)) {
1353  Result = Context.DependentTy;
1354  break;
1355  }
1356 
1357  // Unspecified typespec defaults to int in C90. However, the C90 grammar
1358  // [C90 6.5] only allows a decl-spec if there was *some* type-specifier,
1359  // type-qualifier, or storage-class-specifier. If not, emit an extwarn.
1360  // Note that the one exception to this is function definitions, which are
1361  // allowed to be completely missing a declspec. This is handled in the
1362  // parser already though by it pretending to have seen an 'int' in this
1363  // case.
1364  if (S.getLangOpts().ImplicitInt) {
1365  // In C89 mode, we only warn if there is a completely missing declspec
1366  // when one is not allowed.
1367  if (DS.isEmpty()) {
1368  S.Diag(DeclLoc, diag::ext_missing_declspec)
1369  << DS.getSourceRange()
1370  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(DS.getBeginLoc(), "int");
1371  }
1372  } else if (!DS.hasTypeSpecifier()) {
1373  // C99 and C++ require a type specifier. For example, C99 6.7.2p2 says:
1374  // "At least one type specifier shall be given in the declaration
1375  // specifiers in each declaration, and in the specifier-qualifier list in
1376  // each struct declaration and type name."
1377  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && !DS.isTypeSpecPipe()) {
1378  S.Diag(DeclLoc, diag::err_missing_type_specifier)
1379  << DS.getSourceRange();
1380 
1381  // When this occurs in C++ code, often something is very broken with the
1382  // value being declared, poison it as invalid so we don't get chains of
1383  // errors.
1384  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1385  } else if ((S.getLangOpts().getOpenCLCompatibleVersion() >= 200 ||
1386  S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) &&
1387  DS.isTypeSpecPipe()) {
1388  S.Diag(DeclLoc, diag::err_missing_actual_pipe_type)
1389  << DS.getSourceRange();
1390  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1391  } else {
1392  S.Diag(DeclLoc, diag::ext_missing_type_specifier)
1393  << DS.getSourceRange();
1394  }
1395  }
1396 
1397  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1398  case DeclSpec::TST_int: {
1399  if (DS.getTypeSpecSign() != TypeSpecifierSign::Unsigned) {
1400  switch (DS.getTypeSpecWidth()) {
1401  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Unspecified:
1402  Result = Context.IntTy;
1403  break;
1404  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Short:
1405  Result = Context.ShortTy;
1406  break;
1407  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Long:
1408  Result = Context.LongTy;
1409  break;
1410  case TypeSpecifierWidth::LongLong:
1411  Result = Context.LongLongTy;
1412 
1413  // 'long long' is a C99 or C++11 feature.
1414  if (!S.getLangOpts().C99) {
1415  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
1416  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecWidthLoc(),
1417  S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ?
1418  diag::warn_cxx98_compat_longlong : diag::ext_cxx11_longlong);
1419  else
1420  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecWidthLoc(), diag::ext_c99_longlong);
1421  }
1422  break;
1423  }
1424  } else {
1425  switch (DS.getTypeSpecWidth()) {
1426  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Unspecified:
1427  Result = Context.UnsignedIntTy;
1428  break;
1429  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Short:
1430  Result = Context.UnsignedShortTy;
1431  break;
1432  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Long:
1433  Result = Context.UnsignedLongTy;
1434  break;
1435  case TypeSpecifierWidth::LongLong:
1436  Result = Context.UnsignedLongLongTy;
1437 
1438  // 'long long' is a C99 or C++11 feature.
1439  if (!S.getLangOpts().C99) {
1440  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
1441  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecWidthLoc(),
1442  S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ?
1443  diag::warn_cxx98_compat_longlong : diag::ext_cxx11_longlong);
1444  else
1445  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecWidthLoc(), diag::ext_c99_longlong);
1446  }
1447  break;
1448  }
1449  }
1450  break;
1451  }
1452  case DeclSpec::TST_bitint: {
1453  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasBitIntType())
1454  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_type_unsupported) << "_BitInt";
1455  Result =
1456  S.BuildBitIntType(DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unsigned,
1457  DS.getRepAsExpr(), DS.getBeginLoc());
1458  if (Result.isNull()) {
1459  Result = Context.IntTy;
1460  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1461  }
1462  break;
1463  }
1464  case DeclSpec::TST_accum: {
1465  switch (DS.getTypeSpecWidth()) {
1466  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Short:
1467  Result = Context.ShortAccumTy;
1468  break;
1469  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Unspecified:
1470  Result = Context.AccumTy;
1471  break;
1472  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Long:
1473  Result = Context.LongAccumTy;
1474  break;
1475  case TypeSpecifierWidth::LongLong:
1476  llvm_unreachable("Unable to specify long long as _Accum width");
1477  }
1478 
1479  if (DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unsigned)
1480  Result = Context.getCorrespondingUnsignedType(Result);
1481 
1482  if (DS.isTypeSpecSat())
1483  Result = Context.getCorrespondingSaturatedType(Result);
1484 
1485  break;
1486  }
1487  case DeclSpec::TST_fract: {
1488  switch (DS.getTypeSpecWidth()) {
1489  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Short:
1490  Result = Context.ShortFractTy;
1491  break;
1492  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Unspecified:
1493  Result = Context.FractTy;
1494  break;
1495  case TypeSpecifierWidth::Long:
1496  Result = Context.LongFractTy;
1497  break;
1498  case TypeSpecifierWidth::LongLong:
1499  llvm_unreachable("Unable to specify long long as _Fract width");
1500  }
1501 
1502  if (DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unsigned)
1503  Result = Context.getCorrespondingUnsignedType(Result);
1504 
1505  if (DS.isTypeSpecSat())
1506  Result = Context.getCorrespondingSaturatedType(Result);
1507 
1508  break;
1509  }
1510  case DeclSpec::TST_int128:
1511  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasInt128Type() &&
1512  !(S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice || S.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice ||
1513  (S.getLangOpts().OpenMP && S.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice)))
1514  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_type_unsupported)
1515  << "__int128";
1516  if (DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unsigned)
1517  Result = Context.UnsignedInt128Ty;
1518  else
1519  Result = Context.Int128Ty;
1520  break;
1521  case DeclSpec::TST_float16:
1522  {
1523  // CUDA host and device may have different _Float16 support, therefore
1524  // do not diagnose _Float16 usage to avoid false alarm.
1525  // ToDo: more precise diagnostics for CUDA.
1526  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFloat16Type() &&
1527  !S.getLangOpts().CUDA &&
1528  !(S.getLangOpts().OpenMP && S.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice))
1529  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_type_unsupported)
1530  << "_Float16";
1531  }
1532  Result = Context.Float16Ty;
1533  break;
1534  case DeclSpec::TST_half: Result = Context.HalfTy; break;
1535  case DeclSpec::TST_BFloat16:
1536  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasBFloat16Type())
1537  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_type_unsupported)
1538  << "__bf16";
1539  Result = Context.BFloat16Ty;
1540  break;
1541  case DeclSpec::TST_float: Result = Context.FloatTy; break;
1542  case DeclSpec::TST_double:
1543  if (DS.getTypeSpecWidth() == TypeSpecifierWidth::Long)
1544  Result = Context.LongDoubleTy;
1545  else
1546  Result = Context.DoubleTy;
1547  if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
1548  if (!S.getOpenCLOptions().isSupported("cl_khr_fp64", S.getLangOpts()))
1549  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_opencl_requires_extension)
1550  << 0 << Result
1551  << (S.getLangOpts().getOpenCLCompatibleVersion() == 300
1552  ? "cl_khr_fp64 and __opencl_c_fp64"
1553  : "cl_khr_fp64");
1554  else if (!S.getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption("cl_khr_fp64", S.getLangOpts()))
1555  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::ext_opencl_double_without_pragma);
1556  }
1557  break;
1558  case DeclSpec::TST_float128:
1559  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFloat128Type() &&
1560  !S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
1561  !(S.getLangOpts().OpenMP && S.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice))
1562  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_type_unsupported)
1563  << "__float128";
1564  Result = Context.Float128Ty;
1565  break;
1566  case DeclSpec::TST_ibm128:
1567  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasIbm128Type() &&
1568  !S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice &&
1569  !(S.getLangOpts().OpenMP && S.getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice))
1570  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_type_unsupported) << "__ibm128";
1571  Result = Context.Ibm128Ty;
1572  break;
1573  case DeclSpec::TST_bool:
1574  Result = Context.BoolTy; // _Bool or bool
1575  break;
1576  case DeclSpec::TST_decimal32: // _Decimal32
1577  case DeclSpec::TST_decimal64: // _Decimal64
1578  case DeclSpec::TST_decimal128: // _Decimal128
1579  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_decimal_unsupported);
1580  Result = Context.IntTy;
1581  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1582  break;
1583  case DeclSpec::TST_class:
1584  case DeclSpec::TST_enum:
1585  case DeclSpec::TST_union:
1586  case DeclSpec::TST_struct:
1587  case DeclSpec::TST_interface: {
1588  TagDecl *D = dyn_cast_or_null<TagDecl>(DS.getRepAsDecl());
1589  if (!D) {
1590  // This can happen in C++ with ambiguous lookups.
1591  Result = Context.IntTy;
1592  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1593  break;
1594  }
1595 
1596  // If the type is deprecated or unavailable, diagnose it.
1597  S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(D, DS.getTypeSpecTypeNameLoc());
1598 
1599  assert(DS.getTypeSpecWidth() == TypeSpecifierWidth::Unspecified &&
1600  DS.getTypeSpecComplex() == 0 &&
1601  DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unspecified &&
1602  "No qualifiers on tag names!");
1603 
1604  // TypeQuals handled by caller.
1605  Result = Context.getTypeDeclType(D);
1606 
1607  // In both C and C++, make an ElaboratedType.
1608  ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword
1609  = ElaboratedType::getKeywordForTypeSpec(DS.getTypeSpecType());
1610  Result = S.getElaboratedType(Keyword, DS.getTypeSpecScope(), Result,
1611  DS.isTypeSpecOwned() ? D : nullptr);
1612  break;
1613  }
1614  case DeclSpec::TST_typename: {
1615  assert(DS.getTypeSpecWidth() == TypeSpecifierWidth::Unspecified &&
1616  DS.getTypeSpecComplex() == 0 &&
1617  DS.getTypeSpecSign() == TypeSpecifierSign::Unspecified &&
1618  "Can't handle qualifiers on typedef names yet!");
1619  Result = S.GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType());
1620  if (Result.isNull()) {
1621  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1622  }
1623 
1624  // TypeQuals handled by caller.
1625  break;
1626  }
1627  case DeclSpec::TST_typeofType:
1628  // FIXME: Preserve type source info.
1629  Result = S.GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType());
1630  assert(!Result.isNull() && "Didn't get a type for typeof?");
1631  if (!Result->isDependentType())
1632  if (const TagType *TT = Result->getAs<TagType>())
1633  S.DiagnoseUseOfDecl(TT->getDecl(), DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
1634  // TypeQuals handled by caller.
1635  Result = Context.getTypeOfType(Result);
1636  break;
1637  case DeclSpec::TST_typeofExpr: {
1638  Expr *E = DS.getRepAsExpr();
1639  assert(E && "Didn't get an expression for typeof?");
1640  // TypeQuals handled by caller.
1641  Result = S.BuildTypeofExprType(E);
1642  if (Result.isNull()) {
1643  Result = Context.IntTy;
1644  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1645  }
1646  break;
1647  }
1648  case DeclSpec::TST_decltype: {
1649  Expr *E = DS.getRepAsExpr();
1650  assert(E && "Didn't get an expression for decltype?");
1651  // TypeQuals handled by caller.
1652  Result = S.BuildDecltypeType(E);
1653  if (Result.isNull()) {
1654  Result = Context.IntTy;
1655  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1656  }
1657  break;
1658  }
1659  case DeclSpec::TST_underlyingType:
1660  Result = S.GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType());
1661  assert(!Result.isNull() && "Didn't get a type for __underlying_type?");
1662  Result = S.BuildUnaryTransformType(Result,
1663  UnaryTransformType::EnumUnderlyingType,
1664  DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
1665  if (Result.isNull()) {
1666  Result = Context.IntTy;
1667  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1668  }
1669  break;
1670 
1671  case DeclSpec::TST_auto:
1672  case DeclSpec::TST_decltype_auto: {
1673  auto AutoKW = DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_decltype_auto
1674  ? AutoTypeKeyword::DecltypeAuto
1675  : AutoTypeKeyword::Auto;
1676 
1677  ConceptDecl *TypeConstraintConcept = nullptr;
1678  llvm::SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 8> TemplateArgs;
1679  if (DS.isConstrainedAuto()) {
1680  if (TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = DS.getRepAsTemplateId()) {
1681  TypeConstraintConcept =
1682  cast<ConceptDecl>(TemplateId->Template.get().getAsTemplateDecl());
1683  TemplateArgumentListInfo TemplateArgsInfo;
1684  TemplateArgsInfo.setLAngleLoc(TemplateId->LAngleLoc);
1685  TemplateArgsInfo.setRAngleLoc(TemplateId->RAngleLoc);
1686  ASTTemplateArgsPtr TemplateArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
1687  TemplateId->NumArgs);
1688  S.translateTemplateArguments(TemplateArgsPtr, TemplateArgsInfo);
1689  for (const auto &ArgLoc : TemplateArgsInfo.arguments())
1690  TemplateArgs.push_back(ArgLoc.getArgument());
1691  } else {
1692  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1693  }
1694  }
1695  Result = S.Context.getAutoType(QualType(), AutoKW,
1696  /*IsDependent*/ false, /*IsPack=*/false,
1697  TypeConstraintConcept, TemplateArgs);
1698  break;
1699  }
1700 
1701  case DeclSpec::TST_auto_type:
1702  Result = Context.getAutoType(QualType(), AutoTypeKeyword::GNUAutoType, false);
1703  break;
1704 
1705  case DeclSpec::TST_unknown_anytype:
1706  Result = Context.UnknownAnyTy;
1707  break;
1708 
1709  case DeclSpec::TST_atomic:
1710  Result = S.GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType());
1711  assert(!Result.isNull() && "Didn't get a type for _Atomic?");
1712  Result = S.BuildAtomicType(Result, DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
1713  if (Result.isNull()) {
1714  Result = Context.IntTy;
1715  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1716  }
1717  break;
1718 
1719 #define GENERIC_IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id) \
1720  case DeclSpec::TST_##ImgType##_t: \
1721  switch (getImageAccess(DS.getAttributes())) { \
1722  case OpenCLAccessAttr::Keyword_write_only: \
1723  Result = Context.Id##WOTy; \
1724  break; \
1725  case OpenCLAccessAttr::Keyword_read_write: \
1726  Result = Context.Id##RWTy; \
1727  break; \
1728  case OpenCLAccessAttr::Keyword_read_only: \
1729  Result = Context.Id##ROTy; \
1730  break; \
1731  case OpenCLAccessAttr::SpellingNotCalculated: \
1732  llvm_unreachable("Spelling not yet calculated"); \
1733  } \
1734  break;
1735 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
1736 
1737  case DeclSpec::TST_error:
1738  Result = Context.IntTy;
1739  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1740  break;
1741  }
1742 
1743  // FIXME: we want resulting declarations to be marked invalid, but claiming
1744  // the type is invalid is too strong - e.g. it causes ActOnTypeName to return
1745  // a null type.
1746  if (Result->containsErrors())
1747  declarator.setInvalidType();
1748 
1749  if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
1750  const auto &OpenCLOptions = S.getOpenCLOptions();
1751  bool IsOpenCLC30Compatible =
1752  S.getLangOpts().getOpenCLCompatibleVersion() == 300;
1753  // OpenCL C v3.0 s6.3.3 - OpenCL image types require __opencl_c_images
1754  // support.
1755  // OpenCL C v3.0 s6.2.1 - OpenCL 3d image write types requires support
1756  // for OpenCL C 2.0, or OpenCL C 3.0 or newer and the
1757  // __opencl_c_3d_image_writes feature. OpenCL C v3.0 API s4.2 - For devices
1758  // that support OpenCL 3.0, cl_khr_3d_image_writes must be returned when and
1759  // only when the optional feature is supported
1760  if ((Result->isImageType() || Result->isSamplerT()) &&
1761  (IsOpenCLC30Compatible &&
1762  !OpenCLOptions.isSupported("__opencl_c_images", S.getLangOpts()))) {
1763  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_opencl_requires_extension)
1764  << 0 << Result << "__opencl_c_images";
1765  declarator.setInvalidType();
1766  } else if (Result->isOCLImage3dWOType() &&
1767  !OpenCLOptions.isSupported("cl_khr_3d_image_writes",
1768  S.getLangOpts())) {
1769  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc(), diag::err_opencl_requires_extension)
1770  << 0 << Result
1771  << (IsOpenCLC30Compatible
1772  ? "cl_khr_3d_image_writes and __opencl_c_3d_image_writes"
1773  : "cl_khr_3d_image_writes");
1774  declarator.setInvalidType();
1775  }
1776  }
1777 
1778  bool IsFixedPointType = DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_accum ||
1779  DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_fract;
1780 
1781  // Only fixed point types can be saturated
1782  if (DS.isTypeSpecSat() && !IsFixedPointType)
1783  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecSatLoc(), diag::err_invalid_saturation_spec)
1784  << DS.getSpecifierName(DS.getTypeSpecType(),
1785  Context.getPrintingPolicy());
1786 
1787  // Handle complex types.
1788  if (DS.getTypeSpecComplex() == DeclSpec::TSC_complex) {
1789  if (S.getLangOpts().Freestanding)
1790  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecComplexLoc(), diag::ext_freestanding_complex);
1791  Result = Context.getComplexType(Result);
1792  } else if (DS.isTypeAltiVecVector()) {
1793  unsigned typeSize = static_cast<unsigned>(Context.getTypeSize(Result));
1794  assert(typeSize > 0 && "type size for vector must be greater than 0 bits");
1795  VectorType::VectorKind VecKind = VectorType::AltiVecVector;
1796  if (DS.isTypeAltiVecPixel())
1797  VecKind = VectorType::AltiVecPixel;
1798  else if (DS.isTypeAltiVecBool())
1799  VecKind = VectorType::AltiVecBool;
1800  Result = Context.getVectorType(Result, 128/typeSize, VecKind);
1801  }
1802 
1803  // FIXME: Imaginary.
1804  if (DS.getTypeSpecComplex() == DeclSpec::TSC_imaginary)
1805  S.Diag(DS.getTypeSpecComplexLoc(), diag::err_imaginary_not_supported);
1806 
1807  // Before we process any type attributes, synthesize a block literal
1808  // function declarator if necessary.
1809  if (declarator.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteral)
1810  maybeSynthesizeBlockSignature(state, Result);
1811 
1812  // Apply any type attributes from the decl spec. This may cause the
1813  // list of type attributes to be temporarily saved while the type
1814  // attributes are pushed around.
1815  // pipe attributes will be handled later ( at GetFullTypeForDeclarator )
1816  if (!DS.isTypeSpecPipe())
1817  processTypeAttrs(state, Result, TAL_DeclSpec, DS.getAttributes());
1818 
1819  // Apply const/volatile/restrict qualifiers to T.
1820  if (unsigned TypeQuals = DS.getTypeQualifiers()) {
1821  // Warn about CV qualifiers on function types.
1822  // C99 6.7.3p8:
1823  // If the specification of a function type includes any type qualifiers,
1824  // the behavior is undefined.
1825  // C++11 [dcl.fct]p7:
1826  // The effect of a cv-qualifier-seq in a function declarator is not the
1827  // same as adding cv-qualification on top of the function type. In the
1828  // latter case, the cv-qualifiers are ignored.
1829  if (Result->isFunctionType()) {
1830  diagnoseAndRemoveTypeQualifiers(
1831  S, DS, TypeQuals, Result, DeclSpec::TQ_const | DeclSpec::TQ_volatile,
1832  S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus
1833  ? diag::warn_typecheck_function_qualifiers_ignored
1834  : diag::warn_typecheck_function_qualifiers_unspecified);
1835  // No diagnostic for 'restrict' or '_Atomic' applied to a
1836  // function type; we'll diagnose those later, in BuildQualifiedType.
1837  }
1838 
1839  // C++11 [dcl.ref]p1:
1840  // Cv-qualified references are ill-formed except when the
1841  // cv-qualifiers are introduced through the use of a typedef-name
1842  // or decltype-specifier, in which case the cv-qualifiers are ignored.
1843  //
1844  // There don't appear to be any other contexts in which a cv-qualified
1845  // reference type could be formed, so the 'ill-formed' clause here appears
1846  // to never happen.
1847  if (TypeQuals && Result->isReferenceType()) {
1848  diagnoseAndRemoveTypeQualifiers(
1849  S, DS, TypeQuals, Result,
1850  DeclSpec::TQ_const | DeclSpec::TQ_volatile | DeclSpec::TQ_atomic,
1851  diag::warn_typecheck_reference_qualifiers);
1852  }
1853 
1854  // C90 6.5.3 constraints: "The same type qualifier shall not appear more
1855  // than once in the same specifier-list or qualifier-list, either directly
1856  // or via one or more typedefs."
1857  if (!S.getLangOpts().C99 && !S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus
1858  && TypeQuals & Result.getCVRQualifiers()) {
1859  if (TypeQuals & DeclSpec::TQ_const && Result.isConstQualified()) {
1860  S.Diag(DS.getConstSpecLoc(), diag::ext_duplicate_declspec)
1861  << "const";
1862  }
1863 
1864  if (TypeQuals & DeclSpec::TQ_volatile && Result.isVolatileQualified()) {
1865  S.Diag(DS.getVolatileSpecLoc(), diag::ext_duplicate_declspec)
1866  << "volatile";
1867  }
1868 
1869  // C90 doesn't have restrict nor _Atomic, so it doesn't force us to
1870  // produce a warning in this case.
1871  }
1872 
1873  QualType Qualified = S.BuildQualifiedType(Result, DeclLoc, TypeQuals, &DS);
1874 
1875  // If adding qualifiers fails, just use the unqualified type.
1876  if (Qualified.isNull())
1877  declarator.setInvalidType(true);
1878  else
1879  Result = Qualified;
1880  }
1881 
1882  assert(!Result.isNull() && "This function should not return a null type");
1883  return Result;
1884 }
1885 
1886 static std::string getPrintableNameForEntity(DeclarationName Entity) {
1887  if (Entity)
1888  return Entity.getAsString();
1889 
1890  return "type name";
1891 }
1892 
1893 static bool isDependentOrGNUAutoType(QualType T) {
1894  if (T->isDependentType())
1895  return true;
1896 
1897  const auto *AT = dyn_cast<AutoType>(T);
1898  return AT && AT->isGNUAutoType();
1899 }
1900 
1901 QualType Sema::BuildQualifiedType(QualType T, SourceLocation Loc,
1902  Qualifiers Qs, const DeclSpec *DS) {
1903  if (T.isNull())
1904  return QualType();
1905 
1906  // Ignore any attempt to form a cv-qualified reference.
1907  if (T->isReferenceType()) {
1908  Qs.removeConst();
1909  Qs.removeVolatile();
1910  }
1911 
1912  // Enforce C99 6.7.3p2: "Types other than pointer types derived from
1913  // object or incomplete types shall not be restrict-qualified."
1914  if (Qs.hasRestrict()) {
1915  unsigned DiagID = 0;
1916  QualType ProblemTy;
1917 
1918  if (T->isAnyPointerType() || T->isReferenceType() ||
1919  T->isMemberPointerType()) {
1920  QualType EltTy;
1921  if (T->isObjCObjectPointerType())
1922  EltTy = T;
1923  else if (const MemberPointerType *PTy = T->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
1924  EltTy = PTy->getPointeeType();
1925  else
1926  EltTy = T->getPointeeType();
1927 
1928  // If we have a pointer or reference, the pointee must have an object
1929  // incomplete type.
1930  if (!EltTy->isIncompleteOrObjectType()) {
1931  DiagID = diag::err_typecheck_invalid_restrict_invalid_pointee;
1932  ProblemTy = EltTy;
1933  }
1934  } else if (!isDependentOrGNUAutoType(T)) {
1935  // For an __auto_type variable, we may not have seen the initializer yet
1936  // and so have no idea whether the underlying type is a pointer type or
1937  // not.
1938  DiagID = diag::err_typecheck_invalid_restrict_not_pointer;
1939  ProblemTy = T;
1940  }
1941 
1942  if (DiagID) {
1943  Diag(DS ? DS->getRestrictSpecLoc() : Loc, DiagID) << ProblemTy;
1944  Qs.removeRestrict();
1945  }
1946  }
1947 
1948  return Context.getQualifiedType(T, Qs);
1949 }
1950 
1951 QualType Sema::BuildQualifiedType(QualType T, SourceLocation Loc,
1952  unsigned CVRAU, const DeclSpec *DS) {
1953  if (T.isNull())
1954  return QualType();
1955 
1956  // Ignore any attempt to form a cv-qualified reference.
1957  if (T->isReferenceType())
1958  CVRAU &=
1959  ~(DeclSpec::TQ_const | DeclSpec::TQ_volatile | DeclSpec::TQ_atomic);
1960 
1961  // Convert from DeclSpec::TQ to Qualifiers::TQ by just dropping TQ_atomic and
1962  // TQ_unaligned;
1963  unsigned CVR = CVRAU & ~(DeclSpec::TQ_atomic | DeclSpec::TQ_unaligned);
1964 
1965  // C11 6.7.3/5:
1966  // If the same qualifier appears more than once in the same
1967  // specifier-qualifier-list, either directly or via one or more typedefs,
1968  // the behavior is the same as if it appeared only once.
1969  //
1970  // It's not specified what happens when the _Atomic qualifier is applied to
1971  // a type specified with the _Atomic specifier, but we assume that this
1972  // should be treated as if the _Atomic qualifier appeared multiple times.
1973  if (CVRAU & DeclSpec::TQ_atomic && !T->isAtomicType()) {
1974  // C11 6.7.3/5:
1975  // If other qualifiers appear along with the _Atomic qualifier in a
1976  // specifier-qualifier-list, the resulting type is the so-qualified
1977  // atomic type.
1978  //
1979  // Don't need to worry about array types here, since _Atomic can't be
1980  // applied to such types.
1981  SplitQualType Split = T.getSplitUnqualifiedType();
1982  T = BuildAtomicType(QualType(Split.Ty, 0),
1983  DS ? DS->getAtomicSpecLoc() : Loc);
1984  if (T.isNull())
1985  return T;
1986  Split.Quals.addCVRQualifiers(CVR);
1987  return BuildQualifiedType(T, Loc, Split.Quals);
1988  }
1989 
1990  Qualifiers Q = Qualifiers::fromCVRMask(CVR);
1991  Q.setUnaligned(CVRAU & DeclSpec::TQ_unaligned);
1992  return BuildQualifiedType(T, Loc, Q, DS);
1993 }
1994 
1995 /// Build a paren type including \p T.
1996 QualType Sema::BuildParenType(QualType T) {
1997  return Context.getParenType(T);
1998 }
1999 
2000 /// Given that we're building a pointer or reference to the given
2001 static QualType inferARCLifetimeForPointee(Sema &S, QualType type,
2002  SourceLocation loc,
2003  bool isReference) {
2004  // Bail out if retention is unrequired or already specified.
2005  if (!type->isObjCLifetimeType() ||
2006  type.getObjCLifetime() != Qualifiers::OCL_None)
2007  return type;
2008 
2009  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime implicitLifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_None;
2010 
2011  // If the object type is const-qualified, we can safely use
2012  // __unsafe_unretained. This is safe (because there are no read
2013  // barriers), and it'll be safe to coerce anything but __weak* to
2014  // the resulting type.
2015  if (type.isConstQualified()) {
2016  implicitLifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone;
2017 
2018  // Otherwise, check whether the static type does not require
2019  // retaining. This currently only triggers for Class (possibly
2020  // protocol-qualifed, and arrays thereof).
2021  } else if (type->isObjCARCImplicitlyUnretainedType()) {
2022  implicitLifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone;
2023 
2024  // If we are in an unevaluated context, like sizeof, skip adding a
2025  // qualification.
2026  } else if (S.isUnevaluatedContext()) {
2027  return type;
2028 
2029  // If that failed, give an error and recover using __strong. __strong
2030  // is the option most likely to prevent spurious second-order diagnostics,
2031  // like when binding a reference to a field.
2032  } else {
2033  // These types can show up in private ivars in system headers, so
2034  // we need this to not be an error in those cases. Instead we
2035  // want to delay.
2036  if (S.DelayedDiagnostics.shouldDelayDiagnostics()) {
2037  S.DelayedDiagnostics.add(
2038  sema::DelayedDiagnostic::makeForbiddenType(loc,
2039  diag::err_arc_indirect_no_ownership, type, isReference));
2040  } else {
2041  S.Diag(loc, diag::err_arc_indirect_no_ownership) << type << isReference;
2042  }
2043  implicitLifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_Strong;
2044  }
2045  assert(implicitLifetime && "didn't infer any lifetime!");
2046 
2047  Qualifiers qs;
2048  qs.addObjCLifetime(implicitLifetime);
2049  return S.Context.getQualifiedType(type, qs);
2050 }
2051 
2052 static std::string getFunctionQualifiersAsString(const FunctionProtoType *FnTy){
2053  std::string Quals = FnTy->getMethodQuals().getAsString();
2054 
2055  switch (FnTy->getRefQualifier()) {
2056  case RQ_None:
2057  break;
2058 
2059  case RQ_LValue:
2060  if (!Quals.empty())
2061  Quals += ' ';
2062  Quals += '&';
2063  break;
2064 
2065  case RQ_RValue:
2066  if (!Quals.empty())
2067  Quals += ' ';
2068  Quals += "&&";
2069  break;
2070  }
2071 
2072  return Quals;
2073 }
2074 
2075 namespace {
2076 /// Kinds of declarator that cannot contain a qualified function type.
2077 ///
2078 /// C++98 [dcl.fct]p4 / C++11 [dcl.fct]p6:
2079 /// a function type with a cv-qualifier or a ref-qualifier can only appear
2080 /// at the topmost level of a type.
2081 ///
2082 /// Parens and member pointers are permitted. We don't diagnose array and
2083 /// function declarators, because they don't allow function types at all.
2084 ///
2085 /// The values of this enum are used in diagnostics.
2086 enum QualifiedFunctionKind { QFK_BlockPointer, QFK_Pointer, QFK_Reference };
2087 } // end anonymous namespace
2088 
2089 /// Check whether the type T is a qualified function type, and if it is,
2090 /// diagnose that it cannot be contained within the given kind of declarator.
2091 static bool checkQualifiedFunction(Sema &S, QualType T, SourceLocation Loc,
2092  QualifiedFunctionKind QFK) {
2093  // Does T refer to a function type with a cv-qualifier or a ref-qualifier?
2094  const FunctionProtoType *FPT = T->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2095  if (!FPT ||
2096  (FPT->getMethodQuals().empty() && FPT->getRefQualifier() == RQ_None))
2097  return false;
2098 
2099  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_compound_qualified_function_type)
2100  << QFK << isa<FunctionType>(T.IgnoreParens()) << T
2101  << getFunctionQualifiersAsString(FPT);
2102  return true;
2103 }
2104 
2105 bool Sema::CheckQualifiedFunctionForTypeId(QualType T, SourceLocation Loc) {
2106  const FunctionProtoType *FPT = T->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2107  if (!FPT ||
2108  (FPT->getMethodQuals().empty() && FPT->getRefQualifier() == RQ_None))
2109  return false;
2110 
2111  Diag(Loc, diag::err_qualified_function_typeid)
2112  << T << getFunctionQualifiersAsString(FPT);
2113  return true;
2114 }

2116 // Helper to deduce addr space of a pointee type in OpenCL mode.
2117 static QualType deduceOpenCLPointeeAddrSpace(Sema &S, QualType PointeeType) {
2118  if (!PointeeType->isUndeducedAutoType() && !PointeeType->isDependentType() &&
2119  !PointeeType->isSamplerT() &&
2120  !PointeeType.hasAddressSpace())
2121  PointeeType = S.getASTContext().getAddrSpaceQualType(
2122  PointeeType, S.getASTContext().getDefaultOpenCLPointeeAddrSpace());
2123  return PointeeType;
2124 }
