2126 /// Build a pointer type.
2127 ///
2128 /// \param T The type to which we'll be building a pointer.
2129 ///
2130 /// \param Loc The location of the entity whose type involves this
2131 /// pointer type or, if there is no such entity, the location of the
2132 /// type that will have pointer type.
2133 ///
2134 /// \param Entity The name of the entity that involves the pointer
2135 /// type, if known.
2136 ///
2137 /// \returns A suitable pointer type, if there are no
2138 /// errors. Otherwise, returns a NULL type.
2139 QualType Sema::BuildPointerType(QualType T,
2140  SourceLocation Loc, DeclarationName Entity) {
2141  if (T->isReferenceType()) {
2142  // C++ 8.3.2p4: There shall be no ... pointers to references ...
2143  Diag(Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_pointer_to_reference)
2144  << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity) << T;
2145  return QualType();
2146  }
2147 
2148  if (T->isFunctionType() && getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
2149  !getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption("__cl_clang_function_pointers",
2150  getLangOpts())) {
2151  Diag(Loc, diag::err_opencl_function_pointer) << /*pointer*/ 0;
2152  return QualType();
2153  }
2154 
2155  if (checkQualifiedFunction(*this, T, Loc, QFK_Pointer))
2156  return QualType();
2157 
2158  assert(!T->isObjCObjectType() && "Should build ObjCObjectPointerType");
2159 
2160  // In ARC, it is forbidden to build pointers to unqualified pointers.
2161  if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
2162  T = inferARCLifetimeForPointee(*this, T, Loc, /*reference*/ false);
2163 
2164  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL)
2165  T = deduceOpenCLPointeeAddrSpace(*this, T);
2166 
2167  // Build the pointer type.
2168  return Context.getPointerType(T);
2169 }
2170 
2171 /// Build a reference type.
2172 ///
2173 /// \param T The type to which we'll be building a reference.
2174 ///
2175 /// \param Loc The location of the entity whose type involves this
2176 /// reference type or, if there is no such entity, the location of the
2177 /// type that will have reference type.
2178 ///
2179 /// \param Entity The name of the entity that involves the reference
2180 /// type, if known.
2181 ///
2182 /// \returns A suitable reference type, if there are no
2183 /// errors. Otherwise, returns a NULL type.
2184 QualType Sema::BuildReferenceType(QualType T, bool SpelledAsLValue,
2185  SourceLocation Loc,
2186  DeclarationName Entity) {
2187  assert(Context.getCanonicalType(T) != Context.OverloadTy &&
2188  "Unresolved overloaded function type");
2189 
2190  // C++0x [dcl.ref]p6:
2191  // If a typedef (7.1.3), a type template-parameter (14.3.1), or a
2192  // decltype-specifier (7.1.6.2) denotes a type TR that is a reference to a
2193  // type T, an attempt to create the type "lvalue reference to cv TR" creates
2194  // the type "lvalue reference to T", while an attempt to create the type
2195  // "rvalue reference to cv TR" creates the type TR.
2196  bool LValueRef = SpelledAsLValue || T->getAs<LValueReferenceType>();
2197 
2198  // C++ [dcl.ref]p4: There shall be no references to references.
2199  //
2200  // According to C++ DR 106, references to references are only
2201  // diagnosed when they are written directly (e.g., "int & &"),
2202  // but not when they happen via a typedef:
2203  //
2204  // typedef int& intref;
2205  // typedef intref& intref2;
2206  //
2207  // Parser::ParseDeclaratorInternal diagnoses the case where
2208  // references are written directly; here, we handle the
2209  // collapsing of references-to-references as described in C++0x.
2210  // DR 106 and 540 introduce reference-collapsing into C++98/03.
2211 
2212  // C++ [dcl.ref]p1:
2213  // A declarator that specifies the type "reference to cv void"
2214  // is ill-formed.
2215  if (T->isVoidType()) {
2216  Diag(Loc, diag::err_reference_to_void);
2217  return QualType();
2218  }
2219 
2220  if (checkQualifiedFunction(*this, T, Loc, QFK_Reference))
2221  return QualType();
2222 
2223  if (T->isFunctionType() && getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
2224  !getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption("__cl_clang_function_pointers",
2225  getLangOpts())) {
2226  Diag(Loc, diag::err_opencl_function_pointer) << /*reference*/ 1;
2227  return QualType();
2228  }
2229 
2230  // In ARC, it is forbidden to build references to unqualified pointers.
2231  if (getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
2232  T = inferARCLifetimeForPointee(*this, T, Loc, /*reference*/ true);
2233 
2234  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL)
2235  T = deduceOpenCLPointeeAddrSpace(*this, T);
2236 
2237  // Handle restrict on references.
2238  if (LValueRef)
2239  return Context.getLValueReferenceType(T, SpelledAsLValue);
2240  return Context.getRValueReferenceType(T);
2241 }
2242

2267 /// Build a bit-precise integer type.
2268 ///
2269 /// \param IsUnsigned Boolean representing the signedness of the type.
2270 ///
2271 /// \param BitWidth Size of this int type in bits, or an expression representing
2272 /// that.
2273 ///
2274 /// \param Loc Location of the keyword.
2275 QualType Sema::BuildBitIntType(bool IsUnsigned, Expr *BitWidth,
2276  SourceLocation Loc) {
2277  if (BitWidth->isInstantiationDependent())
2278  return Context.getDependentBitIntType(IsUnsigned, BitWidth);
2279 
2280  llvm::APSInt Bits(32);
2281  ExprResult ICE =
2282  VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(BitWidth, &Bits, /*FIXME*/ AllowFold);
2283 
2284  if (ICE.isInvalid())
2285  return QualType();
2286 
2287  size_t NumBits = Bits.getZExtValue();
2288  if (!IsUnsigned && NumBits < 2) {
2289  Diag(Loc, diag::err_bit_int_bad_size) << 0;
2290  return QualType();
2291  }
2292 
2293  if (IsUnsigned && NumBits < 1) {
2294  Diag(Loc, diag::err_bit_int_bad_size) << 1;
2295  return QualType();
2296  }
2297 
2298  const TargetInfo &TI = getASTContext().getTargetInfo();
2299  if (NumBits > TI.getMaxBitIntWidth()) {
2300  Diag(Loc, diag::err_bit_int_max_size)
2301  << IsUnsigned << static_cast<uint64_t>(TI.getMaxBitIntWidth());
2302  return QualType();
2303  }
2304 
2305  return Context.getBitIntType(IsUnsigned, NumBits);
2306 }

2308 /// Check whether the specified array bound can be evaluated using the relevant
2309 /// language rules. If so, returns the possibly-converted expression and sets
2310 /// SizeVal to the size. If not, but the expression might be a VLA bound,
2311 /// returns ExprResult(). Otherwise, produces a diagnostic and returns
2312 /// ExprError().
2313 static ExprResult checkArraySize(Sema &S, Expr *&ArraySize,
2314  llvm::APSInt &SizeVal, unsigned VLADiag,
2315  bool VLAIsError) {
2316  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 &&
2317  (VLAIsError ||
2318  !ArraySize->getType()->isIntegralOrUnscopedEnumerationType())) {
2319  // C++14 [dcl.array]p1:
2320  // The constant-expression shall be a converted constant expression of
2321  // type std::size_t.
2322  //
2323  // Don't apply this rule if we might be forming a VLA: in that case, we
2324  // allow non-constant expressions and constant-folding. We only need to use
2325  // the converted constant expression rules (to properly convert the source)
2326  // when the source expression is of class type.
2327  return S.CheckConvertedConstantExpression(
2328  ArraySize, S.Context.getSizeType(), SizeVal, Sema::CCEK_ArrayBound);
2329  }
2330 
2331  // If the size is an ICE, it certainly isn't a VLA. If we're in a GNU mode
2332  // (like gnu99, but not c99) accept any evaluatable value as an extension.
2333  class VLADiagnoser : public Sema::VerifyICEDiagnoser {
2334  public:
2335  unsigned VLADiag;
2336  bool VLAIsError;
2337  bool IsVLA = false;
2338 
2339  VLADiagnoser(unsigned VLADiag, bool VLAIsError)
2340  : VLADiag(VLADiag), VLAIsError(VLAIsError) {}
2341 
2342  Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseNotICEType(Sema &S, SourceLocation Loc,
2343  QualType T) override {
2344  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_size_non_int) << T;
2345  }
2346 
2347  Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseNotICE(Sema &S,
2348  SourceLocation Loc) override {
2349  IsVLA = !VLAIsError;
2350  return S.Diag(Loc, VLADiag);
2351  }
2352 
2353  Sema::SemaDiagnosticBuilder diagnoseFold(Sema &S,
2354  SourceLocation Loc) override {
2355  return S.Diag(Loc, diag::ext_vla_folded_to_constant);
2356  }
2357  } Diagnoser(VLADiag, VLAIsError);
2358 
2359  ExprResult R =
2360  S.VerifyIntegerConstantExpression(ArraySize, &SizeVal, Diagnoser);
2361  if (Diagnoser.IsVLA)
2362  return ExprResult();
2363  return R;
2364 }
2365 
2366 /// Build an array type.
2367 ///
2368 /// \param T The type of each element in the array.
2369 ///
2370 /// \param ASM C99 array size modifier (e.g., '*', 'static').
2371 ///
2372 /// \param ArraySize Expression describing the size of the array.
2373 ///
2374 /// \param Brackets The range from the opening '[' to the closing ']'.
2375 ///
2376 /// \param Entity The name of the entity that involves the array
2377 /// type, if known.
2378 ///
2379 /// \returns A suitable array type, if there are no errors. Otherwise,
2380 /// returns a NULL type.
2381 QualType Sema::BuildArrayType(QualType T, ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
2382  Expr *ArraySize, unsigned Quals,
2383  SourceRange Brackets, DeclarationName Entity) {
2384 
2385  SourceLocation Loc = Brackets.getBegin();
2386  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
2387  // C++ [dcl.array]p1:
2388  // T is called the array element type; this type shall not be a reference
2389  // type, the (possibly cv-qualified) type void, a function type or an
2390  // abstract class type.
2391  //
2392  // C++ [dcl.array]p3:
2393  // When several "array of" specifications are adjacent, [...] only the
2394  // first of the constant expressions that specify the bounds of the arrays
2395  // may be omitted.
2396  //
2397  // Note: function types are handled in the common path with C.
2398  if (T->isReferenceType()) {
2399  Diag(Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_array_of_references)
2400  << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity) << T;
2401  return QualType();
2402  }
2403 
2404  if (T->isVoidType() || T->isIncompleteArrayType()) {
2405  Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_incomplete_or_sizeless_type) << 0 << T;
2406  return QualType();
2407  }
2408 
2409  if (RequireNonAbstractType(Brackets.getBegin(), T,
2410  diag::err_array_of_abstract_type))
2411  return QualType();
2412 
2413  // Mentioning a member pointer type for an array type causes us to lock in
2414  // an inheritance model, even if it's inside an unused typedef.
2415  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft())
2416  if (const MemberPointerType *MPTy = T->getAs<MemberPointerType>())
2417  if (!MPTy->getClass()->isDependentType())
2418  (void)isCompleteType(Loc, T);
2419 
2420  } else {
2421  // C99 6.7.5.2p1: If the element type is an incomplete or function type,
2422  // reject it (e.g. void ary[7], struct foo ary[7], void ary[7]())
2423  if (RequireCompleteSizedType(Loc, T,
2424  diag::err_array_incomplete_or_sizeless_type))
2425  return QualType();
2426  }
2427 
2428  if (T->isSizelessType()) {
2429  Diag(Loc, diag::err_array_incomplete_or_sizeless_type) << 1 << T;
2430  return QualType();
2431  }
2432 
2433  if (T->isFunctionType()) {
2434  Diag(Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_array_of_functions)
2435  << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity) << T;
2436  return QualType();
2437  }
2438 
2439  if (const RecordType *EltTy = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
2440  // If the element type is a struct or union that contains a variadic
2441  // array, accept it as a GNU extension: C99 6.7.2.1p2.
2442  if (EltTy->getDecl()->hasFlexibleArrayMember())
2443  Diag(Loc, diag::ext_flexible_array_in_array) << T;
2444  } else if (T->isObjCObjectType()) {
2445  Diag(Loc, diag::err_objc_array_of_interfaces) << T;
2446  return QualType();
2447  }
2448 
2449  // Do placeholder conversions on the array size expression.
2450  if (ArraySize && ArraySize->hasPlaceholderType()) {
2451  ExprResult Result = CheckPlaceholderExpr(ArraySize);
2452  if (Result.isInvalid()) return QualType();
2453  ArraySize = Result.get();
2454  }
2455 
2456  // Do lvalue-to-rvalue conversions on the array size expression.
2457  if (ArraySize && !ArraySize->isPRValue()) {
2458  ExprResult Result = DefaultLvalueConversion(ArraySize);
2459  if (Result.isInvalid())
2460  return QualType();
2461 
2462  ArraySize = Result.get();
2463  }
2464 
2465  // C99 6.7.5.2p1: The size expression shall have integer type.
2466  // C++11 allows contextual conversions to such types.
2467  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 &&
2468  ArraySize && !ArraySize->isTypeDependent() &&
2469  !ArraySize->getType()->isIntegralOrUnscopedEnumerationType()) {
2470  Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_array_size_non_int)
2471  << ArraySize->getType() << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2472  return QualType();
2473  }
2474 
2475  // VLAs always produce at least a -Wvla diagnostic, sometimes an error.
2476  unsigned VLADiag;
2477  bool VLAIsError;
2478  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
2479  // OpenCL v1.2 s6.9.d: variable length arrays are not supported.
2480  VLADiag = diag::err_opencl_vla;
2481  VLAIsError = true;
2482  } else if (getLangOpts().C99) {
2483  VLADiag = diag::warn_vla_used;
2484  VLAIsError = false;
2485  } else if (isSFINAEContext()) {
2486  VLADiag = diag::err_vla_in_sfinae;
2487  VLAIsError = true;
2488  } else if (getLangOpts().OpenMP && isInOpenMPTaskUntiedContext()) {
2489  VLADiag = diag::err_openmp_vla_in_task_untied;
2490  VLAIsError = true;
2491  } else {
2492  VLADiag = diag::ext_vla;
2493  VLAIsError = false;
2494  }
2495 
2496  llvm::APSInt ConstVal(Context.getTypeSize(Context.getSizeType()));
2497  if (!ArraySize) {
2498  if (ASM == ArrayType::Star) {
2499  Diag(Loc, VLADiag);
2500  if (VLAIsError)
2501  return QualType();
2502 
2503  T = Context.getVariableArrayType(T, nullptr, ASM, Quals, Brackets);
2504  } else {
2505  T = Context.getIncompleteArrayType(T, ASM, Quals);
2506  }
2507  } else if (ArraySize->isTypeDependent() || ArraySize->isValueDependent()) {
2508  T = Context.getDependentSizedArrayType(T, ArraySize, ASM, Quals, Brackets);
2509  } else {
2510  ExprResult R =
2511  checkArraySize(*this, ArraySize, ConstVal, VLADiag, VLAIsError);
2512  if (R.isInvalid())
2513  return QualType();
2514 
2515  if (!R.isUsable()) {
2516  // C99: an array with a non-ICE size is a VLA. We accept any expression
2517  // that we can fold to a non-zero positive value as a non-VLA as an
2518  // extension.
2519  T = Context.getVariableArrayType(T, ArraySize, ASM, Quals, Brackets);
2520  } else if (!T->isDependentType() && !T->isIncompleteType() &&
2521  !T->isConstantSizeType()) {
2522  // C99: an array with an element type that has a non-constant-size is a
2523  // VLA.
2524  // FIXME: Add a note to explain why this isn't a VLA.
2525  Diag(Loc, VLADiag);
2526  if (VLAIsError)
2527  return QualType();
2528  T = Context.getVariableArrayType(T, ArraySize, ASM, Quals, Brackets);
2529  } else {
2530  // C99 6.7.5.2p1: If the expression is a constant expression, it shall
2531  // have a value greater than zero.
2532  // In C++, this follows from narrowing conversions being disallowed.
2533  if (ConstVal.isSigned() && ConstVal.isNegative()) {
2534  if (Entity)
2535  Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_decl_negative_array_size)
2536  << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity)
2537  << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2538  else
2539  Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(),
2540  diag::err_typecheck_negative_array_size)
2541  << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2542  return QualType();
2543  }
2544  if (ConstVal == 0) {
2545  // GCC accepts zero sized static arrays. We allow them when
2546  // we're not in a SFINAE context.
2547  Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(),
2548  isSFINAEContext() ? diag::err_typecheck_zero_array_size
2549  : diag::ext_typecheck_zero_array_size)
2550  << 0 << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2551  }
2552 
2553  // Is the array too large?
2554  unsigned ActiveSizeBits =
2555  (!T->isDependentType() && !T->isVariablyModifiedType() &&
2556  !T->isIncompleteType() && !T->isUndeducedType())
2557  ? ConstantArrayType::getNumAddressingBits(Context, T, ConstVal)
2558  : ConstVal.getActiveBits();
2559  if (ActiveSizeBits > ConstantArrayType::getMaxSizeBits(Context)) {
2560  Diag(ArraySize->getBeginLoc(), diag::err_array_too_large)
2561  << toString(ConstVal, 10) << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2562  return QualType();
2563  }
2564 
2565  T = Context.getConstantArrayType(T, ConstVal, ArraySize, ASM, Quals);
2566  }
2567  }
2568 
2569  // Delay diagnostic to SemaSYCL so only Kernel functions are diagnosed.
2570  if (T->isVariableArrayType() && !Context.getTargetInfo().isVLASupported() &&
2571  !getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
2572  // CUDA device code and some other targets don't support VLAs.
2573  targetDiag(Loc, (getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
2574  ? diag::err_cuda_vla
2575  : diag::err_vla_unsupported)
2576  << ((getLangOpts().CUDA && getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice)
2577  ? CurrentCUDATarget()
2578  : CFT_InvalidTarget);
2579  }
2580 
2581  // If this is not C99, diagnose array size modifiers on non-VLAs.
2582  if (!getLangOpts().C99 && !T->isVariableArrayType() &&
2583  (ASM != ArrayType::Normal || Quals != 0)) {
2584  Diag(Loc, getLangOpts().CPlusPlus ? diag::err_c99_array_usage_cxx
2585  : diag::ext_c99_array_usage)
2586  << ASM;
2587  }
2588 
2589  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.12.5 - Arrays of blocks are not supported.
2590  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.16.13.1 - Arrays of pipe type are not supported.
2591  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.9.b - Arrays of image/sampler type are not supported.
2592  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
2593  const QualType ArrType = Context.getBaseElementType(T);
2594  if (ArrType->isBlockPointerType() || ArrType->isPipeType() ||
2595  ArrType->isSamplerT() || ArrType->isImageType()) {
2596  Diag(Loc, diag::err_opencl_invalid_type_array) << ArrType;
2597  return QualType();
2598  }
2599  }
2600 
2601  return T;
2602 }
2603 
2604 QualType Sema::BuildVectorType(QualType CurType, Expr *SizeExpr,
2605  SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
2606  // The base type must be integer (not Boolean or enumeration) or float, and
2607  // can't already be a vector.
2608  if ((!CurType->isDependentType() &&
2609  (!CurType->isBuiltinType() || CurType->isBooleanType() ||
2610  (!CurType->isIntegerType() && !CurType->isRealFloatingType()))) ||
2611  CurType->isArrayType()) {
2612  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_invalid_vector_type) << CurType;
2613  return QualType();
2614  }
2615 
2616  if (SizeExpr->isTypeDependent() || SizeExpr->isValueDependent())
2617  return Context.getDependentVectorType(CurType, SizeExpr, AttrLoc,
2618  VectorType::GenericVector);
2619 
2620  Optional<llvm::APSInt> VecSize = SizeExpr->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
2621  if (!VecSize) {
2622  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
2623  << "vector_size" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
2624  << SizeExpr->getSourceRange();
2625  return QualType();
2626  }
2627 
2628  if (CurType->isDependentType())
2629  return Context.getDependentVectorType(CurType, SizeExpr, AttrLoc,
2630  VectorType::GenericVector);
2631 
2632  // vecSize is specified in bytes - convert to bits.
2633  if (!VecSize->isIntN(61)) {
2634  // Bit size will overflow uint64.
2635  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_size_too_large)
2636  << SizeExpr->getSourceRange() << "vector";
2637  return QualType();
2638  }
2639  uint64_t VectorSizeBits = VecSize->getZExtValue() * 8;
2640  unsigned TypeSize = static_cast<unsigned>(Context.getTypeSize(CurType));
2641 
2642  if (VectorSizeBits == 0) {
2643  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_zero_size)
2644  << SizeExpr->getSourceRange() << "vector";
2645  return QualType();
2646  }
2647 
2648  if (VectorSizeBits % TypeSize) {
2649  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_invalid_size)
2650  << SizeExpr->getSourceRange();
2651  return QualType();
2652  }
2653 
2654  if (VectorSizeBits / TypeSize > std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
2655  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_size_too_large)
2656  << SizeExpr->getSourceRange() << "vector";
2657  return QualType();
2658  }
2659 
2660  return Context.getVectorType(CurType, VectorSizeBits / TypeSize,
2661  VectorType::GenericVector);
2662 }
2663 
2664 /// Build an ext-vector type.
2665 ///
2666 /// Run the required checks for the extended vector type.
2667 QualType Sema::BuildExtVectorType(QualType T, Expr *ArraySize,
2668  SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
2669  // Unlike gcc's vector_size attribute, we do not allow vectors to be defined
2670  // in conjunction with complex types (pointers, arrays, functions, etc.).
2671  //
2672  // Additionally, OpenCL prohibits vectors of booleans (they're considered a
2673  // reserved data type under OpenCL v2.0 s6.1.4), we don't support selects
2674  // on bitvectors, and we have no well-defined ABI for bitvectors, so vectors
2675  // of bool aren't allowed.
2676  //
2677  // We explictly allow bool elements in ext_vector_type for C/C++.
2678  bool IsNoBoolVecLang = getLangOpts().OpenCL || getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus;
2679  if ((!T->isDependentType() && !T->isIntegerType() &&
2680  !T->isRealFloatingType()) ||
2681  (IsNoBoolVecLang && T->isBooleanType())) {
2682  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_invalid_vector_type) << T;
2683  return QualType();
2684  }
2685 
2686  if (!ArraySize->isTypeDependent() && !ArraySize->isValueDependent()) {
2687  Optional<llvm::APSInt> vecSize = ArraySize->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
2688  if (!vecSize) {
2689  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
2690  << "ext_vector_type" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
2691  << ArraySize->getSourceRange();
2692  return QualType();
2693  }
2694 
2695  if (!vecSize->isIntN(32)) {
2696  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_size_too_large)
2697  << ArraySize->getSourceRange() << "vector";
2698  return QualType();
2699  }
2700  // Unlike gcc's vector_size attribute, the size is specified as the
2701  // number of elements, not the number of bytes.
2702  unsigned vectorSize = static_cast<unsigned>(vecSize->getZExtValue());
2703 
2704  if (vectorSize == 0) {
2705  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_zero_size)
2706  << ArraySize->getSourceRange() << "vector";
2707  return QualType();
2708  }
2709 
2710  return Context.getExtVectorType(T, vectorSize);
2711  }
2712 
2713  return Context.getDependentSizedExtVectorType(T, ArraySize, AttrLoc);
2714 }
2715 
2716 QualType Sema::BuildMatrixType(QualType ElementTy, Expr *NumRows, Expr *NumCols,
2717  SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
2718  assert(Context.getLangOpts().MatrixTypes &&
2719  "Should never build a matrix type when it is disabled");
2720 
2721  // Check element type, if it is not dependent.
2722  if (!ElementTy->isDependentType() &&
2723  !MatrixType::isValidElementType(ElementTy)) {
2724  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_invalid_matrix_type) << ElementTy;
2725  return QualType();
2726  }
2727 
2728  if (NumRows->isTypeDependent() || NumCols->isTypeDependent() ||
2729  NumRows->isValueDependent() || NumCols->isValueDependent())
2730  return Context.getDependentSizedMatrixType(ElementTy, NumRows, NumCols,
2731  AttrLoc);
2732 
2733  Optional<llvm::APSInt> ValueRows = NumRows->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
2734  Optional<llvm::APSInt> ValueColumns =
2735  NumCols->getIntegerConstantExpr(Context);
2736 
2737  auto const RowRange = NumRows->getSourceRange();
2738  auto const ColRange = NumCols->getSourceRange();
2739 
2740  // Both are row and column expressions are invalid.
2741  if (!ValueRows && !ValueColumns) {
2742  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
2743  << "matrix_type" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << RowRange
2744  << ColRange;
2745  return QualType();
2746  }
2747 
2748  // Only the row expression is invalid.
2749  if (!ValueRows) {
2750  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
2751  << "matrix_type" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << RowRange;
2752  return QualType();
2753  }
2754 
2755  // Only the column expression is invalid.
2756  if (!ValueColumns) {
2757  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
2758  << "matrix_type" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << ColRange;
2759  return QualType();
2760  }
2761 
2762  // Check the matrix dimensions.
2763  unsigned MatrixRows = static_cast<unsigned>(ValueRows->getZExtValue());
2764  unsigned MatrixColumns = static_cast<unsigned>(ValueColumns->getZExtValue());
2765  if (MatrixRows == 0 && MatrixColumns == 0) {
2766  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_zero_size)
2767  << "matrix" << RowRange << ColRange;
2768  return QualType();
2769  }
2770  if (MatrixRows == 0) {
2771  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_zero_size) << "matrix" << RowRange;
2772  return QualType();
2773  }
2774  if (MatrixColumns == 0) {
2775  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_zero_size) << "matrix" << ColRange;
2776  return QualType();
2777  }
2778  if (!ConstantMatrixType::isDimensionValid(MatrixRows)) {
2779  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_size_too_large)
2780  << RowRange << "matrix row";
2781  return QualType();
2782  }
2783  if (!ConstantMatrixType::isDimensionValid(MatrixColumns)) {
2784  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_size_too_large)
2785  << ColRange << "matrix column";
2786  return QualType();
2787  }
2788  return Context.getConstantMatrixType(ElementTy, MatrixRows, MatrixColumns);
2789 }
2790 
2791 bool Sema::CheckFunctionReturnType(QualType T, SourceLocation Loc) {
2792  if (T->isArrayType() || T->isFunctionType()) {
2793  Diag(Loc, diag::err_func_returning_array_function)
2794  << T->isFunctionType() << T;
2795  return true;
2796  }
2797 
2798  // Functions cannot return half FP.
2799  if (T->isHalfType() && !getLangOpts().HalfArgsAndReturns) {
2800  Diag(Loc, diag::err_parameters_retval_cannot_have_fp16_type) << 1 <<
2801  FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Loc, "*");
2802  return true;
2803  }
2804 
2805  // Methods cannot return interface types. All ObjC objects are
2806  // passed by reference.
2807  if (T->isObjCObjectType()) {
2808  Diag(Loc, diag::err_object_cannot_be_passed_returned_by_value)
2809  << 0 << T << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Loc, "*");
2810  return true;
2811  }
2812 
2813  if (T.hasNonTrivialToPrimitiveDestructCUnion() ||
2814  T.hasNonTrivialToPrimitiveCopyCUnion())
2815  checkNonTrivialCUnion(T, Loc, NTCUC_FunctionReturn,
2816  NTCUK_Destruct|NTCUK_Copy);
2817 
2818  // C++2a [dcl.fct]p12:
2819  // A volatile-qualified return type is deprecated
2820  if (T.isVolatileQualified() && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)
2821  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_deprecated_volatile_return) << T;
2822 
2823  return false;
2824 }
2825 
2826 /// Check the extended parameter information. Most of the necessary
2827 /// checking should occur when applying the parameter attribute; the
2828 /// only other checks required are positional restrictions.
2829 static void checkExtParameterInfos(Sema &S, ArrayRef<QualType> paramTypes,
2830  const FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo &EPI,
2831  llvm::function_ref<SourceLocation(unsigned)> getParamLoc) {
2832  assert(EPI.ExtParameterInfos && "shouldn't get here without param infos");
2833 
2834  bool emittedError = false;
2835  auto actualCC = EPI.ExtInfo.getCC();
2836  enum class RequiredCC { OnlySwift, SwiftOrSwiftAsync };
2837  auto checkCompatible = [&](unsigned paramIndex, RequiredCC required) {
2838  bool isCompatible =
2839  (required == RequiredCC::OnlySwift)
2840  ? (actualCC == CC_Swift)
2841  : (actualCC == CC_Swift || actualCC == CC_SwiftAsync);
2842  if (isCompatible || emittedError)
2843  return;
2844  S.Diag(getParamLoc(paramIndex), diag::err_swift_param_attr_not_swiftcall)
2845  << getParameterABISpelling(EPI.ExtParameterInfos[paramIndex].getABI())
2846  << (required == RequiredCC::OnlySwift);
2847  emittedError = true;
2848  };
2849  for (size_t paramIndex = 0, numParams = paramTypes.size();
2850  paramIndex != numParams; ++paramIndex) {
2851  switch (EPI.ExtParameterInfos[paramIndex].getABI()) {
2852  // Nothing interesting to check for orindary-ABI parameters.
2853  case ParameterABI::Ordinary:
2854  continue;
2855 
2856  // swift_indirect_result parameters must be a prefix of the function
2857  // arguments.
2858  case ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult:
2859  checkCompatible(paramIndex, RequiredCC::SwiftOrSwiftAsync);
2860  if (paramIndex != 0 &&
2861  EPI.ExtParameterInfos[paramIndex - 1].getABI()
2862  != ParameterABI::SwiftIndirectResult) {
2863  S.Diag(getParamLoc(paramIndex),
2864  diag::err_swift_indirect_result_not_first);
2865  }
2866  continue;
2867 
2868  case ParameterABI::SwiftContext:
2869  checkCompatible(paramIndex, RequiredCC::SwiftOrSwiftAsync);
2870  continue;
2871 
2872  // SwiftAsyncContext is not limited to swiftasynccall functions.
2873  case ParameterABI::SwiftAsyncContext:
2874  continue;
2875 
2876  // swift_error parameters must be preceded by a swift_context parameter.
2877  case ParameterABI::SwiftErrorResult:
2878  checkCompatible(paramIndex, RequiredCC::OnlySwift);
2879  if (paramIndex == 0 ||
2880  EPI.ExtParameterInfos[paramIndex - 1].getABI() !=
2881  ParameterABI::SwiftContext) {
2882  S.Diag(getParamLoc(paramIndex),
2883  diag::err_swift_error_result_not_after_swift_context);
2884  }
2885  continue;
2886  }
2887  llvm_unreachable("bad ABI kind");
2888  }
2889 }
2890 
2891 QualType Sema::BuildFunctionType(QualType T,
2892  MutableArrayRef<QualType> ParamTypes,
2893  SourceLocation Loc, DeclarationName Entity,
2894  const FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo &EPI) {
2895  bool Invalid = false;
2896 
2897  Invalid |= CheckFunctionReturnType(T, Loc);
2898 
2899  for (unsigned Idx = 0, Cnt = ParamTypes.size(); Idx < Cnt; ++Idx) {
2900  // FIXME: Loc is too inprecise here, should use proper locations for args.
2901  QualType ParamType = Context.getAdjustedParameterType(ParamTypes[Idx]);
2902  if (ParamType->isVoidType()) {
2903  Diag(Loc, diag::err_param_with_void_type);
2904  Invalid = true;
2905  } else if (ParamType->isHalfType() && !getLangOpts().HalfArgsAndReturns) {
2906  // Disallow half FP arguments.
2907  Diag(Loc, diag::err_parameters_retval_cannot_have_fp16_type) << 0 <<
2908  FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Loc, "*");
2909  Invalid = true;
2910  }
2911 
2912  // C++2a [dcl.fct]p4:
2913  // A parameter with volatile-qualified type is deprecated
2914  if (ParamType.isVolatileQualified() && getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)
2915  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_deprecated_volatile_param) << ParamType;
2916 
2917  ParamTypes[Idx] = ParamType;
2918  }
2919 
2920  if (EPI.ExtParameterInfos) {
2921  checkExtParameterInfos(*this, ParamTypes, EPI,
2922  [=](unsigned i) { return Loc; });
2923  }
2924 
2925  if (EPI.ExtInfo.getProducesResult()) {
2926  // This is just a warning, so we can't fail to build if we see it.
2927  checkNSReturnsRetainedReturnType(Loc, T);
2928  }
2929 
2930  if (Invalid)
2931  return QualType();
2932 
2933  return Context.getFunctionType(T, ParamTypes, EPI);
2934 }
2935 
2936 /// Build a member pointer type \c T Class::*.
2937 ///
2938 /// \param T the type to which the member pointer refers.
2939 /// \param Class the class type into which the member pointer points.
2940 /// \param Loc the location where this type begins
2941 /// \param Entity the name of the entity that will have this member pointer type
2942 ///
2943 /// \returns a member pointer type, if successful, or a NULL type if there was
2944 /// an error.
2945 QualType Sema::BuildMemberPointerType(QualType T, QualType Class,
2946  SourceLocation Loc,
2947  DeclarationName Entity) {
2948  // Verify that we're not building a pointer to pointer to function with
2949  // exception specification.
2950  if (CheckDistantExceptionSpec(T)) {
2951  Diag(Loc, diag::err_distant_exception_spec);
2952  return QualType();
2953  }
2954 
2955  // C++ 8.3.3p3: A pointer to member shall not point to ... a member
2956  // with reference type, or "cv void."
2957  if (T->isReferenceType()) {
2958  Diag(Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_mempointer_to_reference)
2959  << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity) << T;
2960  return QualType();
2961  }
2962 
2963  if (T->isVoidType()) {
2964  Diag(Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_mempointer_to_void)
2965  << getPrintableNameForEntity(Entity);
2966  return QualType();
2967  }
2968 
2969  if (!Class->isDependentType() && !Class->isRecordType()) {
2970  Diag(Loc, diag::err_mempointer_in_nonclass_type) << Class;
2971  return QualType();
2972  }
2973 
2974  if (T->isFunctionType() && getLangOpts().OpenCL &&
2975  !getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption("__cl_clang_function_pointers",
2976  getLangOpts())) {
2977  Diag(Loc, diag::err_opencl_function_pointer) << /*pointer*/ 0;
2978  return QualType();
2979  }
2980 
2981  // Adjust the default free function calling convention to the default method
2982  // calling convention.
2983  bool IsCtorOrDtor =
2984  (Entity.getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXConstructorName) ||
2985  (Entity.getNameKind() == DeclarationName::CXXDestructorName);
2986  if (T->isFunctionType())
2987  adjustMemberFunctionCC(T, /*IsStatic=*/false, IsCtorOrDtor, Loc);
2988 
2989  return Context.getMemberPointerType(T, Class.getTypePtr());
2990 }
2991 
2992 /// Build a block pointer type.
2993 ///
2994 /// \param T The type to which we'll be building a block pointer.
2995 ///
2996 /// \param Loc The source location, used for diagnostics.
2997 ///
2998 /// \param Entity The name of the entity that involves the block pointer
2999 /// type, if known.
3000 ///
3001 /// \returns A suitable block pointer type, if there are no
3002 /// errors. Otherwise, returns a NULL type.
3003 QualType Sema::BuildBlockPointerType(QualType T,
3004  SourceLocation Loc,
3005  DeclarationName Entity) {
3006  if (!T->isFunctionType()) {
3007  Diag(Loc, diag::err_nonfunction_block_type);
3008  return QualType();
3009  }
3010 
3011  if (checkQualifiedFunction(*this, T, Loc, QFK_BlockPointer))
3012  return QualType();
3013 
3014  if (getLangOpts().OpenCL)
3015  T = deduceOpenCLPointeeAddrSpace(*this, T);
3016 
3017  return Context.getBlockPointerType(T);
3018 }

3020 QualType Sema::GetTypeFromParser(ParsedType Ty, TypeSourceInfo **TInfo) {
3021  QualType QT = Ty.get();
3022  if (QT.isNull()) {
3023  if (TInfo) *TInfo = nullptr;
3024  return QualType();
3025  }
3026 
3027  TypeSourceInfo *DI = nullptr;
3028  if (const LocInfoType *LIT = dyn_cast<LocInfoType>(QT)) {
3029  QT = LIT->getType();
3030  DI = LIT->getTypeSourceInfo();
3031  }
3032 
3033  if (TInfo) *TInfo = DI;
3034  return QT;
3035 }

3037 static void transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(TypeProcessingState &state,
3038  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership,
3039  unsigned chunkIndex);
3040 
3041 /// Given that this is the declaration of a parameter under ARC,
3042 /// attempt to infer attributes and such for pointer-to-whatever
3043 /// types.
3044 static void inferARCWriteback(TypeProcessingState &state,
3045  QualType &declSpecType) {
3046  Sema &S = state.getSema();
3047  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
3048 
3049  // TODO: should we care about decl qualifiers?
3050 
3051  // Check whether the declarator has the expected form. We walk
3052  // from the inside out in order to make the block logic work.
3053  unsigned outermostPointerIndex = 0;
3054  bool isBlockPointer = false;
3055  unsigned numPointers = 0;
3056  for (unsigned i = 0, e = declarator.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
3057  unsigned chunkIndex = i;
3058  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(chunkIndex);
3059  switch (chunk.Kind) {
3060  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
3061  // Ignore parens.
3062  break;
3063 
3064  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
3065  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
3066  // Count the number of pointers. Treat references
3067  // interchangeably as pointers; if they're mis-ordered, normal
3068  // type building will discover that.
3069  outermostPointerIndex = chunkIndex;
3070  numPointers++;
3071  break;
3072 
3073  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
3074  // If we have a pointer to block pointer, that's an acceptable
3075  // indirect reference; anything else is not an application of
3076  // the rules.
3077  if (numPointers != 1) return;
3078  numPointers++;
3079  outermostPointerIndex = chunkIndex;
3080  isBlockPointer = true;
3081 
3082  // We don't care about pointer structure in return values here.
3083  goto done;
3084 
3085  case DeclaratorChunk::Array: // suppress if written (id[])?
3086  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
3087  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
3088  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
3089  return;
3090  }
3091  }
3092  done:
3093 
3094  // If we have *one* pointer, then we want to throw the qualifier on
3095  // the declaration-specifiers, which means that it needs to be a
3096  // retainable object type.
3097  if (numPointers == 1) {
3098  // If it's not a retainable object type, the rule doesn't apply.
3099  if (!declSpecType->isObjCRetainableType()) return;
3100 
3101  // If it already has lifetime, don't do anything.
3102  if (declSpecType.getObjCLifetime()) return;
3103 
3104  // Otherwise, modify the type in-place.
3105  Qualifiers qs;
3106 
3107  if (declSpecType->isObjCARCImplicitlyUnretainedType())
3108  qs.addObjCLifetime(Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone);
3109  else
3110  qs.addObjCLifetime(Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing);
3111  declSpecType = S.Context.getQualifiedType(declSpecType, qs);
3112 
3113  // If we have *two* pointers, then we want to throw the qualifier on
3114  // the outermost pointer.
3115  } else if (numPointers == 2) {
3116  // If we don't have a block pointer, we need to check whether the
3117  // declaration-specifiers gave us something that will turn into a
3118  // retainable object pointer after we slap the first pointer on it.
3119  if (!isBlockPointer && !declSpecType->isObjCObjectType())
3120  return;
3121 
3122  // Look for an explicit lifetime attribute there.
3123  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(outermostPointerIndex);
3124  if (chunk.Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Pointer &&
3125  chunk.Kind != DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer)
3126  return;
3127  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : chunk.getAttrs())
3128  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership)
3129  return;
3130 
3131  transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(state, Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing,
3132  outermostPointerIndex);
3133 
3134  // Any other number of pointers/references does not trigger the rule.
3135  } else return;
3136 
3137  // TODO: mark whether we did this inference?
3138 }
3139 
3140 void Sema::diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(unsigned DiagID, unsigned Quals,
3141  SourceLocation FallbackLoc,
3142  SourceLocation ConstQualLoc,
3143  SourceLocation VolatileQualLoc,
3144  SourceLocation RestrictQualLoc,
3145  SourceLocation AtomicQualLoc,
3146  SourceLocation UnalignedQualLoc) {
3147  if (!Quals)
3148  return;
3149 
3150  struct Qual {
3151  const char *Name;
3152  unsigned Mask;
3153  SourceLocation Loc;
3154  } const QualKinds[5] = {
3155  { "const", DeclSpec::TQ_const, ConstQualLoc },
3156  { "volatile", DeclSpec::TQ_volatile, VolatileQualLoc },
3157  { "restrict", DeclSpec::TQ_restrict, RestrictQualLoc },
3158  { "__unaligned", DeclSpec::TQ_unaligned, UnalignedQualLoc },
3159  { "_Atomic", DeclSpec::TQ_atomic, AtomicQualLoc }
3160  };
3161 
3162  SmallString<32> QualStr;
3163  unsigned NumQuals = 0;
3164  SourceLocation Loc;
3165  FixItHint FixIts[5];
3166 
3167  // Build a string naming the redundant qualifiers.
3168  for (auto &E : QualKinds) {
3169  if (Quals & E.Mask) {
3170  if (!QualStr.empty()) QualStr += ' ';
3171  QualStr += E.Name;
3172 
3173  // If we have a location for the qualifier, offer a fixit.
3174  SourceLocation QualLoc = E.Loc;
3175  if (QualLoc.isValid()) {
3176  FixIts[NumQuals] = FixItHint::CreateRemoval(QualLoc);
3177  if (Loc.isInvalid() ||
3178  getSourceManager().isBeforeInTranslationUnit(QualLoc, Loc))
3179  Loc = QualLoc;
3180  }
3181 
3182  ++NumQuals;
3183  }
3184  }
3185 
3186  Diag(Loc.isInvalid() ? FallbackLoc : Loc, DiagID)
3187  << QualStr << NumQuals << FixIts[0] << FixIts[1] << FixIts[2] << FixIts[3];
3188 }

3190 // Diagnose pointless type qualifiers on the return type of a function.
3191 static void diagnoseRedundantReturnTypeQualifiers(Sema &S, QualType RetTy,
3192  Declarator &D,
3193  unsigned FunctionChunkIndex) {
3194  const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI =
3195  D.getTypeObject(FunctionChunkIndex).Fun;
3196  if (FTI.hasTrailingReturnType()) {
3197  S.diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(diag::warn_qual_return_type,
3198  RetTy.getLocalCVRQualifiers(),
3199  FTI.getTrailingReturnTypeLoc());
3200  return;
3201  }
3202 
3203  for (unsigned OuterChunkIndex = FunctionChunkIndex + 1,
3204  End = D.getNumTypeObjects();
3205  OuterChunkIndex != End; ++OuterChunkIndex) {
3206  DeclaratorChunk &OuterChunk = D.getTypeObject(OuterChunkIndex);
3207  switch (OuterChunk.Kind) {
3208  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
3209  continue;
3210 
3211  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer: {
3212  DeclaratorChunk::PointerTypeInfo &PTI = OuterChunk.Ptr;
3213  S.diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(
3214  diag::warn_qual_return_type,
3215  PTI.TypeQuals,
3216  SourceLocation(),
3217  PTI.ConstQualLoc,
3218  PTI.VolatileQualLoc,
3219  PTI.RestrictQualLoc,
3220  PTI.AtomicQualLoc,
3221  PTI.UnalignedQualLoc);
3222  return;
3223  }
3224 
3225  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
3226  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
3227  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
3228  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
3229  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
3230  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
3231  // FIXME: We can't currently provide an accurate source location and a
3232  // fix-it hint for these.
3233  unsigned AtomicQual = RetTy->isAtomicType() ? DeclSpec::TQ_atomic : 0;
3234  S.diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(diag::warn_qual_return_type,
3235  RetTy.getCVRQualifiers() | AtomicQual,
3236  D.getIdentifierLoc());
3237  return;
3238  }
3239 
3240  llvm_unreachable("unknown declarator chunk kind");
3241  }
3242 
3243  // If the qualifiers come from a conversion function type, don't diagnose
3244  // them -- they're not necessarily redundant, since such a conversion
3245  // operator can be explicitly called as "x.operator const int()".
3246  if (D.getName().getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConversionFunctionId)
3247  return;
3248 
3249  // Just parens all the way out to the decl specifiers. Diagnose any qualifiers
3250  // which are present there.
3251  S.diagnoseIgnoredQualifiers(diag::warn_qual_return_type,
3252  D.getDeclSpec().getTypeQualifiers(),
3253  D.getIdentifierLoc(),
3254  D.getDeclSpec().getConstSpecLoc(),
3255  D.getDeclSpec().getVolatileSpecLoc(),
3256  D.getDeclSpec().getRestrictSpecLoc(),
3257  D.getDeclSpec().getAtomicSpecLoc(),
3258  D.getDeclSpec().getUnalignedSpecLoc());
3259 }

3261 static std::pair<QualType, TypeSourceInfo *>
3262 InventTemplateParameter(TypeProcessingState &state, QualType T,
3263  TypeSourceInfo *TrailingTSI, AutoType *Auto,
3264  InventedTemplateParameterInfo &Info) {
3265  Sema &S = state.getSema();
3266  Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
3267 
3268  const unsigned TemplateParameterDepth = Info.AutoTemplateParameterDepth;
3269  const unsigned AutoParameterPosition = Info.TemplateParams.size();
3270  const bool IsParameterPack = D.hasEllipsis();
3271 
3272  // If auto is mentioned in a lambda parameter or abbreviated function
3273  // template context, convert it to a template parameter type.
3274 
3275  // Create the TemplateTypeParmDecl here to retrieve the corresponding
3276  // template parameter type. Template parameters are temporarily added
3277  // to the TU until the associated TemplateDecl is created.
3278  TemplateTypeParmDecl *InventedTemplateParam =
3279  TemplateTypeParmDecl::Create(
3280  S.Context, S.Context.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
3281  /*KeyLoc=*/D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
3282  /*NameLoc=*/D.getIdentifierLoc(),
3283  TemplateParameterDepth, AutoParameterPosition,
3284  S.InventAbbreviatedTemplateParameterTypeName(
3285  D.getIdentifier(), AutoParameterPosition), false,
3286  IsParameterPack, /*HasTypeConstraint=*/Auto->isConstrained());
3287  InventedTemplateParam->setImplicit();
3288  Info.TemplateParams.push_back(InventedTemplateParam);
3289 
3290  // Attach type constraints to the new parameter.
3291  if (Auto->isConstrained()) {
3292  if (TrailingTSI) {
3293  // The 'auto' appears in a trailing return type we've already built;
3294  // extract its type constraints to attach to the template parameter.
3295  AutoTypeLoc AutoLoc = TrailingTSI->getTypeLoc().getContainedAutoTypeLoc();
3296  TemplateArgumentListInfo TAL(AutoLoc.getLAngleLoc(), AutoLoc.getRAngleLoc());
3297  bool Invalid = false;
3298  for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < AutoLoc.getNumArgs(); ++Idx) {
3299  if (D.getEllipsisLoc().isInvalid() && !Invalid &&
3300  S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(AutoLoc.getArgLoc(Idx),
3301  Sema::UPPC_TypeConstraint))
3302  Invalid = true;
3303  TAL.addArgument(AutoLoc.getArgLoc(Idx));
3304  }
3305 
3306  if (!Invalid) {
3307  S.AttachTypeConstraint(
3308  AutoLoc.getNestedNameSpecifierLoc(), AutoLoc.getConceptNameInfo(),
3309  AutoLoc.getNamedConcept(),
3310  AutoLoc.hasExplicitTemplateArgs() ? &TAL : nullptr,
3311  InventedTemplateParam, D.getEllipsisLoc());
3312  }
3313  } else {
3314  // The 'auto' appears in the decl-specifiers; we've not finished forming
3315  // TypeSourceInfo for it yet.
3316  TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = D.getDeclSpec().getRepAsTemplateId();
3317  TemplateArgumentListInfo TemplateArgsInfo;
3318  bool Invalid = false;
3319  if (TemplateId->LAngleLoc.isValid()) {
3320  ASTTemplateArgsPtr TemplateArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
3321  TemplateId->NumArgs);
3322  S.translateTemplateArguments(TemplateArgsPtr, TemplateArgsInfo);
3323 
3324  if (D.getEllipsisLoc().isInvalid()) {
3325  for (TemplateArgumentLoc Arg : TemplateArgsInfo.arguments()) {
3326  if (S.DiagnoseUnexpandedParameterPack(Arg,
3327  Sema::UPPC_TypeConstraint)) {
3328  Invalid = true;
3329  break;
3330  }
3331  }
3332  }
3333  }
3334  if (!Invalid) {
3335  S.AttachTypeConstraint(
3336  D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecScope().getWithLocInContext(S.Context),
3337  DeclarationNameInfo(DeclarationName(TemplateId->Name),
3338  TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc),
3339  cast<ConceptDecl>(TemplateId->Template.get().getAsTemplateDecl()),
3340  TemplateId->LAngleLoc.isValid() ? &TemplateArgsInfo : nullptr,
3341  InventedTemplateParam, D.getEllipsisLoc());
3342  }
3343  }
3344  }
3345 
3346  // Replace the 'auto' in the function parameter with this invented
3347  // template type parameter.
3348  // FIXME: Retain some type sugar to indicate that this was written
3349  // as 'auto'?
3350  QualType Replacement(InventedTemplateParam->getTypeForDecl(), 0);
3351  QualType NewT = state.ReplaceAutoType(T, Replacement);
3352  TypeSourceInfo *NewTSI =
3353  TrailingTSI ? S.ReplaceAutoTypeSourceInfo(TrailingTSI, Replacement)
3354  : nullptr;
3355  return {NewT, NewTSI};
3356 }

3358 static TypeSourceInfo *
3359 GetTypeSourceInfoForDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &State,
3360  QualType T, TypeSourceInfo *ReturnTypeInfo);
3361 
3362 static QualType GetDeclSpecTypeForDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &state,
3363  TypeSourceInfo *&ReturnTypeInfo) {
3364  Sema &SemaRef = state.getSema();
3365  Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
3366  QualType T;
3367  ReturnTypeInfo = nullptr;
3368 
3369  // The TagDecl owned by the DeclSpec.
3370  TagDecl *OwnedTagDecl = nullptr;
3371 
3372  switch (D.getName().getKind()) {
3373  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ImplicitSelfParam:
3374  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_OperatorFunctionId:
3375  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_Identifier:
3376  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_LiteralOperatorId:
3377  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_TemplateId:
3378  T = ConvertDeclSpecToType(state);
3379 
3380  if (!D.isInvalidType() && D.getDeclSpec().isTypeSpecOwned()) {
3381  OwnedTagDecl = cast<TagDecl>(D.getDeclSpec().getRepAsDecl());
3382  // Owned declaration is embedded in declarator.
3383  OwnedTagDecl->setEmbeddedInDeclarator(true);
3384  }
3385  break;
3386 
3387  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConstructorName:
3388  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConstructorTemplateId:
3389  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_DestructorName:
3390  // Constructors and destructors don't have return types. Use
3391  // "void" instead.
3392  T = SemaRef.Context.VoidTy;
3393  processTypeAttrs(state, T, TAL_DeclSpec,
3394  D.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes());
3395  break;
3396 
3397  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_DeductionGuideName:
3398  // Deduction guides have a trailing return type and no type in their
3399  // decl-specifier sequence. Use a placeholder return type for now.
3400  T = SemaRef.Context.DependentTy;
3401  break;
3402 
3403  case UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConversionFunctionId:
3404  // The result type of a conversion function is the type that it
3405  // converts to.
3406  T = SemaRef.GetTypeFromParser(D.getName().ConversionFunctionId,
3407  &ReturnTypeInfo);
3408  break;
3409  }
3410 
3411  if (!D.getAttributes().empty())
3412  distributeTypeAttrsFromDeclarator(state, T);
3413 
3414  // Find the deduced type in this type. Look in the trailing return type if we
3415  // have one, otherwise in the DeclSpec type.
3416  // FIXME: The standard wording doesn't currently describe this.
3417  DeducedType *Deduced = T->getContainedDeducedType();
3418  bool DeducedIsTrailingReturnType = false;
3419  if (Deduced && isa<AutoType>(Deduced) && D.hasTrailingReturnType()) {
3420  QualType T = SemaRef.GetTypeFromParser(D.getTrailingReturnType());
3421  Deduced = T.isNull() ? nullptr : T->getContainedDeducedType();
3422  DeducedIsTrailingReturnType = true;
3423  }
3424 
3425  // C++11 [dcl.spec.auto]p5: reject 'auto' if it is not in an allowed context.
3426  if (Deduced) {
3427  AutoType *Auto = dyn_cast<AutoType>(Deduced);
3428  int Error = -1;
3429 
3430  // Is this a 'auto' or 'decltype(auto)' type (as opposed to __auto_type or
3431  // class template argument deduction)?
3432  bool IsCXXAutoType =
3433  (Auto && Auto->getKeyword() != AutoTypeKeyword::GNUAutoType);
3434  bool IsDeducedReturnType = false;
3435 
3436  switch (D.getContext()) {
3437  case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr:
3438  // Declared return type of a lambda-declarator is implicit and is always
3439  // 'auto'.
3440  break;
3441  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameter:
3442  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCResult:
3443  Error = 0;
3444  break;
3445  case DeclaratorContext::RequiresExpr:
3446  Error = 22;
3447  break;
3448  case DeclaratorContext::Prototype:
3449  case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameter: {
3450  InventedTemplateParameterInfo *Info = nullptr;
3451  if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::Prototype) {
3452  // With concepts we allow 'auto' in function parameters.
3453  if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 || !Auto ||
3454  Auto->getKeyword() != AutoTypeKeyword::Auto) {
3455  Error = 0;
3456  break;
3457  } else if (!SemaRef.getCurScope()->isFunctionDeclarationScope()) {
3458  Error = 21;
3459  break;
3460  }
3461 
3462  Info = &SemaRef.InventedParameterInfos.back();
3463  } else {
3464  // In C++14, generic lambdas allow 'auto' in their parameters.
3465  if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 || !Auto ||
3466  Auto->getKeyword() != AutoTypeKeyword::Auto) {
3467  Error = 16;
3468  break;
3469  }
3470  Info = SemaRef.getCurLambda();
3471  assert(Info && "No LambdaScopeInfo on the stack!");
3472  }
3473 
3474  // We'll deal with inventing template parameters for 'auto' in trailing
3475  // return types when we pick up the trailing return type when processing
3476  // the function chunk.
3477  if (!DeducedIsTrailingReturnType)
3478  T = InventTemplateParameter(state, T, nullptr, Auto, *Info).first;
3479  break;
3480  }
3481  case DeclaratorContext::Member: {
3482  if (D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_static ||
3483  D.isFunctionDeclarator())
3484  break;
3485  bool Cxx = SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
3486  if (isa<ObjCContainerDecl>(SemaRef.CurContext)) {
3487  Error = 6; // Interface member.
3488  } else {
3489  switch (cast<TagDecl>(SemaRef.CurContext)->getTagKind()) {
3490  case TTK_Enum: llvm_unreachable("unhandled tag kind");
3491  case TTK_Struct: Error = Cxx ? 1 : 2; /* Struct member */ break;
3492  case TTK_Union: Error = Cxx ? 3 : 4; /* Union member */ break;
3493  case TTK_Class: Error = 5; /* Class member */ break;
3494  case TTK_Interface: Error = 6; /* Interface member */ break;
3495  }
3496  }
3497  if (D.getDeclSpec().isFriendSpecified())
3498  Error = 20; // Friend type
3499  break;
3500  }
3501  case DeclaratorContext::CXXCatch:
3502  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCCatch:
3503  Error = 7; // Exception declaration
3504  break;
3505  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateParam:
3506  if (isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced) &&
3507  !SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)
3508  Error = 19; // Template parameter (until C++20)
3509  else if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17)
3510  Error = 8; // Template parameter (until C++17)
3511  break;
3512  case DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteral:
3513  Error = 9; // Block literal
3514  break;
3515  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateArg:
3516  // Within a template argument list, a deduced template specialization
3517  // type will be reinterpreted as a template template argument.
3518  if (isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced) &&
3519  !D.getNumTypeObjects() &&
3520  D.getDeclSpec().getParsedSpecifiers() == DeclSpec::PQ_TypeSpecifier)
3521  break;
3522  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3523  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArg:
3524  Error = 10; // Template type argument
3525  break;
3526  case DeclaratorContext::AliasDecl:
3527  case DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplate:
3528  Error = 12; // Type alias
3529  break;
3530  case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturn:
3531  case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVar:
3532  if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 || !IsCXXAutoType)
3533  Error = 13; // Function return type
3534  IsDeducedReturnType = true;
3535  break;
3536  case DeclaratorContext::ConversionId:
3537  if (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14 || !IsCXXAutoType)
3538  Error = 14; // conversion-type-id
3539  IsDeducedReturnType = true;
3540  break;
3541  case DeclaratorContext::FunctionalCast:
3542  if (isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced))
3543  break;
3544  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus2b && IsCXXAutoType &&
3545  !Auto->isDecltypeAuto())
3546  break; // auto(x)
3547  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3548  case DeclaratorContext::TypeName:
3549  Error = 15; // Generic
3550  break;
3551  case DeclaratorContext::File:
3552  case DeclaratorContext::Block:
3553  case DeclaratorContext::ForInit:
3554  case DeclaratorContext::SelectionInit:
3555  case DeclaratorContext::Condition:
3556  // FIXME: P0091R3 (erroneously) does not permit class template argument
3557  // deduction in conditions, for-init-statements, and other declarations
3558  // that are not simple-declarations.
3559  break;
3560  case DeclaratorContext::CXXNew:
3561  // FIXME: P0091R3 does not permit class template argument deduction here,
3562  // but we follow GCC and allow it anyway.
3563  if (!IsCXXAutoType && !isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced))
3564  Error = 17; // 'new' type
3565  break;
3566  case DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeList:
3567  Error = 18; // K&R function parameter
3568  break;
3569  }
3570 
3571  if (D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_typedef)
3572  Error = 11;
3573 
3574  // In Objective-C it is an error to use 'auto' on a function declarator
3575  // (and everywhere for '__auto_type').
3576  if (D.isFunctionDeclarator() &&
3577  (!SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 || !IsCXXAutoType))
3578  Error = 13;
3579 
3580  SourceRange AutoRange = D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc();
3581  if (D.getName().getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConversionFunctionId)
3582  AutoRange = D.getName().getSourceRange();
3583 
3584  if (Error != -1) {
3585  unsigned Kind;
3586  if (Auto) {
3587  switch (Auto->getKeyword()) {
3588  case AutoTypeKeyword::Auto: Kind = 0; break;
3589  case AutoTypeKeyword::DecltypeAuto: Kind = 1; break;
3590  case AutoTypeKeyword::GNUAutoType: Kind = 2; break;
3591  }
3592  } else {
3593  assert(isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced) &&
3594  "unknown auto type");
3595  Kind = 3;
3596  }
3597 
3598  auto *DTST = dyn_cast<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(Deduced);
3599  TemplateName TN = DTST ? DTST->getTemplateName() : TemplateName();
3600 
3601  SemaRef.Diag(AutoRange.getBegin(), diag::err_auto_not_allowed)
3602  << Kind << Error << (int)SemaRef.getTemplateNameKindForDiagnostics(TN)
3603  << QualType(Deduced, 0) << AutoRange;
3604  if (auto *TD = TN.getAsTemplateDecl())
3605  SemaRef.Diag(TD->getLocation(), diag::note_template_decl_here);
3606 
3607  T = SemaRef.Context.IntTy;
3608  D.setInvalidType(true);
3609  } else if (Auto && D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr) {
3610  // If there was a trailing return type, we already got
3611  // warn_cxx98_compat_trailing_return_type in the parser.
3612  SemaRef.Diag(AutoRange.getBegin(),
3613  D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameter
3614  ? diag::warn_cxx11_compat_generic_lambda
3615  : IsDeducedReturnType
3616  ? diag::warn_cxx11_compat_deduced_return_type
3617  : diag::warn_cxx98_compat_auto_type_specifier)
3618  << AutoRange;
3619  }
3620  }
3621 
3622  if (SemaRef.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
3623  OwnedTagDecl && OwnedTagDecl->isCompleteDefinition()) {
3624  // Check the contexts where C++ forbids the declaration of a new class
3625  // or enumeration in a type-specifier-seq.
3626  unsigned DiagID = 0;
3627  switch (D.getContext()) {
3628  case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturn:
3629  case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVar:
3630  // Class and enumeration definitions are syntactically not allowed in
3631  // trailing return types.
3632  llvm_unreachable("parser should not have allowed this");
3633  break;
3634  case DeclaratorContext::File:
3635  case DeclaratorContext::Member:
3636  case DeclaratorContext::Block:
3637  case DeclaratorContext::ForInit:
3638  case DeclaratorContext::SelectionInit:
3639  case DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteral:
3640  case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr:
3641  // C++11 [dcl.type]p3:
3642  // A type-specifier-seq shall not define a class or enumeration unless
3643  // it appears in the type-id of an alias-declaration (7.1.3) that is not
3644  // the declaration of a template-declaration.
3645  case DeclaratorContext::AliasDecl:
3646  break;
3647  case DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplate:
3648  DiagID = diag::err_type_defined_in_alias_template;
3649  break;
3650  case DeclaratorContext::TypeName:
3651  case DeclaratorContext::FunctionalCast:
3652  case DeclaratorContext::ConversionId:
3653  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateParam:
3654  case DeclaratorContext::CXXNew:
3655  case DeclaratorContext::CXXCatch:
3656  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCCatch:
3657  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateArg:
3658  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArg:
3659  DiagID = diag::err_type_defined_in_type_specifier;
3660  break;
3661  case DeclaratorContext::Prototype:
3662  case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameter:
3663  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameter:
3664  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCResult:
3665  case DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeList:
3666  case DeclaratorContext::RequiresExpr:
3667  // C++ [dcl.fct]p6:
3668  // Types shall not be defined in return or parameter types.
3669  DiagID = diag::err_type_defined_in_param_type;
3670  break;
3671  case DeclaratorContext::Condition:
3672  // C++ 6.4p2:
3673  // The type-specifier-seq shall not contain typedef and shall not declare
3674  // a new class or enumeration.
3675  DiagID = diag::err_type_defined_in_condition;
3676  break;
3677  }
3678 
3679  if (DiagID != 0) {
3680  SemaRef.Diag(OwnedTagDecl->getLocation(), DiagID)
3681  << SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(OwnedTagDecl);
3682  D.setInvalidType(true);
3683  }
3684  }
3685 
3686  assert(!T.isNull() && "This function should not return a null type");
3687  return T;
3688 }
3689 
3690 /// Produce an appropriate diagnostic for an ambiguity between a function
3691 /// declarator and a C++ direct-initializer.
3692 static void warnAboutAmbiguousFunction(Sema &S, Declarator &D,
3693  DeclaratorChunk &DeclType, QualType RT) {
3694  const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI = DeclType.Fun;
3695  assert(FTI.isAmbiguous && "no direct-initializer / function ambiguity");
3696 
3697  // If the return type is void there is no ambiguity.
3698  if (RT->isVoidType())
3699  return;
3700 
3701  // An initializer for a non-class type can have at most one argument.
3702  if (!RT->isRecordType() && FTI.NumParams > 1)
3703  return;
3704 
3705  // An initializer for a reference must have exactly one argument.
3706  if (RT->isReferenceType() && FTI.NumParams != 1)
3707  return;
3708 
3709  // Only warn if this declarator is declaring a function at block scope, and
3710  // doesn't have a storage class (such as 'extern') specified.
3711  if (!D.isFunctionDeclarator() ||
3712  D.getFunctionDefinitionKind() != FunctionDefinitionKind::Declaration ||
3713  !S.CurContext->isFunctionOrMethod() ||
3714  D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() != DeclSpec::SCS_unspecified)
3715  return;
3716 
3717  // Inside a condition, a direct initializer is not permitted. We allow one to
3718  // be parsed in order to give better diagnostics in condition parsing.
3719  if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::Condition)
3720  return;
3721 
3722  SourceRange ParenRange(DeclType.Loc, DeclType.EndLoc);
3723 
3724  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc,
3725  FTI.NumParams ? diag::warn_parens_disambiguated_as_function_declaration
3726  : diag::warn_empty_parens_are_function_decl)
3727  << ParenRange;
3728 
3729  // If the declaration looks like:
3730  // T var1,
3731  // f();
3732  // and name lookup finds a function named 'f', then the ',' was
3733  // probably intended to be a ';'.
3734  if (!D.isFirstDeclarator() && D.getIdentifier()) {
3735  FullSourceLoc Comma(D.getCommaLoc(), S.SourceMgr);
3736  FullSourceLoc Name(D.getIdentifierLoc(), S.SourceMgr);
3737  if (Comma.getFileID() != Name.getFileID() ||
3738  Comma.getSpellingLineNumber() != Name.getSpellingLineNumber()) {
3739  LookupResult Result(S, D.getIdentifier(), SourceLocation(),
3740  Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
3741  if (S.LookupName(Result, S.getCurScope()))
3742  S.Diag(D.getCommaLoc(), diag::note_empty_parens_function_call)
3743  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(D.getCommaLoc(), ";")
3744  << D.getIdentifier();
3745  Result.suppressDiagnostics();
3746  }
3747  }
3748 
3749  if (FTI.NumParams > 0) {
3750  // For a declaration with parameters, eg. "T var(T());", suggest adding
3751  // parens around the first parameter to turn the declaration into a
3752  // variable declaration.
3753  SourceRange Range = FTI.Params[0].Param->getSourceRange();
3754  SourceLocation B = Range.getBegin();
3755  SourceLocation E = S.getLocForEndOfToken(Range.getEnd());
3756  // FIXME: Maybe we should suggest adding braces instead of parens
3757  // in C++11 for classes that don't have an initializer_list constructor.
3758  S.Diag(B, diag::note_additional_parens_for_variable_declaration)
3759  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(B, "(")
3760  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(E, ")");
3761  } else {
3762  // For a declaration without parameters, eg. "T var();", suggest replacing
3763  // the parens with an initializer to turn the declaration into a variable
3764  // declaration.
3765  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = RT->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3766 
3767  // Empty parens mean value-initialization, and no parens mean
3768  // default initialization. These are equivalent if the default
3769  // constructor is user-provided or if zero-initialization is a
3770  // no-op.
3771  if (RD && RD->hasDefinition() &&
3772  (RD->isEmpty() || RD->hasUserProvidedDefaultConstructor()))
3773  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::note_empty_parens_default_ctor)
3774  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(ParenRange);
3775  else {
3776  std::string Init =
3777  S.getFixItZeroInitializerForType(RT, ParenRange.getBegin());
3778  if (Init.empty() && S.LangOpts.CPlusPlus11)
3779  Init = "{}";
3780  if (!Init.empty())
3781  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::note_empty_parens_zero_initialize)
3782  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(ParenRange, Init);
3783  }
3784  }
3785 }
3786 
3787 /// Produce an appropriate diagnostic for a declarator with top-level
3788 /// parentheses.
3789 static void warnAboutRedundantParens(Sema &S, Declarator &D, QualType T) {
3790  DeclaratorChunk &Paren = D.getTypeObject(D.getNumTypeObjects() - 1);
3791  assert(Paren.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Paren &&
3792  "do not have redundant top-level parentheses");
3793 
3794  // This is a syntactic check; we're not interested in cases that arise
3795  // during template instantiation.
3796  if (S.inTemplateInstantiation())
3797  return;
3798 
3799  // Check whether this could be intended to be a construction of a temporary
3800  // object in C++ via a function-style cast.
3801  bool CouldBeTemporaryObject =
3802  S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && D.isExpressionContext() &&
3803  !D.isInvalidType() && D.getIdentifier() &&
3804  D.getDeclSpec().getParsedSpecifiers() == DeclSpec::PQ_TypeSpecifier &&
3805  (T->isRecordType() || T->isDependentType()) &&
3806  D.getDeclSpec().getTypeQualifiers() == 0 && D.isFirstDeclarator();
3807 
3808  bool StartsWithDeclaratorId = true;
3809  for (auto &C : D.type_objects()) {
3810  switch (C.Kind) {
3811  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
3812  if (&C == &Paren)
3813  continue;
3814  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3815  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
3816  StartsWithDeclaratorId = false;
3817  continue;
3818 
3819  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
3820  if (!C.Arr.NumElts)
3821  CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3822  continue;
3823 
3824  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
3825  // FIXME: Suppress the warning here if there is no initializer; we're
3826  // going to give an error anyway.
3827  // We assume that something like 'T (&x) = y;' is highly likely to not
3828  // be intended to be a temporary object.
3829  CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3830  StartsWithDeclaratorId = false;
3831  continue;
3832 
3833  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
3834  // In a new-type-id, function chunks require parentheses.
3835  if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::CXXNew)
3836  return;
3837  // FIXME: "A(f())" deserves a vexing-parse warning, not just a
3838  // redundant-parens warning, but we don't know whether the function
3839  // chunk was syntactically valid as an expression here.
3840  CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3841  continue;
3842 
3843  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
3844  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
3845  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
3846  // These cannot appear in expressions.
3847  CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3848  StartsWithDeclaratorId = false;
3849  continue;
3850  }
3851  }
3852 
3853  // FIXME: If there is an initializer, assume that this is not intended to be
3854  // a construction of a temporary object.
3855 
3856  // Check whether the name has already been declared; if not, this is not a
3857  // function-style cast.
3858  if (CouldBeTemporaryObject) {
3859  LookupResult Result(S, D.getIdentifier(), SourceLocation(),
3860  Sema::LookupOrdinaryName);
3861  if (!S.LookupName(Result, S.getCurScope()))
3862  CouldBeTemporaryObject = false;
3863  Result.suppressDiagnostics();
3864  }
3865 
3866  SourceRange ParenRange(Paren.Loc, Paren.EndLoc);
3867 
3868  if (!CouldBeTemporaryObject) {
3869  // If we have A (::B), the parentheses affect the meaning of the program.
3870  // Suppress the warning in that case. Don't bother looking at the DeclSpec
3871  // here: even (e.g.) "int ::x" is visually ambiguous even though it's
3872  // formally unambiguous.
3873  if (StartsWithDeclaratorId && D.getCXXScopeSpec().isValid()) {
3874  for (NestedNameSpecifier *NNS = D.getCXXScopeSpec().getScopeRep(); NNS;
3875  NNS = NNS->getPrefix()) {
3876  if (NNS->getKind() == NestedNameSpecifier::Global)
3877  return;
3878  }
3879  }
3880 
3881  S.Diag(Paren.Loc, diag::warn_redundant_parens_around_declarator)
3882  << ParenRange << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Paren.Loc)
3883  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Paren.EndLoc);
3884  return;
3885  }
3886 
3887  S.Diag(Paren.Loc, diag::warn_parens_disambiguated_as_variable_declaration)
3888  << ParenRange << D.getIdentifier();
3889  auto *RD = T->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
3890  if (!RD || !RD->hasDefinition() || RD->hasNonTrivialDestructor())
3891  S.Diag(Paren.Loc, diag::note_raii_guard_add_name)
3892  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(Paren.Loc, " varname") << T
3893  << D.getIdentifier();
3894  // FIXME: A cast to void is probably a better suggestion in cases where it's
3895  // valid (when there is no initializer and we're not in a condition).
3896  S.Diag(D.getBeginLoc(), diag::note_function_style_cast_add_parentheses)
3897  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(D.getBeginLoc(), "(")
3898  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(S.getLocForEndOfToken(D.getEndLoc()), ")");
3899  S.Diag(Paren.Loc, diag::note_remove_parens_for_variable_declaration)
3900  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Paren.Loc)
3901  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(Paren.EndLoc);
3902 }
3903 
3904 /// Helper for figuring out the default CC for a function declarator type. If
3905 /// this is the outermost chunk, then we can determine the CC from the
3906 /// declarator context. If not, then this could be either a member function
3907 /// type or normal function type.
3908 static CallingConv getCCForDeclaratorChunk(
3909  Sema &S, Declarator &D, const ParsedAttributesView &AttrList,
3910  const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI, unsigned ChunkIndex) {
3911  assert(D.getTypeObject(ChunkIndex).Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Function);
3912 
3913  // Check for an explicit CC attribute.
3914  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : AttrList) {
3915  switch (AL.getKind()) {
3916  CALLING_CONV_ATTRS_CASELIST : {
3917  // Ignore attributes that don't validate or can't apply to the
3918  // function type. We'll diagnose the failure to apply them in
3919  // handleFunctionTypeAttr.
3920  CallingConv CC;
3921  if (!S.CheckCallingConvAttr(AL, CC) &&
3922  (!FTI.isVariadic || supportsVariadicCall(CC))) {
3923  return CC;
3924  }
3925  break;
3926  }
3927 
3928  default:
3929  break;
3930  }
3931  }
3932 
3933  bool IsCXXInstanceMethod = false;
3934 
3935  if (S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
3936  // Look inwards through parentheses to see if this chunk will form a
3937  // member pointer type or if we're the declarator. Any type attributes
3938  // between here and there will override the CC we choose here.
3939  unsigned I = ChunkIndex;
3940  bool FoundNonParen = false;
3941  while (I && !FoundNonParen) {
3942  --I;
3943  if (D.getTypeObject(I).Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Paren)
3944  FoundNonParen = true;
3945  }
3946 
3947  if (FoundNonParen) {
3948  // If we're not the declarator, we're a regular function type unless we're
3949  // in a member pointer.
3950  IsCXXInstanceMethod =
3951  D.getTypeObject(I).Kind == DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer;
3952  } else if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr) {
3953  // This can only be a call operator for a lambda, which is an instance
3954  // method.
3955  IsCXXInstanceMethod = true;
3956  } else {
3957  // We're the innermost decl chunk, so must be a function declarator.
3958  assert(D.isFunctionDeclarator());
3959 
3960  // If we're inside a record, we're declaring a method, but it could be
3961  // explicitly or implicitly static.
3962  IsCXXInstanceMethod =
3963  D.isFirstDeclarationOfMember() &&
3964  D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() != DeclSpec::SCS_typedef &&
3965  !D.isStaticMember();
3966  }
3967  }
3968 
3969  CallingConv CC = S.Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(FTI.isVariadic,
3970  IsCXXInstanceMethod);
3971 
3972  // Attribute AT_OpenCLKernel affects the calling convention for SPIR
3973  // and AMDGPU targets, hence it cannot be treated as a calling
3974  // convention attribute. This is the simplest place to infer
3975  // calling convention for OpenCL kernels.
3976  if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
3977  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes()) {
3978  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLKernel) {
3979  CC = CC_OpenCLKernel;
3980  break;
3981  }
3982  }
3983  } else if (S.getLangOpts().CUDA) {
3984  // If we're compiling CUDA/HIP code and targeting SPIR-V we need to make
3985  // sure the kernels will be marked with the right calling convention so that
3986  // they will be visible by the APIs that ingest SPIR-V.
3987  llvm::Triple Triple = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
3988  if (Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::spirv32 ||
3989  Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::spirv64) {
3990  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes()) {
3991  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_CUDAGlobal) {
3992  CC = CC_OpenCLKernel;
3993  break;
3994  }
3995  }
3996  }
3997  }
3998 
3999  return CC;
4000 }

4002 namespace {
4003  /// A simple notion of pointer kinds, which matches up with the various
4004  /// pointer declarators.
4005  enum class SimplePointerKind {
4006  Pointer,
4007  BlockPointer,
4008  MemberPointer,
4009  Array,
4010  };

4013 IdentifierInfo *Sema::getNullabilityKeyword(NullabilityKind nullability) {
4014  switch (nullability) {
4015  case NullabilityKind::NonNull:
4016  if (!Ident__Nonnull)
4017  Ident__Nonnull = PP.getIdentifierInfo("_Nonnull");
4018  return Ident__Nonnull;
4019 
4020  case NullabilityKind::Nullable:
4021  if (!Ident__Nullable)
4022  Ident__Nullable = PP.getIdentifierInfo("_Nullable");
4023  return Ident__Nullable;
4024 
4025  case NullabilityKind::NullableResult:
4026  if (!Ident__Nullable_result)
4027  Ident__Nullable_result = PP.getIdentifierInfo("_Nullable_result");
4028  return Ident__Nullable_result;
4029 
4030  case NullabilityKind::Unspecified:
4031  if (!Ident__Null_unspecified)
4032  Ident__Null_unspecified = PP.getIdentifierInfo("_Null_unspecified");
4033  return Ident__Null_unspecified;
4034  }
4035  llvm_unreachable("Unknown nullability kind.");
4036 }

4046 /// Check whether there is a nullability attribute of any kind in the given
4047 /// attribute list.
4048 static bool hasNullabilityAttr(const ParsedAttributesView &attrs) {
4049  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : attrs) {
4050  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNonNull ||
4051  AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullable ||
4052  AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullableResult ||
4053  AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullUnspecified)
4054  return true;
4055  }
4056 
4057  return false;
4058 }

4060 namespace {
4061  /// Describes the kind of a pointer a declarator describes.
4062  enum class PointerDeclaratorKind {
4063  // Not a pointer.
4064  NonPointer,
4065  // Single-level pointer.
4066  SingleLevelPointer,
4067  // Multi-level pointer (of any pointer kind).
4068  MultiLevelPointer,
4069  // CFFooRef*
4070  MaybePointerToCFRef,
4071  // CFErrorRef*
4072  CFErrorRefPointer,
4073  // NSError**
4074  NSErrorPointerPointer,
4075  };

4077  /// Describes a declarator chunk wrapping a pointer that marks inference as
4078  /// unexpected.
4079  // These values must be kept in sync with diagnostics.
4080  enum class PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind {
4081  /// Pointer is top-level.
4082  None = -1,
4083  /// Pointer is an array element.
4084  Array = 0,
4085  /// Pointer is the referent type of a C++ reference.
4086  Reference = 1
4087  };
