4089 
4090 /// Classify the given declarator, whose type-specified is \c type, based on
4091 /// what kind of pointer it refers to.
4092 ///
4093 /// This is used to determine the default nullability.
4094 static PointerDeclaratorKind
4095 classifyPointerDeclarator(Sema &S, QualType type, Declarator &declarator,
4096  PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind &wrappingKind) {
4097  unsigned numNormalPointers = 0;
4098 
4099  // For any dependent type, we consider it a non-pointer.
4100  if (type->isDependentType())
4101  return PointerDeclaratorKind::NonPointer;
4102 
4103  // Look through the declarator chunks to identify pointers.
4104  for (unsigned i = 0, n = declarator.getNumTypeObjects(); i != n; ++i) {
4105  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i);
4106  switch (chunk.Kind) {
4107  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
4108  if (numNormalPointers == 0)
4109  wrappingKind = PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::Array;
4110  break;
4111 
4112  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
4113  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
4114  break;
4115 
4116  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
4117  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
4118  return numNormalPointers > 0 ? PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer
4119  : PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer;
4120 
4121  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
4122  break;
4123 
4124  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
4125  if (numNormalPointers == 0)
4126  wrappingKind = PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::Reference;
4127  break;
4128 
4129  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
4130  ++numNormalPointers;
4131  if (numNormalPointers > 2)
4132  return PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer;
4133  break;
4134  }
4135  }
4136 
4137  // Then, dig into the type specifier itself.
4138  unsigned numTypeSpecifierPointers = 0;
4139  do {
4140  // Decompose normal pointers.
4141  if (auto ptrType = type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
4142  ++numNormalPointers;
4143 
4144  if (numNormalPointers > 2)
4145  return PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer;
4146 
4147  type = ptrType->getPointeeType();
4148  ++numTypeSpecifierPointers;
4149  continue;
4150  }
4151 
4152  // Decompose block pointers.
4153  if (type->getAs<BlockPointerType>()) {
4154  return numNormalPointers > 0 ? PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer
4155  : PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer;
4156  }
4157 
4158  // Decompose member pointers.
4159  if (type->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
4160  return numNormalPointers > 0 ? PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer
4161  : PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer;
4162  }
4163 
4164  // Look at Objective-C object pointers.
4165  if (auto objcObjectPtr = type->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
4166  ++numNormalPointers;
4167  ++numTypeSpecifierPointers;
4168 
4169  // If this is NSError**, report that.
4170  if (auto objcClassDecl = objcObjectPtr->getInterfaceDecl()) {
4171  if (objcClassDecl->getIdentifier() == S.getNSErrorIdent() &&
4172  numNormalPointers == 2 && numTypeSpecifierPointers < 2) {
4173  return PointerDeclaratorKind::NSErrorPointerPointer;
4174  }
4175  }
4176 
4177  break;
4178  }
4179 
4180  // Look at Objective-C class types.
4181  if (auto objcClass = type->getAs<ObjCInterfaceType>()) {
4182  if (objcClass->getInterface()->getIdentifier() == S.getNSErrorIdent()) {
4183  if (numNormalPointers == 2 && numTypeSpecifierPointers < 2)
4184  return PointerDeclaratorKind::NSErrorPointerPointer;
4185  }
4186 
4187  break;
4188  }
4189 
4190  // If at this point we haven't seen a pointer, we won't see one.
4191  if (numNormalPointers == 0)
4192  return PointerDeclaratorKind::NonPointer;
4193 
4194  if (auto recordType = type->getAs<RecordType>()) {
4195  RecordDecl *recordDecl = recordType->getDecl();
4196 
4197  // If this is CFErrorRef*, report it as such.
4198  if (numNormalPointers == 2 && numTypeSpecifierPointers < 2 &&
4199  S.isCFError(recordDecl)) {
4200  return PointerDeclaratorKind::CFErrorRefPointer;
4201  }
4202  break;
4203  }
4204 
4205  break;
4206  } while (true);
4207 
4208  switch (numNormalPointers) {
4209  case 0:
4210  return PointerDeclaratorKind::NonPointer;
4211 
4212  case 1:
4213  return PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer;
4214 
4215  case 2:
4216  return PointerDeclaratorKind::MaybePointerToCFRef;
4217 
4218  default:
4219  return PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer;
4220  }
4221 }
4222 
4223 bool Sema::isCFError(RecordDecl *RD) {
4224  // If we already know about CFError, test it directly.
4225  if (CFError)
4226  return CFError == RD;
4227 
4228  // Check whether this is CFError, which we identify based on its bridge to
4229  // NSError. CFErrorRef used to be declared with "objc_bridge" but is now
4230  // declared with "objc_bridge_mutable", so look for either one of the two
4231  // attributes.
4232  if (RD->getTagKind() == TTK_Struct) {
4233  IdentifierInfo *bridgedType = nullptr;
4234  if (auto bridgeAttr = RD->getAttr<ObjCBridgeAttr>())
4235  bridgedType = bridgeAttr->getBridgedType();
4236  else if (auto bridgeAttr = RD->getAttr<ObjCBridgeMutableAttr>())
4237  bridgedType = bridgeAttr->getBridgedType();
4238 
4239  if (bridgedType == getNSErrorIdent()) {
4240  CFError = RD;
4241  return true;
4242  }
4243  }
4244 
4245  return false;
4246 }
4247 
4248 static FileID getNullabilityCompletenessCheckFileID(Sema &S,
4249  SourceLocation loc) {
4250  // If we're anywhere in a function, method, or closure context, don't perform
4251  // completeness checks.
4252  for (DeclContext *ctx = S.CurContext; ctx; ctx = ctx->getParent()) {
4253  if (ctx->isFunctionOrMethod())
4254  return FileID();
4255 
4256  if (ctx->isFileContext())
4257  break;
4258  }
4259 
4260  // We only care about the expansion location.
4261  loc = S.SourceMgr.getExpansionLoc(loc);
4262  FileID file = S.SourceMgr.getFileID(loc);
4263  if (file.isInvalid())
4264  return FileID();
4265 
4266  // Retrieve file information.
4267  bool invalid = false;
4268  const SrcMgr::SLocEntry &sloc = S.SourceMgr.getSLocEntry(file, &invalid);
4269  if (invalid || !sloc.isFile())
4270  return FileID();
4271 
4272  // We don't want to perform completeness checks on the main file or in
4273  // system headers.
4274  const SrcMgr::FileInfo &fileInfo = sloc.getFile();
4275  if (fileInfo.getIncludeLoc().isInvalid())
4276  return FileID();
4277  if (fileInfo.getFileCharacteristic() != SrcMgr::C_User &&
4278  S.Diags.getSuppressSystemWarnings()) {
4279  return FileID();
4280  }
4281 
4282  return file;
4283 }
4284 
4285 /// Creates a fix-it to insert a C-style nullability keyword at \p pointerLoc,
4286 /// taking into account whitespace before and after.
4287 template <typename DiagBuilderT>
4288 static void fixItNullability(Sema &S, DiagBuilderT &Diag,
4289  SourceLocation PointerLoc,
4290  NullabilityKind Nullability) {
4291  assert(PointerLoc.isValid());
4292  if (PointerLoc.isMacroID())
4293  return;
4294 
4295  SourceLocation FixItLoc = S.getLocForEndOfToken(PointerLoc);
4296  if (!FixItLoc.isValid() || FixItLoc == PointerLoc)
4297  return;
4298 
4299  const char *NextChar = S.SourceMgr.getCharacterData(FixItLoc);
4300  if (!NextChar)
4301  return;
4302 
4303  SmallString<32> InsertionTextBuf{" "};
4304  InsertionTextBuf += getNullabilitySpelling(Nullability);
4305  InsertionTextBuf += " ";
4306  StringRef InsertionText = InsertionTextBuf.str();
4307 
4308  if (isWhitespace(*NextChar)) {
4309  InsertionText = InsertionText.drop_back();
4310  } else if (NextChar[-1] == '[') {
4311  if (NextChar[0] == ']')
4312  InsertionText = InsertionText.drop_back().drop_front();
4313  else
4314  InsertionText = InsertionText.drop_front();
4315  } else if (!isAsciiIdentifierContinue(NextChar[0], /*allow dollar*/ true) &&
4316  !isAsciiIdentifierContinue(NextChar[-1], /*allow dollar*/ true)) {
4317  InsertionText = InsertionText.drop_back().drop_front();
4318  }
4319 
4320  Diag << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FixItLoc, InsertionText);
4321 }
4322 
4323 static void emitNullabilityConsistencyWarning(Sema &S,
4324  SimplePointerKind PointerKind,
4325  SourceLocation PointerLoc,
4326  SourceLocation PointerEndLoc) {
4327  assert(PointerLoc.isValid());
4328 
4329  if (PointerKind == SimplePointerKind::Array) {
4330  S.Diag(PointerLoc, diag::warn_nullability_missing_array);
4331  } else {
4332  S.Diag(PointerLoc, diag::warn_nullability_missing)
4333  << static_cast<unsigned>(PointerKind);
4334  }
4335 
4336  auto FixItLoc = PointerEndLoc.isValid() ? PointerEndLoc : PointerLoc;
4337  if (FixItLoc.isMacroID())
4338  return;
4339 
4340  auto addFixIt = [&](NullabilityKind Nullability) {
4341  auto Diag = S.Diag(FixItLoc, diag::note_nullability_fix_it);
4342  Diag << static_cast<unsigned>(Nullability);
4343  Diag << static_cast<unsigned>(PointerKind);
4344  fixItNullability(S, Diag, FixItLoc, Nullability);
4345  };
4346  addFixIt(NullabilityKind::Nullable);
4347  addFixIt(NullabilityKind::NonNull);
4348 }
4349 
4350 /// Complains about missing nullability if the file containing \p pointerLoc
4351 /// has other uses of nullability (either the keywords or the \c assume_nonnull
4352 /// pragma).
4353 ///
4354 /// If the file has \e not seen other uses of nullability, this particular
4355 /// pointer is saved for possible later diagnosis. See recordNullabilitySeen().
4356 static void
4357 checkNullabilityConsistency(Sema &S, SimplePointerKind pointerKind,
4358  SourceLocation pointerLoc,
4359  SourceLocation pointerEndLoc = SourceLocation()) {
4360  // Determine which file we're performing consistency checking for.
4361  FileID file = getNullabilityCompletenessCheckFileID(S, pointerLoc);
4362  if (file.isInvalid())
4363  return;
4364 
4365  // If we haven't seen any type nullability in this file, we won't warn now
4366  // about anything.
4367  FileNullability &fileNullability = S.NullabilityMap[file];
4368  if (!fileNullability.SawTypeNullability) {
4369  // If this is the first pointer declarator in the file, and the appropriate
4370  // warning is on, record it in case we need to diagnose it retroactively.
4371  diag::kind diagKind;
4372  if (pointerKind == SimplePointerKind::Array)
4373  diagKind = diag::warn_nullability_missing_array;
4374  else
4375  diagKind = diag::warn_nullability_missing;
4376 
4377  if (fileNullability.PointerLoc.isInvalid() &&
4378  !S.Context.getDiagnostics().isIgnored(diagKind, pointerLoc)) {
4379  fileNullability.PointerLoc = pointerLoc;
4380  fileNullability.PointerEndLoc = pointerEndLoc;
4381  fileNullability.PointerKind = static_cast<unsigned>(pointerKind);
4382  }
4383 
4384  return;
4385  }
4386 
4387  // Complain about missing nullability.
4388  emitNullabilityConsistencyWarning(S, pointerKind, pointerLoc, pointerEndLoc);
4389 }
4390 
4391 /// Marks that a nullability feature has been used in the file containing
4392 /// \p loc.
4393 ///
4394 /// If this file already had pointer types in it that were missing nullability,
4395 /// the first such instance is retroactively diagnosed.
4396 ///
4397 /// \sa checkNullabilityConsistency
4398 static void recordNullabilitySeen(Sema &S, SourceLocation loc) {
4399  FileID file = getNullabilityCompletenessCheckFileID(S, loc);
4400  if (file.isInvalid())
4401  return;
4402 
4403  FileNullability &fileNullability = S.NullabilityMap[file];
4404  if (fileNullability.SawTypeNullability)
4405  return;
4406  fileNullability.SawTypeNullability = true;
4407 
4408  // If we haven't seen any type nullability before, now we have. Retroactively
4409  // diagnose the first unannotated pointer, if there was one.
4410  if (fileNullability.PointerLoc.isInvalid())
4411  return;
4412 
4413  auto kind = static_cast<SimplePointerKind>(fileNullability.PointerKind);
4414  emitNullabilityConsistencyWarning(S, kind, fileNullability.PointerLoc,
4415  fileNullability.PointerEndLoc);
4416 }
4417 
4418 /// Returns true if any of the declarator chunks before \p endIndex include a
4419 /// level of indirection: array, pointer, reference, or pointer-to-member.
4420 ///
4421 /// Because declarator chunks are stored in outer-to-inner order, testing
4422 /// every chunk before \p endIndex is testing all chunks that embed the current
4423 /// chunk as part of their type.
4424 ///
4425 /// It is legal to pass the result of Declarator::getNumTypeObjects() as the
4426 /// end index, in which case all chunks are tested.
4427 static bool hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(const Declarator &D, unsigned endIndex) {
4428  unsigned i = endIndex;
4429  while (i != 0) {
4430  // Walk outwards along the declarator chunks.
4431  --i;
4432  const DeclaratorChunk &DC = D.getTypeObject(i);
4433  switch (DC.Kind) {
4434  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
4435  break;
4436  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
4437  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
4438  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
4439  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
4440  return true;
4441  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
4442  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
4443  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
4444  // These are invalid anyway, so just ignore.
4445  break;
4446  }
4447  }
4448  return false;
4449 }
4450 
4451 static bool IsNoDerefableChunk(DeclaratorChunk Chunk) {
4452  return (Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer ||
4453  Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Array);
4454 }

4456 template<typename AttrT>
4457 static AttrT *createSimpleAttr(ASTContext &Ctx, ParsedAttr &AL) {
4458  AL.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
4459  return ::new (Ctx) AttrT(Ctx, AL);
4460 }
4461 
4462 static Attr *createNullabilityAttr(ASTContext &Ctx, ParsedAttr &Attr,
4463  NullabilityKind NK) {
4464  switch (NK) {
4465  case NullabilityKind::NonNull:
4466  return createSimpleAttr<TypeNonNullAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
4467 
4468  case NullabilityKind::Nullable:
4469  return createSimpleAttr<TypeNullableAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
4470 
4471  case NullabilityKind::NullableResult:
4472  return createSimpleAttr<TypeNullableResultAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
4473 
4474  case NullabilityKind::Unspecified:
4475  return createSimpleAttr<TypeNullUnspecifiedAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
4476  }
4477  llvm_unreachable("unknown NullabilityKind");
4478 }

4480 // Diagnose whether this is a case with the multiple addr spaces.
4481 // Returns true if this is an invalid case.
4482 // ISO/IEC TR 18037 S5.3 (amending C99 6.7.3): "No type shall be qualified
4483 // by qualifiers for two or more different address spaces."
4484 static bool DiagnoseMultipleAddrSpaceAttributes(Sema &S, LangAS ASOld,
4485  LangAS ASNew,
4486  SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
4487  if (ASOld != LangAS::Default) {
4488  if (ASOld != ASNew) {
4489  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_address_multiple_qualifiers);
4490  return true;
4491  }
4492  // Emit a warning if they are identical; it's likely unintended.
4493  S.Diag(AttrLoc,
4494  diag::warn_attribute_address_multiple_identical_qualifiers);
4495  }
4496  return false;
4497 }
4498 
4499 static TypeSourceInfo *GetFullTypeForDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &state,
4500  QualType declSpecType,
4501  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo) {
4502  // The TypeSourceInfo that this function returns will not be a null type.
4503  // If there is an error, this function will fill in a dummy type as fallback.
4504  QualType T = declSpecType;
4505  Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
4506  Sema &S = state.getSema();
4507  ASTContext &Context = S.Context;
4508  const LangOptions &LangOpts = S.getLangOpts();
4509 
4510  // The name we're declaring, if any.
4511  DeclarationName Name;
4512  if (D.getIdentifier())
4513  Name = D.getIdentifier();
4514 
4515  // Does this declaration declare a typedef-name?
4516  bool IsTypedefName =
4517  D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() == DeclSpec::SCS_typedef ||
4518  D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasDecl ||
4519  D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplate;
4520 
4521  // Does T refer to a function type with a cv-qualifier or a ref-qualifier?
4522  bool IsQualifiedFunction = T->isFunctionProtoType() &&
4523  (!T->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getMethodQuals().empty() ||
4524  T->castAs<FunctionProtoType>()->getRefQualifier() != RQ_None);
4525 
4526  // If T is 'decltype(auto)', the only declarators we can have are parens
4527  // and at most one function declarator if this is a function declaration.
4528  // If T is a deduced class template specialization type, we can have no
4529  // declarator chunks at all.
4530  if (auto *DT = T->getAs<DeducedType>()) {
4531  const AutoType *AT = T->getAs<AutoType>();
4532  bool IsClassTemplateDeduction = isa<DeducedTemplateSpecializationType>(DT);
4533  if ((AT && AT->isDecltypeAuto()) || IsClassTemplateDeduction) {
4534  for (unsigned I = 0, E = D.getNumTypeObjects(); I != E; ++I) {
4535  unsigned Index = E - I - 1;
4536  DeclaratorChunk &DeclChunk = D.getTypeObject(Index);
4537  unsigned DiagId = IsClassTemplateDeduction
4538  ? diag::err_deduced_class_template_compound_type
4539  : diag::err_decltype_auto_compound_type;
4540  unsigned DiagKind = 0;
4541  switch (DeclChunk.Kind) {
4542  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
4543  // FIXME: Rejecting this is a little silly.
4544  if (IsClassTemplateDeduction) {
4545  DiagKind = 4;
4546  break;
4547  }
4548  continue;
4549  case DeclaratorChunk::Function: {
4550  if (IsClassTemplateDeduction) {
4551  DiagKind = 3;
4552  break;
4553  }
4554  unsigned FnIndex;
4555  if (D.isFunctionDeclarationContext() &&
4556  D.isFunctionDeclarator(FnIndex) && FnIndex == Index)
4557  continue;
4558  DiagId = diag::err_decltype_auto_function_declarator_not_declaration;
4559  break;
4560  }
4561  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
4562  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
4563  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
4564  DiagKind = 0;
4565  break;
4566  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
4567  DiagKind = 1;
4568  break;
4569  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
4570  DiagKind = 2;
4571  break;
4572  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
4573  break;
4574  }
4575 
4576  S.Diag(DeclChunk.Loc, DiagId) << DiagKind;
4577  D.setInvalidType(true);
4578  break;
4579  }
4580  }
4581  }
4582 
4583  // Determine whether we should infer _Nonnull on pointer types.
4584  Optional<NullabilityKind> inferNullability;
4585  bool inferNullabilityCS = false;
4586  bool inferNullabilityInnerOnly = false;
4587  bool inferNullabilityInnerOnlyComplete = false;
4588 
4589  // Are we in an assume-nonnull region?
4590  bool inAssumeNonNullRegion = false;
4591  SourceLocation assumeNonNullLoc = S.PP.getPragmaAssumeNonNullLoc();
4592  if (assumeNonNullLoc.isValid()) {
4593  inAssumeNonNullRegion = true;
4594  recordNullabilitySeen(S, assumeNonNullLoc);
4595  }
4596 
4597  // Whether to complain about missing nullability specifiers or not.
4598  enum {
4599  /// Never complain.
4600  CAMN_No,
4601  /// Complain on the inner pointers (but not the outermost
4602  /// pointer).
4603  CAMN_InnerPointers,
4604  /// Complain about any pointers that don't have nullability
4605  /// specified or inferred.
4606  CAMN_Yes
4607  } complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_No;
4608  unsigned NumPointersRemaining = 0;
4609  auto complainAboutInferringWithinChunk = PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::None;
4610 
4611  if (IsTypedefName) {
4612  // For typedefs, we do not infer any nullability (the default),
4613  // and we only complain about missing nullability specifiers on
4614  // inner pointers.
4615  complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_InnerPointers;
4616 
4617  if (T->canHaveNullability(/*ResultIfUnknown*/false) &&
4618  !T->getNullability(S.Context)) {
4619  // Note that we allow but don't require nullability on dependent types.
4620  ++NumPointersRemaining;
4621  }
4622 
4623  for (unsigned i = 0, n = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != n; ++i) {
4624  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = D.getTypeObject(i);
4625  switch (chunk.Kind) {
4626  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
4627  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
4628  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
4629  break;
4630 
4631  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
4632  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
4633  ++NumPointersRemaining;
4634  break;
4635 
4636  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
4637  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
4638  continue;
4639 
4640  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
4641  ++NumPointersRemaining;
4642  continue;
4643  }
4644  }
4645  } else {
4646  bool isFunctionOrMethod = false;
4647  switch (auto context = state.getDeclarator().getContext()) {
4648  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameter:
4649  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCResult:
4650  case DeclaratorContext::Prototype:
4651  case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturn:
4652  case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVar:
4653  isFunctionOrMethod = true;
4654  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4655 
4656  case DeclaratorContext::Member:
4657  if (state.getDeclarator().isObjCIvar() && !isFunctionOrMethod) {
4658  complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_No;
4659  break;
4660  }
4661 
4662  // Weak properties are inferred to be nullable.
4663  if (state.getDeclarator().isObjCWeakProperty() && inAssumeNonNullRegion) {
4664  inferNullability = NullabilityKind::Nullable;
4665  break;
4666  }
4667 
4668  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4669 
4670  case DeclaratorContext::File:
4671  case DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeList: {
4672  complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_Yes;
4673 
4674  // Nullability inference depends on the type and declarator.
4675  auto wrappingKind = PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::None;
4676  switch (classifyPointerDeclarator(S, T, D, wrappingKind)) {
4677  case PointerDeclaratorKind::NonPointer:
4678  case PointerDeclaratorKind::MultiLevelPointer:
4679  // Cannot infer nullability.
4680  break;
4681 
4682  case PointerDeclaratorKind::SingleLevelPointer:
4683  // Infer _Nonnull if we are in an assumes-nonnull region.
4684  if (inAssumeNonNullRegion) {
4685  complainAboutInferringWithinChunk = wrappingKind;
4686  inferNullability = NullabilityKind::NonNull;
4687  inferNullabilityCS = (context == DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameter ||
4688  context == DeclaratorContext::ObjCResult);
4689  }
4690  break;
4691 
4692  case PointerDeclaratorKind::CFErrorRefPointer:
4693  case PointerDeclaratorKind::NSErrorPointerPointer:
4694  // Within a function or method signature, infer _Nullable at both
4695  // levels.
4696  if (isFunctionOrMethod && inAssumeNonNullRegion)
4697  inferNullability = NullabilityKind::Nullable;
4698  break;
4699 
4700  case PointerDeclaratorKind::MaybePointerToCFRef:
4701  if (isFunctionOrMethod) {
4702  // On pointer-to-pointer parameters marked cf_returns_retained or
4703  // cf_returns_not_retained, if the outer pointer is explicit then
4704  // infer the inner pointer as _Nullable.
4705  auto hasCFReturnsAttr =
4706  [](const ParsedAttributesView &AttrList) -> bool {
4707  return AttrList.hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsRetained) ||
4708  AttrList.hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_CFReturnsNotRetained);
4709  };
4710  if (const auto *InnermostChunk = D.getInnermostNonParenChunk()) {
4711  if (hasCFReturnsAttr(D.getAttributes()) ||
4712  hasCFReturnsAttr(InnermostChunk->getAttrs()) ||
4713  hasCFReturnsAttr(D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes())) {
4714  inferNullability = NullabilityKind::Nullable;
4715  inferNullabilityInnerOnly = true;
4716  }
4717  }
4718  }
4719  break;
4720  }
4721  break;
4722  }
4723 
4724  case DeclaratorContext::ConversionId:
4725  complainAboutMissingNullability = CAMN_Yes;
4726  break;
4727 
4728  case DeclaratorContext::AliasDecl:
4729  case DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplate:
4730  case DeclaratorContext::Block:
4731  case DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteral:
4732  case DeclaratorContext::Condition:
4733  case DeclaratorContext::CXXCatch:
4734  case DeclaratorContext::CXXNew:
4735  case DeclaratorContext::ForInit:
4736  case DeclaratorContext::SelectionInit:
4737  case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr:
4738  case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameter:
4739  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCCatch:
4740  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateParam:
4741  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateArg:
4742  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArg:
4743  case DeclaratorContext::TypeName:
4744  case DeclaratorContext::FunctionalCast:
4745  case DeclaratorContext::RequiresExpr:
4746  // Don't infer in these contexts.
4747  break;
4748  }
4749  }
4750 
4751  // Local function that returns true if its argument looks like a va_list.
4752  auto isVaList = [&S](QualType T) -> bool {
4753  auto *typedefTy = T->getAs<TypedefType>();
4754  if (!typedefTy)
4755  return false;
4756  TypedefDecl *vaListTypedef = S.Context.getBuiltinVaListDecl();
4757  do {
4758  if (typedefTy->getDecl() == vaListTypedef)
4759  return true;
4760  if (auto *name = typedefTy->getDecl()->getIdentifier())
4761  if (name->isStr("va_list"))
4762  return true;
4763  typedefTy = typedefTy->desugar()->getAs<TypedefType>();
4764  } while (typedefTy);
4765  return false;
4766  };
4767 
4768  // Local function that checks the nullability for a given pointer declarator.
4769  // Returns true if _Nonnull was inferred.
4770  auto inferPointerNullability =
4771  [&](SimplePointerKind pointerKind, SourceLocation pointerLoc,
4772  SourceLocation pointerEndLoc,
4773  ParsedAttributesView &attrs, AttributePool &Pool) -> ParsedAttr * {
4774  // We've seen a pointer.
4775  if (NumPointersRemaining > 0)
4776  --NumPointersRemaining;
4777 
4778  // If a nullability attribute is present, there's nothing to do.
4779  if (hasNullabilityAttr(attrs))
4780  return nullptr;
4781 
4782  // If we're supposed to infer nullability, do so now.
4783  if (inferNullability && !inferNullabilityInnerOnlyComplete) {
4784  ParsedAttr::Syntax syntax = inferNullabilityCS
4785  ? ParsedAttr::AS_ContextSensitiveKeyword
4786  : ParsedAttr::AS_Keyword;
4787  ParsedAttr *nullabilityAttr = Pool.create(
4788  S.getNullabilityKeyword(*inferNullability), SourceRange(pointerLoc),
4789  nullptr, SourceLocation(), nullptr, 0, syntax);
4790 
4791  attrs.addAtEnd(nullabilityAttr);
4792 
4793  if (inferNullabilityCS) {
4794  state.getDeclarator().getMutableDeclSpec().getObjCQualifiers()
4795  ->setObjCDeclQualifier(ObjCDeclSpec::DQ_CSNullability);
4796  }
4797 
4798  if (pointerLoc.isValid() &&
4799  complainAboutInferringWithinChunk !=
4800  PointerWrappingDeclaratorKind::None) {
4801  auto Diag =
4802  S.Diag(pointerLoc, diag::warn_nullability_inferred_on_nested_type);
4803  Diag << static_cast<int>(complainAboutInferringWithinChunk);
4804  fixItNullability(S, Diag, pointerLoc, NullabilityKind::NonNull);
4805  }
4806 
4807  if (inferNullabilityInnerOnly)
4808  inferNullabilityInnerOnlyComplete = true;
4809  return nullabilityAttr;
4810  }
4811 
4812  // If we're supposed to complain about missing nullability, do so
4813  // now if it's truly missing.
4814  switch (complainAboutMissingNullability) {
4815  case CAMN_No:
4816  break;
4817 
4818  case CAMN_InnerPointers:
4819  if (NumPointersRemaining == 0)
4820  break;
4821  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
4822 
4823  case CAMN_Yes:
4824  checkNullabilityConsistency(S, pointerKind, pointerLoc, pointerEndLoc);
4825  }
4826  return nullptr;
4827  };
4828 
4829  // If the type itself could have nullability but does not, infer pointer
4830  // nullability and perform consistency checking.
4831  if (S.CodeSynthesisContexts.empty()) {
4832  if (T->canHaveNullability(/*ResultIfUnknown*/false) &&
4833  !T->getNullability(S.Context)) {
4834  if (isVaList(T)) {
4835  // Record that we've seen a pointer, but do nothing else.
4836  if (NumPointersRemaining > 0)
4837  --NumPointersRemaining;
4838  } else {
4839  SimplePointerKind pointerKind = SimplePointerKind::Pointer;
4840  if (T->isBlockPointerType())
4841  pointerKind = SimplePointerKind::BlockPointer;
4842  else if (T->isMemberPointerType())
4843  pointerKind = SimplePointerKind::MemberPointer;
4844 
4845  if (auto *attr = inferPointerNullability(
4846  pointerKind, D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
4847  D.getDeclSpec().getEndLoc(),
4848  D.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes(),
4849  D.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributePool())) {
4850  T = state.getAttributedType(
4851  createNullabilityAttr(Context, *attr, *inferNullability), T, T);
4852  }
4853  }
4854  }
4855 
4856  if (complainAboutMissingNullability == CAMN_Yes &&
4857  T->isArrayType() && !T->getNullability(S.Context) && !isVaList(T) &&
4858  D.isPrototypeContext() &&
4859  !hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(D, D.getNumTypeObjects())) {
4860  checkNullabilityConsistency(S, SimplePointerKind::Array,
4861  D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
4862  }
4863  }
4864 
4865  bool ExpectNoDerefChunk =
4866  state.getCurrentAttributes().hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_NoDeref);
4867 
4868  // Walk the DeclTypeInfo, building the recursive type as we go.
4869  // DeclTypeInfos are ordered from the identifier out, which is
4870  // opposite of what we want :).
4871  for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
4872  unsigned chunkIndex = e - i - 1;
4873  state.setCurrentChunkIndex(chunkIndex);
4874  DeclaratorChunk &DeclType = D.getTypeObject(chunkIndex);
4875  IsQualifiedFunction &= DeclType.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Paren;
4876  switch (DeclType.Kind) {
4877  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
4878  if (i == 0)
4879  warnAboutRedundantParens(S, D, T);
4880  T = S.BuildParenType(T);
4881  break;
4882  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
4883  // If blocks are disabled, emit an error.
4884  if (!LangOpts.Blocks)
4885  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_blocks_disable) << LangOpts.OpenCL;
4886 
4887  // Handle pointer nullability.
4888  inferPointerNullability(SimplePointerKind::BlockPointer, DeclType.Loc,
4889  DeclType.EndLoc, DeclType.getAttrs(),
4890  state.getDeclarator().getAttributePool());
4891 
4892  T = S.BuildBlockPointerType(T, D.getIdentifierLoc(), Name);
4893  if (DeclType.Cls.TypeQuals || LangOpts.OpenCL) {
4894  // OpenCL v2.0, s6.12.5 - Block variable declarations are implicitly
4895  // qualified with const.
4896  if (LangOpts.OpenCL)
4897  DeclType.Cls.TypeQuals |= DeclSpec::TQ_const;
4898  T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, DeclType.Cls.TypeQuals);
4899  }
4900  break;
4901  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
4902  // Verify that we're not building a pointer to pointer to function with
4903  // exception specification.
4904  if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && S.CheckDistantExceptionSpec(T)) {
4905  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_distant_exception_spec);
4906  D.setInvalidType(true);
4907  // Build the type anyway.
4908  }
4909 
4910  // Handle pointer nullability
4911  inferPointerNullability(SimplePointerKind::Pointer, DeclType.Loc,
4912  DeclType.EndLoc, DeclType.getAttrs(),
4913  state.getDeclarator().getAttributePool());
4914 
4915  if (LangOpts.ObjC && T->getAs<ObjCObjectType>()) {
4916  T = Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(T);
4917  if (DeclType.Ptr.TypeQuals)
4918  T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, DeclType.Ptr.TypeQuals);
4919  break;
4920  }
4921 
4922  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.9b - Pointer to image/sampler cannot be used.
4923  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.13.16.1 - Pointer to pipe cannot be used.
4924  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.12.5 - Pointers to Blocks are not allowed.
4925  if (LangOpts.OpenCL || LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
4926  if (T->isImageType() || T->isSamplerT() || T->isPipeType() ||
4927  T->isBlockPointerType()) {
4928  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_pointer_to_type) << T;
4929  D.setInvalidType(true);
4930  }
4931  }
4932 
4933  T = S.BuildPointerType(T, DeclType.Loc, Name);
4934  if (DeclType.Ptr.TypeQuals)
4935  T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, DeclType.Ptr.TypeQuals);
4936  break;
4937  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference: {
4938  // Verify that we're not building a reference to pointer to function with
4939  // exception specification.
4940  if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && S.CheckDistantExceptionSpec(T)) {
4941  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_distant_exception_spec);
4942  D.setInvalidType(true);
4943  // Build the type anyway.
4944  }
4945  T = S.BuildReferenceType(T, DeclType.Ref.LValueRef, DeclType.Loc, Name);
4946 
4947  if (DeclType.Ref.HasRestrict)
4948  T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, Qualifiers::Restrict);
4949  break;
4950  }
4951  case DeclaratorChunk::Array: {
4952  // Verify that we're not building an array of pointers to function with
4953  // exception specification.
4954  if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && S.CheckDistantExceptionSpec(T)) {
4955  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_distant_exception_spec);
4956  D.setInvalidType(true);
4957  // Build the type anyway.
4958  }
4959  DeclaratorChunk::ArrayTypeInfo &ATI = DeclType.Arr;
4960  Expr *ArraySize = static_cast<Expr*>(ATI.NumElts);
4961  ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM;
4962  if (ATI.isStar)
4963  ASM = ArrayType::Star;
4964  else if (ATI.hasStatic)
4965  ASM = ArrayType::Static;
4966  else
4967  ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
4968  if (ASM == ArrayType::Star && !D.isPrototypeContext()) {
4969  // FIXME: This check isn't quite right: it allows star in prototypes
4970  // for function definitions, and disallows some edge cases detailed
4971  // in http://gcc.gnu.org/ml/gcc-patches/2009-02/msg00133.html
4972  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_array_star_outside_prototype);
4973  ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
4974  D.setInvalidType(true);
4975  }
4976 
4977  // C99 6.7.5.2p1: The optional type qualifiers and the keyword static
4978  // shall appear only in a declaration of a function parameter with an
4979  // array type, ...
4980  if (ASM == ArrayType::Static || ATI.TypeQuals) {
4981  if (!(D.isPrototypeContext() ||
4982  D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeList)) {
4983  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_array_static_outside_prototype) <<
4984  (ASM == ArrayType::Static ? "'static'" : "type qualifier");
4985  // Remove the 'static' and the type qualifiers.
4986  if (ASM == ArrayType::Static)
4987  ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
4988  ATI.TypeQuals = 0;
4989  D.setInvalidType(true);
4990  }
4991 
4992  // C99 6.7.5.2p1: ... and then only in the outermost array type
4993  // derivation.
4994  if (hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(D, chunkIndex)) {
4995  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_array_static_not_outermost) <<
4996  (ASM == ArrayType::Static ? "'static'" : "type qualifier");
4997  if (ASM == ArrayType::Static)
4998  ASM = ArrayType::Normal;
4999  ATI.TypeQuals = 0;
5000  D.setInvalidType(true);
5001  }
5002  }
5003  const AutoType *AT = T->getContainedAutoType();
5004  // Allow arrays of auto if we are a generic lambda parameter.
5005  // i.e. [](auto (&array)[5]) { return array[0]; }; OK
5006  if (AT && D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameter) {
5007  // We've already diagnosed this for decltype(auto).
5008  if (!AT->isDecltypeAuto())
5009  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_illegal_decl_array_of_auto)
5010  << getPrintableNameForEntity(Name) << T;
5011  T = QualType();
5012  break;
5013  }
5014 
5015  // Array parameters can be marked nullable as well, although it's not
5016  // necessary if they're marked 'static'.
5017  if (complainAboutMissingNullability == CAMN_Yes &&
5018  !hasNullabilityAttr(DeclType.getAttrs()) &&
5019  ASM != ArrayType::Static &&
5020  D.isPrototypeContext() &&
5021  !hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(D, chunkIndex)) {
5022  checkNullabilityConsistency(S, SimplePointerKind::Array, DeclType.Loc);
5023  }
5024 
5025  T = S.BuildArrayType(T, ASM, ArraySize, ATI.TypeQuals,
5026  SourceRange(DeclType.Loc, DeclType.EndLoc), Name);
5027  break;
5028  }
5029  case DeclaratorChunk::Function: {
5030  // If the function declarator has a prototype (i.e. it is not () and
5031  // does not have a K&R-style identifier list), then the arguments are part
5032  // of the type, otherwise the argument list is ().
5033  DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI = DeclType.Fun;
5034  IsQualifiedFunction =
5035  FTI.hasMethodTypeQualifiers() || FTI.hasRefQualifier();
5036 
5037  // Check for auto functions and trailing return type and adjust the
5038  // return type accordingly.
5039  if (!D.isInvalidType()) {
5040  // trailing-return-type is only required if we're declaring a function,
5041  // and not, for instance, a pointer to a function.
5042  if (D.getDeclSpec().hasAutoTypeSpec() &&
5043  !FTI.hasTrailingReturnType() && chunkIndex == 0) {
5044  if (!S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus14) {
5045  S.Diag(D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
5046  D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_auto
5047  ? diag::err_auto_missing_trailing_return
5048  : diag::err_deduced_return_type);
5049  T = Context.IntTy;
5050  D.setInvalidType(true);
5051  } else {
5052  S.Diag(D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
5053  diag::warn_cxx11_compat_deduced_return_type);
5054  }
5055  } else if (FTI.hasTrailingReturnType()) {
5056  // T must be exactly 'auto' at this point. See CWG issue 681.
5057  if (isa<ParenType>(T)) {
5058  S.Diag(D.getBeginLoc(), diag::err_trailing_return_in_parens)
5059  << T << D.getSourceRange();
5060  D.setInvalidType(true);
5061  } else if (D.getName().getKind() ==
5062  UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_DeductionGuideName) {
5063  if (T != Context.DependentTy) {
5064  S.Diag(D.getDeclSpec().getBeginLoc(),
5065  diag::err_deduction_guide_with_complex_decl)
5066  << D.getSourceRange();
5067  D.setInvalidType(true);
5068  }
5069  } else if (D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr &&
5070  (T.hasQualifiers() || !isa<AutoType>(T) ||
5071  cast<AutoType>(T)->getKeyword() !=
5072  AutoTypeKeyword::Auto ||
5073  cast<AutoType>(T)->isConstrained())) {
5074  S.Diag(D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc(),
5075  diag::err_trailing_return_without_auto)
5076  << T << D.getDeclSpec().getSourceRange();
5077  D.setInvalidType(true);
5078  }
5079  T = S.GetTypeFromParser(FTI.getTrailingReturnType(), &TInfo);
5080  if (T.isNull()) {
5081  // An error occurred parsing the trailing return type.
5082  T = Context.IntTy;
5083  D.setInvalidType(true);
5084  } else if (AutoType *Auto = T->getContainedAutoType()) {
5085  // If the trailing return type contains an `auto`, we may need to
5086  // invent a template parameter for it, for cases like
5087  // `auto f() -> C auto` or `[](auto (*p) -> auto) {}`.
5088  InventedTemplateParameterInfo *InventedParamInfo = nullptr;
5089  if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::Prototype)
5090  InventedParamInfo = &S.InventedParameterInfos.back();
5091  else if (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameter)
5092  InventedParamInfo = S.getCurLambda();
5093  if (InventedParamInfo) {
5094  std::tie(T, TInfo) = InventTemplateParameter(
5095  state, T, TInfo, Auto, *InventedParamInfo);
5096  }
5097  }
5098  } else {
5099  // This function type is not the type of the entity being declared,
5100  // so checking the 'auto' is not the responsibility of this chunk.
5101  }
5102  }
5103 
5104  // C99 6.7.5.3p1: The return type may not be a function or array type.
5105  // For conversion functions, we'll diagnose this particular error later.
5106  if (!D.isInvalidType() && (T->isArrayType() || T->isFunctionType()) &&
5107  (D.getName().getKind() !=
5108  UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_ConversionFunctionId)) {
5109  unsigned diagID = diag::err_func_returning_array_function;
5110  // Last processing chunk in block context means this function chunk
5111  // represents the block.
5112  if (chunkIndex == 0 &&
5113  D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteral)
5114  diagID = diag::err_block_returning_array_function;
5115  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diagID) << T->isFunctionType() << T;
5116  T = Context.IntTy;
5117  D.setInvalidType(true);
5118  }
5119 
5120  // Do not allow returning half FP value.
5121  // FIXME: This really should be in BuildFunctionType.
5122  if (T->isHalfType()) {
5123  if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
5124  if (!S.getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption("cl_khr_fp16",
5125  S.getLangOpts())) {
5126  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_return)
5127  << T << 0 /*pointer hint*/;
5128  D.setInvalidType(true);
5129  }
5130  } else if (!S.getLangOpts().HalfArgsAndReturns) {
5131  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(),
5132  diag::err_parameters_retval_cannot_have_fp16_type) << 1;
5133  D.setInvalidType(true);
5134  }
5135  }
5136 
5137  if (LangOpts.OpenCL) {
5138  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.12.5 - A pipe cannot be the return value of a
5139  // function. Disrespect this for SYCL.
5140  if (T->isPipeType()) {
5141  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_return)
5142  << T << 1 /*hint off*/;
5143  D.setInvalidType(true);
5144  }
5145  }
5146 
5147  if (LangOpts.OpenCL || LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
5148  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.12.5 - A block cannot be the return value of a
5149  // function.
5150  if (!T->isSampledImageType() &&
5151  (T->isBlockPointerType() || T->isImageType() || T->isSamplerT())) {
5152  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_return)
5153  << T << 1 /*hint off*/;
5154  D.setInvalidType(true);
5155  }
5156  // OpenCL doesn't support variadic functions and blocks
5157  // (s6.9.e and s6.12.5 OpenCL v2.0) except for printf.
5158  // We also allow here any toolchain reserved identifiers.
5159  if (FTI.isVariadic &&
5160  !LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice &&
5161  !S.getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption(
5162  "__cl_clang_variadic_functions", S.getLangOpts()) &&
5163  !(D.getIdentifier() &&
5164  ((D.getIdentifier()->getName() == "printf" &&
5165  LangOpts.getOpenCLCompatibleVersion() >= 120) ||
5166  D.getIdentifier()->getName().startswith("__")))) {
5167  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::err_opencl_variadic_function);
5168  D.setInvalidType(true);
5169  }
5170  }
5171 
5172  // Methods cannot return interface types. All ObjC objects are
5173  // passed by reference.
5174  if (T->isObjCObjectType()) {
5175  SourceLocation DiagLoc, FixitLoc;
5176  if (TInfo) {
5177  DiagLoc = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc();
5178  FixitLoc = S.getLocForEndOfToken(TInfo->getTypeLoc().getEndLoc());
5179  } else {
5180  DiagLoc = D.getDeclSpec().getTypeSpecTypeLoc();
5181  FixitLoc = S.getLocForEndOfToken(D.getDeclSpec().getEndLoc());
5182  }
5183  S.Diag(DiagLoc, diag::err_object_cannot_be_passed_returned_by_value)
5184  << 0 << T
5185  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FixitLoc, "*");
5186 
5187  T = Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(T);
5188  if (TInfo) {
5189  TypeLocBuilder TLB;
5190  TLB.pushFullCopy(TInfo->getTypeLoc());
5191  ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc TLoc = TLB.push<ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc>(T);
5192  TLoc.setStarLoc(FixitLoc);
5193  TInfo = TLB.getTypeSourceInfo(Context, T);
5194  }
5195 
5196  D.setInvalidType(true);
5197  }
5198 
5199  // cv-qualifiers on return types are pointless except when the type is a
5200  // class type in C++.
5201  if ((T.getCVRQualifiers() || T->isAtomicType()) &&
5202  !(S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5203  (T->isDependentType() || T->isRecordType()))) {
5204  if (T->isVoidType() && !S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
5205  D.getFunctionDefinitionKind() ==
5206  FunctionDefinitionKind::Definition) {
5207  // [6.9.1/3] qualified void return is invalid on a C
5208  // function definition. Apparently ok on declarations and
5209  // in C++ though (!)
5210  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_func_returning_qualified_void) << T;
5211  } else
5212  diagnoseRedundantReturnTypeQualifiers(S, T, D, chunkIndex);
5213 
5214  // C++2a [dcl.fct]p12:
5215  // A volatile-qualified return type is deprecated
5216  if (T.isVolatileQualified() && S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20)
5217  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::warn_deprecated_volatile_return) << T;
5218  }
5219 
5220  // Objective-C ARC ownership qualifiers are ignored on the function
5221  // return type (by type canonicalization). Complain if this attribute
5222  // was written here.
5223  if (T.getQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime()) {
5224  SourceLocation AttrLoc;
5225  if (chunkIndex + 1 < D.getNumTypeObjects()) {
5226  DeclaratorChunk ReturnTypeChunk = D.getTypeObject(chunkIndex + 1);
5227  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : ReturnTypeChunk.getAttrs()) {
5228  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership) {
5229  AttrLoc = AL.getLoc();
5230  break;
5231  }
5232  }
5233  }
5234  if (AttrLoc.isInvalid()) {
5235  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes()) {
5236  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership) {
5237  AttrLoc = AL.getLoc();
5238  break;
5239  }
5240  }
5241  }
5242 
5243  if (AttrLoc.isValid()) {
5244  // The ownership attributes are almost always written via
5245  // the predefined
5246  // __strong/__weak/__autoreleasing/__unsafe_unretained.
5247  if (AttrLoc.isMacroID())
5248  AttrLoc =
5249  S.SourceMgr.getImmediateExpansionRange(AttrLoc).getBegin();
5250 
5251  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_arc_lifetime_result_type)
5252  << T.getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime();
5253  }
5254  }
5255 
5256  if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && D.getDeclSpec().hasTagDefinition()) {
5257  // C++ [dcl.fct]p6:
5258  // Types shall not be defined in return or parameter types.
5259  TagDecl *Tag = cast<TagDecl>(D.getDeclSpec().getRepAsDecl());
5260  S.Diag(Tag->getLocation(), diag::err_type_defined_in_result_type)
5261  << Context.getTypeDeclType(Tag);
5262  }
5263 
5264  // Exception specs are not allowed in typedefs. Complain, but add it
5265  // anyway.
5266  if (IsTypedefName && FTI.getExceptionSpecType() && !LangOpts.CPlusPlus17)
5267  S.Diag(FTI.getExceptionSpecLocBeg(),
5268  diag::err_exception_spec_in_typedef)
5269  << (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasDecl ||
5270  D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplate);
5271 
5272  // If we see "T var();" or "T var(T());" at block scope, it is probably
5273  // an attempt to initialize a variable, not a function declaration.
5274  if (FTI.isAmbiguous)
5275  warnAboutAmbiguousFunction(S, D, DeclType, T);
5276 
5277  FunctionType::ExtInfo EI(
5278  getCCForDeclaratorChunk(S, D, DeclType.getAttrs(), FTI, chunkIndex));
5279 
5280  if (!FTI.NumParams && !FTI.isVariadic && !LangOpts.CPlusPlus &&
5281  !LangOpts.OpenCL && !LangOpts.SYCLIsDevice) {
5282  // Simple void foo(), where the incoming T is the result type.
5283  T = Context.getFunctionNoProtoType(T, EI);
5284  } else {
5285  // We allow a zero-parameter variadic function in C if the
5286  // function is marked with the "overloadable" attribute. Scan
5287  // for this attribute now.
5288  if (!FTI.NumParams && FTI.isVariadic && !LangOpts.CPlusPlus)
5289  if (!D.getAttributes().hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_Overloadable) &&
5290  !D.getDeclSpec().getAttributes().hasAttribute(
5291  ParsedAttr::AT_Overloadable))
5292  S.Diag(FTI.getEllipsisLoc(), diag::err_ellipsis_first_param);
5293 
5294  if (FTI.NumParams && FTI.Params[0].Param == nullptr) {
5295  // C99 6.7.5.3p3: Reject int(x,y,z) when it's not a function
5296  // definition.
5297  S.Diag(FTI.Params[0].IdentLoc,
5298  diag::err_ident_list_in_fn_declaration);
5299  D.setInvalidType(true);
5300  // Recover by creating a K&R-style function type.
5301  T = Context.getFunctionNoProtoType(T, EI);
5302  break;
5303  }
5304 
5305  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI;
5306  EPI.ExtInfo = EI;
5307  EPI.Variadic = FTI.isVariadic;
5308  EPI.EllipsisLoc = FTI.getEllipsisLoc();
5309  EPI.HasTrailingReturn = FTI.hasTrailingReturnType();
5310  EPI.TypeQuals.addCVRUQualifiers(
5311  FTI.MethodQualifiers ? FTI.MethodQualifiers->getTypeQualifiers()
5312  : 0);
5313  EPI.RefQualifier = !FTI.hasRefQualifier()? RQ_None
5314  : FTI.RefQualifierIsLValueRef? RQ_LValue
5315  : RQ_RValue;
5316 
5317  // Otherwise, we have a function with a parameter list that is
5318  // potentially variadic.
5319  SmallVector<QualType, 16> ParamTys;
5320  ParamTys.reserve(FTI.NumParams);
5321 
5322  SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 16>
5323  ExtParameterInfos(FTI.NumParams);
5324  bool HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = false;
5325 
5326  for (unsigned i = 0, e = FTI.NumParams; i != e; ++i) {
5327  ParmVarDecl *Param = cast<ParmVarDecl>(FTI.Params[i].Param);
5328  QualType ParamTy = Param->getType();
5329  assert(!ParamTy.isNull() && "Couldn't parse type?");
5330 
5331  // Look for 'void'. void is allowed only as a single parameter to a
5332  // function with no other parameters (C99 6.7.5.3p10). We record
5333  // int(void) as a FunctionProtoType with an empty parameter list.
5334  if (ParamTy->isVoidType()) {
5335  // If this is something like 'float(int, void)', reject it. 'void'
5336  // is an incomplete type (C99 6.2.5p19) and function decls cannot
5337  // have parameters of incomplete type.
5338  if (FTI.NumParams != 1 || FTI.isVariadic) {
5339  S.Diag(FTI.Params[i].IdentLoc, diag::err_void_only_param);
5340  ParamTy = Context.IntTy;
5341  Param->setType(ParamTy);
5342  } else if (FTI.Params[i].Ident) {
5343  // Reject, but continue to parse 'int(void abc)'.
5344  S.Diag(FTI.Params[i].IdentLoc, diag::err_param_with_void_type);
5345  ParamTy = Context.IntTy;
5346  Param->setType(ParamTy);
5347  } else {
5348  // Reject, but continue to parse 'float(const void)'.
5349  if (ParamTy.hasQualifiers())
5350  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::err_void_param_qualified);
5351 
5352  // Do not add 'void' to the list.
5353  break;
5354  }
5355  } else if (ParamTy->isHalfType()) {
5356  // Disallow half FP parameters.
5357  // FIXME: This really should be in BuildFunctionType.
5358  if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
5359  if (!S.getOpenCLOptions().isAvailableOption("cl_khr_fp16",
5360  S.getLangOpts())) {
5361  S.Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_param)
5362  << ParamTy << 0;
5363  D.setInvalidType();
5364  Param->setInvalidDecl();
5365  }
5366  } else if (!S.getLangOpts().HalfArgsAndReturns) {
5367  S.Diag(Param->getLocation(),
5368  diag::err_parameters_retval_cannot_have_fp16_type) << 0;
5369  D.setInvalidType();
5370  }
5371  } else if (!FTI.hasPrototype) {
5372  if (ParamTy->isPromotableIntegerType()) {
5373  ParamTy = Context.getPromotedIntegerType(ParamTy);
5374  Param->setKNRPromoted(true);
5375  } else if (const BuiltinType* BTy = ParamTy->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
5376  if (BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Float) {
5377  ParamTy = Context.DoubleTy;
5378  Param->setKNRPromoted(true);
5379  }
5380  }
5381  } else if (S.getLangOpts().OpenCL && ParamTy->isBlockPointerType()) {
5382  // OpenCL 2.0 s6.12.5: A block cannot be a parameter of a function.
5383  S.Diag(Param->getLocation(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_param)
5384  << ParamTy << 1 /*hint off*/;
5385  D.setInvalidType();
5386  }
5387 
5388  if (LangOpts.ObjCAutoRefCount && Param->hasAttr<NSConsumedAttr>()) {
5389  ExtParameterInfos[i] = ExtParameterInfos[i].withIsConsumed(true);
5390  HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = true;
5391  }
5392 
5393  if (auto attr = Param->getAttr<ParameterABIAttr>()) {
5394  ExtParameterInfos[i] =
5395  ExtParameterInfos[i].withABI(attr->getABI());
5396  HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = true;
5397  }
5398 
5399  if (Param->hasAttr<PassObjectSizeAttr>()) {
5400  ExtParameterInfos[i] = ExtParameterInfos[i].withHasPassObjectSize();
5401  HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = true;
5402  }
5403 
5404  if (Param->hasAttr<NoEscapeAttr>()) {
5405  ExtParameterInfos[i] = ExtParameterInfos[i].withIsNoEscape(true);
5406  HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos = true;
5407  }
5408 
5409  ParamTys.push_back(ParamTy);
5410  }
5411 
5412  if (HasAnyInterestingExtParameterInfos) {
5413  EPI.ExtParameterInfos = ExtParameterInfos.data();
5414  checkExtParameterInfos(S, ParamTys, EPI,
5415  [&](unsigned i) { return FTI.Params[i].Param->getLocation(); });
5416  }
5417 
5418  SmallVector<QualType, 4> Exceptions;
5419  SmallVector<ParsedType, 2> DynamicExceptions;
5420  SmallVector<SourceRange, 2> DynamicExceptionRanges;
5421  Expr *NoexceptExpr = nullptr;
5422 
5423  if (FTI.getExceptionSpecType() == EST_Dynamic) {
5424  // FIXME: It's rather inefficient to have to split into two vectors
5425  // here.
5426  unsigned N = FTI.getNumExceptions();
5427  DynamicExceptions.reserve(N);
5428  DynamicExceptionRanges.reserve(N);
5429  for (unsigned I = 0; I != N; ++I) {
5430  DynamicExceptions.push_back(FTI.Exceptions[I].Ty);
5431  DynamicExceptionRanges.push_back(FTI.Exceptions[I].Range);
5432  }
5433  } else if (isComputedNoexcept(FTI.getExceptionSpecType())) {
5434  NoexceptExpr = FTI.NoexceptExpr;
5435  }
5436 
5437  S.checkExceptionSpecification(D.isFunctionDeclarationContext(),
5438  FTI.getExceptionSpecType(),
5439  DynamicExceptions,
5440  DynamicExceptionRanges,
5441  NoexceptExpr,
5442  Exceptions,
5443  EPI.ExceptionSpec);
5444 
5445  // FIXME: Set address space from attrs for C++ mode here.
5446  // OpenCLCPlusPlus: A class member function has an address space.
5447  auto IsClassMember = [&]() {
5448  return (!state.getDeclarator().getCXXScopeSpec().isEmpty() &&
5449  state.getDeclarator()
5450  .getCXXScopeSpec()
5451  .getScopeRep()
5452  ->getKind() == NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec) ||
5453  state.getDeclarator().getContext() ==
5454  DeclaratorContext::Member ||
5455  state.getDeclarator().getContext() ==
5456  DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr;
5457  };
5458 
5459  if (state.getSema().getLangOpts().OpenCLCPlusPlus && IsClassMember()) {
5460  LangAS ASIdx = LangAS::Default;
5461  // Take address space attr if any and mark as invalid to avoid adding
5462  // them later while creating QualType.
5463  if (FTI.MethodQualifiers)
5464  for (ParsedAttr &attr : FTI.MethodQualifiers->getAttributes()) {
5465  LangAS ASIdxNew = attr.asOpenCLLangAS();
5466  if (DiagnoseMultipleAddrSpaceAttributes(S, ASIdx, ASIdxNew,
5467  attr.getLoc()))
5468  D.setInvalidType(true);
5469  else
5470  ASIdx = ASIdxNew;
5471  }
5472  // If a class member function's address space is not set, set it to
5473  // __generic.
5474  LangAS AS =
5475  (ASIdx == LangAS::Default ? S.getDefaultCXXMethodAddrSpace()
5476  : ASIdx);
5477  EPI.TypeQuals.addAddressSpace(AS);
5478  }
5479  T = Context.getFunctionType(T, ParamTys, EPI);
5480  }
5481  break;
5482  }
5483  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer: {
5484  // The scope spec must refer to a class, or be dependent.
5485  CXXScopeSpec &SS = DeclType.Mem.Scope();
5486  QualType ClsType;
5487 
5488  // Handle pointer nullability.
5489  inferPointerNullability(SimplePointerKind::MemberPointer, DeclType.Loc,
5490  DeclType.EndLoc, DeclType.getAttrs(),
5491  state.getDeclarator().getAttributePool());
5492 
5493  if (SS.isInvalid()) {
5494  // Avoid emitting extra errors if we already errored on the scope.
5495  D.setInvalidType(true);
5496  } else if (S.isDependentScopeSpecifier(SS) ||
5497  isa_and_nonnull<CXXRecordDecl>(S.computeDeclContext(SS))) {
5498  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS = SS.getScopeRep();
5499  NestedNameSpecifier *NNSPrefix = NNS->getPrefix();
5500  switch (NNS->getKind()) {
5501  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
5502  ClsType = Context.getDependentNameType(ETK_None, NNSPrefix,
5503  NNS->getAsIdentifier());
5504  break;
5505 
5506  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
5507  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
5508  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
5509  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
5510  llvm_unreachable("Nested-name-specifier must name a type");
5511 
5512  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
5513  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
5514  ClsType = QualType(NNS->getAsType(), 0);
5515  // Note: if the NNS has a prefix and ClsType is a nondependent
5516  // TemplateSpecializationType, then the NNS prefix is NOT included
5517  // in ClsType; hence we wrap ClsType into an ElaboratedType.
5518  // NOTE: in particular, no wrap occurs if ClsType already is an
5519  // Elaborated, DependentName, or DependentTemplateSpecialization.
5520  if (NNSPrefix && isa<TemplateSpecializationType>(NNS->getAsType()))
5521  ClsType = Context.getElaboratedType(ETK_None, NNSPrefix, ClsType);
5522  break;
5523  }
5524  } else {
5525  S.Diag(DeclType.Mem.Scope().getBeginLoc(),
5526  diag::err_illegal_decl_mempointer_in_nonclass)
5527  << (D.getIdentifier() ? D.getIdentifier()->getName() : "type name")
5528  << DeclType.Mem.Scope().getRange();
5529  D.setInvalidType(true);
5530  }
5531 
5532  if (!ClsType.isNull())
5533  T = S.BuildMemberPointerType(T, ClsType, DeclType.Loc,
5534  D.getIdentifier());
5535  if (T.isNull()) {
5536  T = Context.IntTy;
5537  D.setInvalidType(true);
5538  } else if (DeclType.Mem.TypeQuals) {
5539  T = S.BuildQualifiedType(T, DeclType.Loc, DeclType.Mem.TypeQuals);
5540  }
5541  break;
5542  }
5543 
5544  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe: {
5545  T = S.BuildReadPipeType(T, DeclType.Loc);
5546  processTypeAttrs(state, T, TAL_DeclSpec,
5547  D.getMutableDeclSpec().getAttributes());
5548  break;
5549  }
5550  }
5551 
5552  if (T.isNull()) {
5553  D.setInvalidType(true);
5554  T = Context.IntTy;
5555  }
5556 
5557  // See if there are any attributes on this declarator chunk.
5558  processTypeAttrs(state, T, TAL_DeclChunk, DeclType.getAttrs());
5559 
5560  if (DeclType.Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Paren) {
5561  if (ExpectNoDerefChunk && !IsNoDerefableChunk(DeclType))
5562  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::warn_noderef_on_non_pointer_or_array);
5563 
5564  ExpectNoDerefChunk = state.didParseNoDeref();
5565  }
5566  }
5567 
5568  if (ExpectNoDerefChunk)
5569  S.Diag(state.getDeclarator().getBeginLoc(),
5570  diag::warn_noderef_on_non_pointer_or_array);
5571 
5572  // GNU warning -Wstrict-prototypes
5573  // Warn if a function declaration is without a prototype.
5574  // This warning is issued for all kinds of unprototyped function
5575  // declarations (i.e. function type typedef, function pointer etc.)
5576  // C99 6.7.5.3p14:
5577  // The empty list in a function declarator that is not part of a definition
5578  // of that function specifies that no information about the number or types
5579  // of the parameters is supplied.
5580  if (!LangOpts.CPlusPlus &&
5581  D.getFunctionDefinitionKind() == FunctionDefinitionKind::Declaration) {
5582  bool IsBlock = false;
5583  for (const DeclaratorChunk &DeclType : D.type_objects()) {
5584  switch (DeclType.Kind) {
5585  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
5586  IsBlock = true;
5587  break;
5588  case DeclaratorChunk::Function: {
5589  const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI = DeclType.Fun;
5590  // We suppress the warning when there's no LParen location, as this
5591  // indicates the declaration was an implicit declaration, which gets
5592  // warned about separately via -Wimplicit-function-declaration.
5593  if (FTI.NumParams == 0 && !FTI.isVariadic && FTI.getLParenLoc().isValid())
5594  S.Diag(DeclType.Loc, diag::warn_strict_prototypes)
5595  << IsBlock
5596  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(FTI.getRParenLoc(), "void");
5597  IsBlock = false;
5598  break;
5599  }
5600  default:
5601  break;
5602  }
5603  }
5604  }
5605 
5606  assert(!T.isNull() && "T must not be null after this point");
5607 
5608  if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && T->isFunctionType()) {
5609  const FunctionProtoType *FnTy = T->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
5610  assert(FnTy && "Why oh why is there not a FunctionProtoType here?");
5611 
5612  // C++ 8.3.5p4:
5613  // A cv-qualifier-seq shall only be part of the function type
5614  // for a nonstatic member function, the function type to which a pointer
5615  // to member refers, or the top-level function type of a function typedef
5616  // declaration.
5617  //
5618  // Core issue 547 also allows cv-qualifiers on function types that are
5619  // top-level template type arguments.
5620  enum { NonMember, Member, DeductionGuide } Kind = NonMember;
5621  if (D.getName().getKind() == UnqualifiedIdKind::IK_DeductionGuideName)
5622  Kind = DeductionGuide;
5623  else if (!D.getCXXScopeSpec().isSet()) {
5624  if ((D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::Member ||
5625  D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr) &&
5626  !D.getDeclSpec().isFriendSpecified())
5627  Kind = Member;
5628  } else {
5629  DeclContext *DC = S.computeDeclContext(D.getCXXScopeSpec());
5630  if (!DC || DC->isRecord())
5631  Kind = Member;
5632  }
5633 
5634  // C++11 [dcl.fct]p6 (w/DR1417):
5635  // An attempt to specify a function type with a cv-qualifier-seq or a
5636  // ref-qualifier (including by typedef-name) is ill-formed unless it is:
5637  // - the function type for a non-static member function,
5638  // - the function type to which a pointer to member refers,
5639  // - the top-level function type of a function typedef declaration or
5640  // alias-declaration,
5641  // - the type-id in the default argument of a type-parameter, or
5642  // - the type-id of a template-argument for a type-parameter
5643  //
5644  // FIXME: Checking this here is insufficient. We accept-invalid on:
5645  //
5646  // template<typename T> struct S { void f(T); };
5647  // S<int() const> s;
5648  //
5649  // ... for instance.
5650  if (IsQualifiedFunction &&
5651  !(Kind == Member &&
5652  D.getDeclSpec().getStorageClassSpec() != DeclSpec::SCS_static) &&
5653  !IsTypedefName && D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::TemplateArg &&
5654  D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArg) {
5655  SourceLocation Loc = D.getBeginLoc();
5656  SourceRange RemovalRange;
5657  unsigned I;
5658  if (D.isFunctionDeclarator(I)) {
5659  SmallVector<SourceLocation, 4> RemovalLocs;
5660  const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk = D.getTypeObject(I);
5661  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Function);
5662 
5663  if (Chunk.Fun.hasRefQualifier())
5664  RemovalLocs.push_back(Chunk.Fun.getRefQualifierLoc());
5665 
5666  if (Chunk.Fun.hasMethodTypeQualifiers())
5667  Chunk.Fun.MethodQualifiers->forEachQualifier(
5668  [&](DeclSpec::TQ TypeQual, StringRef QualName,
5669  SourceLocation SL) { RemovalLocs.push_back(SL); });
5670 
5671  if (!RemovalLocs.empty()) {
5672  llvm::sort(RemovalLocs,
5673  BeforeThanCompare<SourceLocation>(S.getSourceManager()));
5674  RemovalRange = SourceRange(RemovalLocs.front(), RemovalLocs.back());
5675  Loc = RemovalLocs.front();
5676  }
5677  }
5678 
5679  S.Diag(Loc, diag::err_invalid_qualified_function_type)
5680  << Kind << D.isFunctionDeclarator() << T
5681  << getFunctionQualifiersAsString(FnTy)
5682  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(RemovalRange);
5683 
5684  // Strip the cv-qualifiers and ref-qualifiers from the type.
5685  FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FnTy->getExtProtoInfo();
5686  EPI.TypeQuals.removeCVRQualifiers();
5687  EPI.RefQualifier = RQ_None;
5688 
5689  T = Context.getFunctionType(FnTy->getReturnType(), FnTy->getParamTypes(),
5690  EPI);
5691  // Rebuild any parens around the identifier in the function type.
5692  for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
5693  if (D.getTypeObject(i).Kind != DeclaratorChunk::Paren)
5694  break;
5695  T = S.BuildParenType(T);
5696  }
5697  }
5698  }
5699 
5700  // Apply any undistributed attributes from the declarator.
5701  processTypeAttrs(state, T, TAL_DeclName, D.getAttributes());
5702 
5703  // Diagnose any ignored type attributes.
5704  state.diagnoseIgnoredTypeAttrs(T);
5705 
5706  // C++0x [dcl.constexpr]p9:
5707  // A constexpr specifier used in an object declaration declares the object
5708  // as const.
5709  if (D.getDeclSpec().getConstexprSpecifier() == ConstexprSpecKind::Constexpr &&
5710  T->isObjectType())
5711  T.addConst();
5712 
5713  // C++2a [dcl.fct]p4:
5714  // A parameter with volatile-qualified type is deprecated
5715  if (T.isVolatileQualified() && S.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 &&
5716  (D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::Prototype ||
5717  D.getContext() == DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameter))
5718  S.Diag(D.getIdentifierLoc(), diag::warn_deprecated_volatile_param) << T;
5719 
5720  // If there was an ellipsis in the declarator, the declaration declares a
5721  // parameter pack whose type may be a pack expansion type.
5722  if (D.hasEllipsis()) {
5723  // C++0x [dcl.fct]p13:
5724  // A declarator-id or abstract-declarator containing an ellipsis shall
5725  // only be used in a parameter-declaration. Such a parameter-declaration
5726  // is a parameter pack (14.5.3). [...]
5727  switch (D.getContext()) {
5728  case DeclaratorContext::Prototype:
5729  case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExprParameter:
5730  case DeclaratorContext::RequiresExpr:
5731  // C++0x [dcl.fct]p13:
5732  // [...] When it is part of a parameter-declaration-clause, the
5733  // parameter pack is a function parameter pack (14.5.3). The type T
5734  // of the declarator-id of the function parameter pack shall contain
5735  // a template parameter pack; each template parameter pack in T is
5736  // expanded by the function parameter pack.
5737  //
5738  // We represent function parameter packs as function parameters whose
5739  // type is a pack expansion.
5740  if (!T->containsUnexpandedParameterPack() &&
5741  (!LangOpts.CPlusPlus20 || !T->getContainedAutoType())) {
5742  S.Diag(D.getEllipsisLoc(),
5743  diag::err_function_parameter_pack_without_parameter_packs)
5744  << T << D.getSourceRange();
5745  D.setEllipsisLoc(SourceLocation());
5746  } else {
5747  T = Context.getPackExpansionType(T, None, /*ExpectPackInType=*/false);
5748  }
5749  break;
5750  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateParam:
5751  // C++0x [temp.param]p15:
5752  // If a template-parameter is a [...] is a parameter-declaration that
5753  // declares a parameter pack (8.3.5), then the template-parameter is a
5754  // template parameter pack (14.5.3).
5755  //
5756  // Note: core issue 778 clarifies that, if there are any unexpanded
5757  // parameter packs in the type of the non-type template parameter, then
5758  // it expands those parameter packs.
5759  if (T->containsUnexpandedParameterPack())
5760  T = Context.getPackExpansionType(T, None);
5761  else
5762  S.Diag(D.getEllipsisLoc(),
5763  LangOpts.CPlusPlus11
5764  ? diag::warn_cxx98_compat_variadic_templates
5765  : diag::ext_variadic_templates);
5766  break;
5767 
5768  case DeclaratorContext::File:
5769  case DeclaratorContext::KNRTypeList:
5770  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameter: // FIXME: special diagnostic here?
5771  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCResult: // FIXME: special diagnostic here?
5772  case DeclaratorContext::TypeName:
5773  case DeclaratorContext::FunctionalCast:
5774  case DeclaratorContext::CXXNew:
5775  case DeclaratorContext::AliasDecl:
5776  case DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplate:
5777  case DeclaratorContext::Member:
5778  case DeclaratorContext::Block:
5779  case DeclaratorContext::ForInit:
5780  case DeclaratorContext::SelectionInit:
5781  case DeclaratorContext::Condition:
5782  case DeclaratorContext::CXXCatch:
5783  case DeclaratorContext::ObjCCatch:
5784  case DeclaratorContext::BlockLiteral:
5785  case DeclaratorContext::LambdaExpr:
5786  case DeclaratorContext::ConversionId:
5787  case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturn:
5788  case DeclaratorContext::TrailingReturnVar:
5789  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateArg:
5790  case DeclaratorContext::TemplateTypeArg:
5791  // FIXME: We may want to allow parameter packs in block-literal contexts
5792  // in the future.
5793  S.Diag(D.getEllipsisLoc(),
5794  diag::err_ellipsis_in_declarator_not_parameter);
5795  D.setEllipsisLoc(SourceLocation());
5796  break;
5797  }
5798  }
5799 
5800  assert(!T.isNull() && "T must not be null at the end of this function");
5801  if (D.isInvalidType())
5802  return Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T);
5803 
5804  return GetTypeSourceInfoForDeclarator(state, T, TInfo);
5805 }
5806 
5807 /// GetTypeForDeclarator - Convert the type for the specified
5808 /// declarator to Type instances.
5809 ///
5810 /// The result of this call will never be null, but the associated
5811 /// type may be a null type if there's an unrecoverable error.
5812 TypeSourceInfo *Sema::GetTypeForDeclarator(Declarator &D, Scope *S) {
5813  // Determine the type of the declarator. Not all forms of declarator
5814  // have a type.
5815 
5816  TypeProcessingState state(*this, D);
5817 
5818  TypeSourceInfo *ReturnTypeInfo = nullptr;
5819  QualType T = GetDeclSpecTypeForDeclarator(state, ReturnTypeInfo);
5820  if (D.isPrototypeContext() && getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount)
5821  inferARCWriteback(state, T);
5822 
5823  return GetFullTypeForDeclarator(state, T, ReturnTypeInfo);
5824 }
5825 
5826 static void transferARCOwnershipToDeclSpec(Sema &S,
5827  QualType &declSpecTy,
5828  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership) {
5829  if (declSpecTy->isObjCRetainableType() &&
5830  declSpecTy.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_None) {
5831  Qualifiers qs;
5832  qs.addObjCLifetime(ownership);
5833  declSpecTy = S.Context.getQualifiedType(declSpecTy, qs);
5834  }
5835 }
5836 
5837 static void transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(TypeProcessingState &state,
5838  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership,
5839  unsigned chunkIndex) {
5840  Sema &S = state.getSema();
5841  Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
5842 
5843  // Look for an explicit lifetime attribute.
5844  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = D.getTypeObject(chunkIndex);
5845  if (chunk.getAttrs().hasAttribute(ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership))
5846  return;
5847 
5848  const char *attrStr = nullptr;
5849  switch (ownership) {
5850  case Qualifiers::OCL_None: llvm_unreachable("no ownership!");
5851  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone: attrStr = "none"; break;
5852  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong: attrStr = "strong"; break;
5853  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak: attrStr = "weak"; break;
5854  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing: attrStr = "autoreleasing"; break;
5855  }
5856 
5857  IdentifierLoc *Arg = new (S.Context) IdentifierLoc;
5858  Arg->Ident = &S.Context.Idents.get(attrStr);
5859  Arg->Loc = SourceLocation();
5860 
5861  ArgsUnion Args(Arg);
5862 
5863  // If there wasn't one, add one (with an invalid source location
5864  // so that we don't make an AttributedType for it).
5865  ParsedAttr *attr = D.getAttributePool().create(
5866  &S.Context.Idents.get("objc_ownership"), SourceLocation(),
5867  /*scope*/ nullptr, SourceLocation(),
5868  /*args*/ &Args, 1, ParsedAttr::AS_GNU);
5869  chunk.getAttrs().addAtEnd(attr);
5870  // TODO: mark whether we did this inference?
5871 }
5872 
5873 /// Used for transferring ownership in casts resulting in l-values.
5874 static void transferARCOwnership(TypeProcessingState &state,
5875  QualType &declSpecTy,
5876  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership) {
5877  Sema &S = state.getSema();
5878  Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
5879 
5880  int inner = -1;
5881  bool hasIndirection = false;
5882  for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
5883  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = D.getTypeObject(i);
5884  switch (chunk.Kind) {
5885  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
5886  // Ignore parens.
5887  break;
5888 
5889  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
5890  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
5891  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
5892  if (inner != -1)
5893  hasIndirection = true;
5894  inner = i;
5895  break;
5896 
5897  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
5898  if (inner != -1)
5899  transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(state, ownership, i);
5900  return;
5901 
5902  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
5903  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
5904  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
5905  return;
5906  }
5907  }
5908 
5909  if (inner == -1)
5910  return;
5911 
5912  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = D.getTypeObject(inner);
5913  if (chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer) {
5914  if (declSpecTy->isObjCRetainableType())
5915  return transferARCOwnershipToDeclSpec(S, declSpecTy, ownership);
5916  if (declSpecTy->isObjCObjectType() && hasIndirection)
5917  return transferARCOwnershipToDeclaratorChunk(state, ownership, inner);
5918  } else {
5919  assert(chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Array ||
5920  chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Reference);
5921  return transferARCOwnershipToDeclSpec(S, declSpecTy, ownership);
5922  }
5923 }
5924 
5925 TypeSourceInfo *Sema::GetTypeForDeclaratorCast(Declarator &D, QualType FromTy) {
5926  TypeProcessingState state(*this, D);
5927 
5928  TypeSourceInfo *ReturnTypeInfo = nullptr;
5929  QualType declSpecTy = GetDeclSpecTypeForDeclarator(state, ReturnTypeInfo);
5930 
5931  if (getLangOpts().ObjC) {
5932  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ownership = Context.getInnerObjCOwnership(FromTy);
5933  if (ownership != Qualifiers::OCL_None)
5934  transferARCOwnership(state, declSpecTy, ownership);
5935  }
5936 
5937  return GetFullTypeForDeclarator(state, declSpecTy, ReturnTypeInfo);
5938 }
5939 
5940 static void fillAttributedTypeLoc(AttributedTypeLoc TL,
5941  TypeProcessingState &State) {
5942  TL.setAttr(State.takeAttrForAttributedType(TL.getTypePtr()));
5943 }
5944 
5945 namespace {
5946  class TypeSpecLocFiller : public TypeLocVisitor<TypeSpecLocFiller> {
5947  Sema &SemaRef;
5948  ASTContext &Context;
5949  TypeProcessingState &State;
5950  const DeclSpec &DS;
5951 
5952  public:
5953  TypeSpecLocFiller(Sema &S, ASTContext &Context, TypeProcessingState &State,
5954  const DeclSpec &DS)
5955  : SemaRef(S), Context(Context), State(State), DS(DS) {}
5956 
5957  void VisitAttributedTypeLoc(AttributedTypeLoc TL) {
5958  Visit(TL.getModifiedLoc());
5959  fillAttributedTypeLoc(TL, State);
5960  }
5961  void VisitBTFTagAttributedTypeLoc(BTFTagAttributedTypeLoc TL) {
5962  Visit(TL.getWrappedLoc());
5963  }
5964  void VisitMacroQualifiedTypeLoc(MacroQualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
5965  Visit(TL.getInnerLoc());
5966  TL.setExpansionLoc(
5967  State.getExpansionLocForMacroQualifiedType(TL.getTypePtr()));
5968  }
5969  void VisitQualifiedTypeLoc(QualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
5970  Visit(TL.getUnqualifiedLoc());
5971  }
5972  // Allow to fill pointee's type locations, e.g.,
5973  // int __attr * __attr * __attr *p;
5974  void VisitPointerTypeLoc(PointerTypeLoc TL) { Visit(TL.getNextTypeLoc()); }
5975  void VisitTypedefTypeLoc(TypedefTypeLoc TL) {
5976  TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5977  }
5978  void VisitObjCInterfaceTypeLoc(ObjCInterfaceTypeLoc TL) {
5979  TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
5980  // FIXME. We should have DS.getTypeSpecTypeEndLoc(). But, it requires
5981  // addition field. What we have is good enough for display of location
5982  // of 'fixit' on interface name.
5983  TL.setNameEndLoc(DS.getEndLoc());
5984  }
5985  void VisitObjCObjectTypeLoc(ObjCObjectTypeLoc TL) {
5986  TypeSourceInfo *RepTInfo = nullptr;
5987  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &RepTInfo);
5988  TL.copy(RepTInfo->getTypeLoc());
5989  }
5990  void VisitObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc(ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc TL) {
5991  TypeSourceInfo *RepTInfo = nullptr;
5992  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &RepTInfo);
5993  TL.copy(RepTInfo->getTypeLoc());
5994  }
5995  void VisitTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc(TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL) {
5996  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
5997  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
5998 
5999  // If we got no declarator info from previous Sema routines,
6000  // just fill with the typespec loc.
6001  if (!TInfo) {
6002  TL.initialize(Context, DS.getTypeSpecTypeNameLoc());
6003  return;
6004  }
6005 
6006  TypeLoc OldTL = TInfo->getTypeLoc();
6007  if (TInfo->getType()->getAs<ElaboratedType>()) {
6008  ElaboratedTypeLoc ElabTL = OldTL.castAs<ElaboratedTypeLoc>();
6009  TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc NamedTL = ElabTL.getNamedTypeLoc()
6010  .castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>();
6011  TL.copy(NamedTL);
6012  } else {
6013  TL.copy(OldTL.castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>());
6014  assert(TL.getRAngleLoc() == OldTL.castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>().getRAngleLoc());
6015  }
6016 
6017  }
6018  void VisitTypeOfExprTypeLoc(TypeOfExprTypeLoc TL) {
6019  assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_typeofExpr);
6020  TL.setTypeofLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6021  TL.setParensRange(DS.getTypeofParensRange());
6022  }
6023  void VisitTypeOfTypeLoc(TypeOfTypeLoc TL) {
6024  assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_typeofType);
6025  TL.setTypeofLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6026  TL.setParensRange(DS.getTypeofParensRange());
6027  assert(DS.getRepAsType());
6028  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
6029  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
6030  TL.setUnderlyingTInfo(TInfo);
6031  }
6032  void VisitDecltypeTypeLoc(DecltypeTypeLoc TL) {
6033  assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_decltype);
6034  TL.setDecltypeLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6035  TL.setRParenLoc(DS.getTypeofParensRange().getEnd());
6036  }
6037  void VisitUnaryTransformTypeLoc(UnaryTransformTypeLoc TL) {
6038  // FIXME: This holds only because we only have one unary transform.
6039  assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_underlyingType);
6040  TL.setKWLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6041  TL.setParensRange(DS.getTypeofParensRange());
6042  assert(DS.getRepAsType());
6043  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
6044  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
6045  TL.setUnderlyingTInfo(TInfo);
6046  }
6047  void VisitBuiltinTypeLoc(BuiltinTypeLoc TL) {
6048  // By default, use the source location of the type specifier.
6049  TL.setBuiltinLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6050  if (TL.needsExtraLocalData()) {
6051  // Set info for the written builtin specifiers.
6052  TL.getWrittenBuiltinSpecs() = DS.getWrittenBuiltinSpecs();
6053  // Try to have a meaningful source location.
6054  if (TL.getWrittenSignSpec() != TypeSpecifierSign::Unspecified)
6055  TL.expandBuiltinRange(DS.getTypeSpecSignLoc());
6056  if (TL.getWrittenWidthSpec() != TypeSpecifierWidth::Unspecified)
6057  TL.expandBuiltinRange(DS.getTypeSpecWidthRange());
6058  }
6059  }
6060  void VisitElaboratedTypeLoc(ElaboratedTypeLoc TL) {
6061  ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword
6062  = TypeWithKeyword::getKeywordForTypeSpec(DS.getTypeSpecType());
6063  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_typename) {
6064  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
6065  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
6066  if (TInfo) {
6067  TL.copy(TInfo->getTypeLoc().castAs<ElaboratedTypeLoc>());
6068  return;
6069  }
6070  }
6071  TL.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(Keyword != ETK_None
6072  ? DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc()
6073  : SourceLocation());
6074  const CXXScopeSpec& SS = DS.getTypeSpecScope();
6075  TL.setQualifierLoc(SS.getWithLocInContext(Context));
6076  Visit(TL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc());
6077  }
6078  void VisitDependentNameTypeLoc(DependentNameTypeLoc TL) {
6079  assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_typename);
6080  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
6081  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
6082  assert(TInfo);
6083  TL.copy(TInfo->getTypeLoc().castAs<DependentNameTypeLoc>());
6084  }
6085  void VisitDependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc(
6086  DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL) {
6087  assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_typename);
6088  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
6089  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
6090  assert(TInfo);
6091  TL.copy(
6092  TInfo->getTypeLoc().castAs<DependentTemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>());
6093  }
6094  void VisitAutoTypeLoc(AutoTypeLoc TL) {
6095  assert(DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_auto ||
6096  DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_decltype_auto ||
6097  DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_auto_type ||
6098  DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_unspecified);
6099  TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6100  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == TST_decltype_auto)
6101  TL.setRParenLoc(DS.getTypeofParensRange().getEnd());
6102  if (!DS.isConstrainedAuto())
6103  return;
6104  TemplateIdAnnotation *TemplateId = DS.getRepAsTemplateId();
6105  if (!TemplateId)
6106  return;
6107  if (DS.getTypeSpecScope().isNotEmpty())
6108  TL.setNestedNameSpecifierLoc(
6109  DS.getTypeSpecScope().getWithLocInContext(Context));
6110  else
6111  TL.setNestedNameSpecifierLoc(NestedNameSpecifierLoc());
6112  TL.setTemplateKWLoc(TemplateId->TemplateKWLoc);
6113  TL.setConceptNameLoc(TemplateId->TemplateNameLoc);
6114  TL.setFoundDecl(nullptr);
6115  TL.setLAngleLoc(TemplateId->LAngleLoc);
6116  TL.setRAngleLoc(TemplateId->RAngleLoc);
6117  if (TemplateId->NumArgs == 0)
6118  return;
6119  TemplateArgumentListInfo TemplateArgsInfo;
6120  ASTTemplateArgsPtr TemplateArgsPtr(TemplateId->getTemplateArgs(),
6121  TemplateId->NumArgs);
6122  SemaRef.translateTemplateArguments(TemplateArgsPtr, TemplateArgsInfo);
6123  for (unsigned I = 0; I < TemplateId->NumArgs; ++I)
6124  TL.setArgLocInfo(I, TemplateArgsInfo.arguments()[I].getLocInfo());
6125  }
6126  void VisitTagTypeLoc(TagTypeLoc TL) {
6127  TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeNameLoc());
6128  }
6129  void VisitAtomicTypeLoc(AtomicTypeLoc TL) {
6130  // An AtomicTypeLoc can come from either an _Atomic(...) type specifier
6131  // or an _Atomic qualifier.
6132  if (DS.getTypeSpecType() == DeclSpec::TST_atomic) {
6133  TL.setKWLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6134  TL.setParensRange(DS.getTypeofParensRange());
6135 
6136  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
6137  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
