6138  assert(TInfo);
6139  TL.getValueLoc().initializeFullCopy(TInfo->getTypeLoc());
6140  } else {
6141  TL.setKWLoc(DS.getAtomicSpecLoc());
6142  // No parens, to indicate this was spelled as an _Atomic qualifier.
6143  TL.setParensRange(SourceRange());
6144  Visit(TL.getValueLoc());
6145  }
6146  }
6147 
6148  void VisitPipeTypeLoc(PipeTypeLoc TL) {
6149  TL.setKWLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6150 
6151  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = nullptr;
6152  Sema::GetTypeFromParser(DS.getRepAsType(), &TInfo);
6153  TL.getValueLoc().initializeFullCopy(TInfo->getTypeLoc());
6154  }
6155 
6156  void VisitExtIntTypeLoc(BitIntTypeLoc TL) {
6157  TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6158  }
6159 
6160  void VisitDependentExtIntTypeLoc(DependentBitIntTypeLoc TL) {
6161  TL.setNameLoc(DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6162  }
6163 
6164  void VisitTypeLoc(TypeLoc TL) {
6165  // FIXME: add other typespec types and change this to an assert.
6166  TL.initialize(Context, DS.getTypeSpecTypeLoc());
6167  }
6168  };
6169 
6170  class DeclaratorLocFiller : public TypeLocVisitor<DeclaratorLocFiller> {
6171  ASTContext &Context;
6172  TypeProcessingState &State;
6173  const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk;
6174 
6175  public:
6176  DeclaratorLocFiller(ASTContext &Context, TypeProcessingState &State,
6177  const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk)
6178  : Context(Context), State(State), Chunk(Chunk) {}
6179 
6180  void VisitQualifiedTypeLoc(QualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
6181  llvm_unreachable("qualified type locs not expected here!");
6182  }
6183  void VisitDecayedTypeLoc(DecayedTypeLoc TL) {
6184  llvm_unreachable("decayed type locs not expected here!");
6185  }
6186 
6187  void VisitAttributedTypeLoc(AttributedTypeLoc TL) {
6188  fillAttributedTypeLoc(TL, State);
6189  }
6190  void VisitBTFTagAttributedTypeLoc(BTFTagAttributedTypeLoc TL) {
6191  // nothing
6192  }
6193  void VisitAdjustedTypeLoc(AdjustedTypeLoc TL) {
6194  // nothing
6195  }
6196  void VisitBlockPointerTypeLoc(BlockPointerTypeLoc TL) {
6197  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer);
6198  TL.setCaretLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6199  }
6200  void VisitPointerTypeLoc(PointerTypeLoc TL) {
6201  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer);
6202  TL.setStarLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6203  }
6204  void VisitObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc(ObjCObjectPointerTypeLoc TL) {
6205  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer);
6206  TL.setStarLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6207  }
6208  void VisitMemberPointerTypeLoc(MemberPointerTypeLoc TL) {
6209  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer);
6210  const CXXScopeSpec& SS = Chunk.Mem.Scope();
6211  NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNSLoc = SS.getWithLocInContext(Context);
6212 
6213  const Type* ClsTy = TL.getClass();
6214  QualType ClsQT = QualType(ClsTy, 0);
6215  TypeSourceInfo *ClsTInfo = Context.CreateTypeSourceInfo(ClsQT, 0);
6216  // Now copy source location info into the type loc component.
6217  TypeLoc ClsTL = ClsTInfo->getTypeLoc();
6218  switch (NNSLoc.getNestedNameSpecifier()->getKind()) {
6219  case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
6220  assert(isa<DependentNameType>(ClsTy) && "Unexpected TypeLoc");
6221  {
6222  DependentNameTypeLoc DNTLoc = ClsTL.castAs<DependentNameTypeLoc>();
6223  DNTLoc.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(SourceLocation());
6224  DNTLoc.setQualifierLoc(NNSLoc.getPrefix());
6225  DNTLoc.setNameLoc(NNSLoc.getLocalBeginLoc());
6226  }
6227  break;
6228 
6229  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
6230  case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate:
6231  if (isa<ElaboratedType>(ClsTy)) {
6232  ElaboratedTypeLoc ETLoc = ClsTL.castAs<ElaboratedTypeLoc>();
6233  ETLoc.setElaboratedKeywordLoc(SourceLocation());
6234  ETLoc.setQualifierLoc(NNSLoc.getPrefix());
6235  TypeLoc NamedTL = ETLoc.getNamedTypeLoc();
6236  NamedTL.initializeFullCopy(NNSLoc.getTypeLoc());
6237  } else {
6238  ClsTL.initializeFullCopy(NNSLoc.getTypeLoc());
6239  }
6240  break;
6241 
6242  case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
6243  case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
6244  case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
6245  case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
6246  llvm_unreachable("Nested-name-specifier must name a type");
6247  }
6248 
6249  // Finally fill in MemberPointerLocInfo fields.
6250  TL.setStarLoc(Chunk.Mem.StarLoc);
6251  TL.setClassTInfo(ClsTInfo);
6252  }
6253  void VisitLValueReferenceTypeLoc(LValueReferenceTypeLoc TL) {
6254  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Reference);
6255  // 'Amp' is misleading: this might have been originally
6256  /// spelled with AmpAmp.
6257  TL.setAmpLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6258  }
6259  void VisitRValueReferenceTypeLoc(RValueReferenceTypeLoc TL) {
6260  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Reference);
6261  assert(!Chunk.Ref.LValueRef);
6262  TL.setAmpAmpLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6263  }
6264  void VisitArrayTypeLoc(ArrayTypeLoc TL) {
6265  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Array);
6266  TL.setLBracketLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6267  TL.setRBracketLoc(Chunk.EndLoc);
6268  TL.setSizeExpr(static_cast<Expr*>(Chunk.Arr.NumElts));
6269  }
6270  void VisitFunctionTypeLoc(FunctionTypeLoc TL) {
6271  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Function);
6272  TL.setLocalRangeBegin(Chunk.Loc);
6273  TL.setLocalRangeEnd(Chunk.EndLoc);
6274 
6275  const DeclaratorChunk::FunctionTypeInfo &FTI = Chunk.Fun;
6276  TL.setLParenLoc(FTI.getLParenLoc());
6277  TL.setRParenLoc(FTI.getRParenLoc());
6278  for (unsigned i = 0, e = TL.getNumParams(), tpi = 0; i != e; ++i) {
6279  ParmVarDecl *Param = cast<ParmVarDecl>(FTI.Params[i].Param);
6280  TL.setParam(tpi++, Param);
6281  }
6282  TL.setExceptionSpecRange(FTI.getExceptionSpecRange());
6283  }
6284  void VisitParenTypeLoc(ParenTypeLoc TL) {
6285  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Paren);
6286  TL.setLParenLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6287  TL.setRParenLoc(Chunk.EndLoc);
6288  }
6289  void VisitPipeTypeLoc(PipeTypeLoc TL) {
6290  assert(Chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pipe);
6291  TL.setKWLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6292  }
6293  void VisitBitIntTypeLoc(BitIntTypeLoc TL) {
6294  TL.setNameLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6295  }
6296  void VisitMacroQualifiedTypeLoc(MacroQualifiedTypeLoc TL) {
6297  TL.setExpansionLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6298  }
6299  void VisitVectorTypeLoc(VectorTypeLoc TL) { TL.setNameLoc(Chunk.Loc); }
6300  void VisitDependentVectorTypeLoc(DependentVectorTypeLoc TL) {
6301  TL.setNameLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6302  }
6303  void VisitExtVectorTypeLoc(ExtVectorTypeLoc TL) {
6304  TL.setNameLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6305  }
6306  void
6307  VisitDependentSizedExtVectorTypeLoc(DependentSizedExtVectorTypeLoc TL) {
6308  TL.setNameLoc(Chunk.Loc);
6309  }
6310 
6311  void VisitTypeLoc(TypeLoc TL) {
6312  llvm_unreachable("unsupported TypeLoc kind in declarator!");
6313  }
6314  };
6315 } // end anonymous namespace
6316 
6317 static void fillAtomicQualLoc(AtomicTypeLoc ATL, const DeclaratorChunk &Chunk) {
6318  SourceLocation Loc;
6319  switch (Chunk.Kind) {
6320  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
6321  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
6322  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
6323  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
6324  llvm_unreachable("cannot be _Atomic qualified");
6325 
6326  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
6327  Loc = Chunk.Ptr.AtomicQualLoc;
6328  break;
6329 
6330  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
6331  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
6332  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
6333  // FIXME: Provide a source location for the _Atomic keyword.
6334  break;
6335  }
6336 
6337  ATL.setKWLoc(Loc);
6338  ATL.setParensRange(SourceRange());
6339 }
6340 
6341 static void
6342 fillDependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc(DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc DASTL,
6343  const ParsedAttributesView &Attrs) {
6344  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : Attrs) {
6345  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_AddressSpace) {
6346  DASTL.setAttrNameLoc(AL.getLoc());
6347  DASTL.setAttrExprOperand(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
6348  DASTL.setAttrOperandParensRange(SourceRange());
6349  return;
6350  }
6351  }
6352 
6353  llvm_unreachable(
6354  "no address_space attribute found at the expected location!");
6355 }
6356 
6357 static void fillMatrixTypeLoc(MatrixTypeLoc MTL,
6358  const ParsedAttributesView &Attrs) {
6359  for (const ParsedAttr &AL : Attrs) {
6360  if (AL.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_MatrixType) {
6361  MTL.setAttrNameLoc(AL.getLoc());
6362  MTL.setAttrRowOperand(AL.getArgAsExpr(0));
6363  MTL.setAttrColumnOperand(AL.getArgAsExpr(1));
6364  MTL.setAttrOperandParensRange(SourceRange());
6365  return;
6366  }
6367  }
6368 
6369  llvm_unreachable("no matrix_type attribute found at the expected location!");
6370 }
6371 
6372 /// Create and instantiate a TypeSourceInfo with type source information.
6373 ///
6374 /// \param T QualType referring to the type as written in source code.
6375 ///
6376 /// \param ReturnTypeInfo For declarators whose return type does not show
6377 /// up in the normal place in the declaration specifiers (such as a C++
6378 /// conversion function), this pointer will refer to a type source information
6379 /// for that return type.
6380 static TypeSourceInfo *
6381 GetTypeSourceInfoForDeclarator(TypeProcessingState &State,
6382  QualType T, TypeSourceInfo *ReturnTypeInfo) {
6383  Sema &S = State.getSema();
6384  Declarator &D = State.getDeclarator();
6385 
6386  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = S.Context.CreateTypeSourceInfo(T);
6387  UnqualTypeLoc CurrTL = TInfo->getTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
6388 
6389  // Handle parameter packs whose type is a pack expansion.
6390  if (isa<PackExpansionType>(T)) {
6391  CurrTL.castAs<PackExpansionTypeLoc>().setEllipsisLoc(D.getEllipsisLoc());
6392  CurrTL = CurrTL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
6393  }
6394 
6395  for (unsigned i = 0, e = D.getNumTypeObjects(); i != e; ++i) {
6396  // An AtomicTypeLoc might be produced by an atomic qualifier in this
6397  // declarator chunk.
6398  if (AtomicTypeLoc ATL = CurrTL.getAs<AtomicTypeLoc>()) {
6399  fillAtomicQualLoc(ATL, D.getTypeObject(i));
6400  CurrTL = ATL.getValueLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
6401  }
6402 
6403  while (MacroQualifiedTypeLoc TL = CurrTL.getAs<MacroQualifiedTypeLoc>()) {
6404  TL.setExpansionLoc(
6405  State.getExpansionLocForMacroQualifiedType(TL.getTypePtr()));
6406  CurrTL = TL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
6407  }
6408 
6409  while (AttributedTypeLoc TL = CurrTL.getAs<AttributedTypeLoc>()) {
6410  fillAttributedTypeLoc(TL, State);
6411  CurrTL = TL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
6412  }
6413 
6414  while (DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc TL =
6415  CurrTL.getAs<DependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc>()) {
6416  fillDependentAddressSpaceTypeLoc(TL, D.getTypeObject(i).getAttrs());
6417  CurrTL = TL.getPointeeTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
6418  }
6419 
6420  if (MatrixTypeLoc TL = CurrTL.getAs<MatrixTypeLoc>())
6421  fillMatrixTypeLoc(TL, D.getTypeObject(i).getAttrs());
6422 
6423  // FIXME: Ordering here?
6424  while (AdjustedTypeLoc TL = CurrTL.getAs<AdjustedTypeLoc>())
6425  CurrTL = TL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
6426 
6427  DeclaratorLocFiller(S.Context, State, D.getTypeObject(i)).Visit(CurrTL);
6428  CurrTL = CurrTL.getNextTypeLoc().getUnqualifiedLoc();
6429  }
6430 
6431  // If we have different source information for the return type, use
6432  // that. This really only applies to C++ conversion functions.
6433  if (ReturnTypeInfo) {
6434  TypeLoc TL = ReturnTypeInfo->getTypeLoc();
6435  assert(TL.getFullDataSize() == CurrTL.getFullDataSize());
6436  memcpy(CurrTL.getOpaqueData(), TL.getOpaqueData(), TL.getFullDataSize());
6437  } else {
6438  TypeSpecLocFiller(S, S.Context, State, D.getDeclSpec()).Visit(CurrTL);
6439  }
6440 
6441  return TInfo;
6442 }
6443 
6444 /// Create a LocInfoType to hold the given QualType and TypeSourceInfo.
6445 ParsedType Sema::CreateParsedType(QualType T, TypeSourceInfo *TInfo) {
6446  // FIXME: LocInfoTypes are "transient", only needed for passing to/from Parser
6447  // and Sema during declaration parsing. Try deallocating/caching them when
6448  // it's appropriate, instead of allocating them and keeping them around.
6449  LocInfoType *LocT = (LocInfoType*)BumpAlloc.Allocate(sizeof(LocInfoType),
6450  TypeAlignment);
6451  new (LocT) LocInfoType(T, TInfo);
6452  assert(LocT->getTypeClass() != T->getTypeClass() &&
6453  "LocInfoType's TypeClass conflicts with an existing Type class");
6454  return ParsedType::make(QualType(LocT, 0));
6455 }
6456 
6457 void LocInfoType::getAsStringInternal(std::string &Str,
6458  const PrintingPolicy &Policy) const {
6459  llvm_unreachable("LocInfoType leaked into the type system; an opaque TypeTy*"
6460  " was used directly instead of getting the QualType through"
6461  " GetTypeFromParser");
6462 }
6463 
6464 TypeResult Sema::ActOnTypeName(Scope *S, Declarator &D) {
6465  // C99 6.7.6: Type names have no identifier. This is already validated by
6466  // the parser.
6467  assert(D.getIdentifier() == nullptr &&
6468  "Type name should have no identifier!");
6469 
6470  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = GetTypeForDeclarator(D, S);
6471  QualType T = TInfo->getType();
6472  if (D.isInvalidType())
6473  return true;
6474 
6475  // Make sure there are no unused decl attributes on the declarator.
6476  // We don't want to do this for ObjC parameters because we're going
6477  // to apply them to the actual parameter declaration.
6478  // Likewise, we don't want to do this for alias declarations, because
6479  // we are actually going to build a declaration from this eventually.
6480  if (D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::ObjCParameter &&
6481  D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::AliasDecl &&
6482  D.getContext() != DeclaratorContext::AliasTemplate)
6483  checkUnusedDeclAttributes(D);
6484 
6485  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
6486  // Check that there are no default arguments (C++ only).
6487  CheckExtraCXXDefaultArguments(D);
6488  }
6489 
6490  return CreateParsedType(T, TInfo);
6491 }
6492 
6493 ParsedType Sema::ActOnObjCInstanceType(SourceLocation Loc) {
6494  QualType T = Context.getObjCInstanceType();
6495  TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = Context.getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T, Loc);
6496  return CreateParsedType(T, TInfo);
6497 }
6498 
6499 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6500 // Type Attribute Processing
6501 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6502 
6503 /// Build an AddressSpace index from a constant expression and diagnose any
6504 /// errors related to invalid address_spaces. Returns true on successfully
6505 /// building an AddressSpace index.
6506 static bool BuildAddressSpaceIndex(Sema &S, LangAS &ASIdx,
6507  const Expr *AddrSpace,
6508  SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
6509  if (!AddrSpace->isValueDependent()) {
6510  Optional<llvm::APSInt> OptAddrSpace =
6511  AddrSpace->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context);
6512  if (!OptAddrSpace) {
6513  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
6514  << "'address_space'" << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant
6515  << AddrSpace->getSourceRange();
6516  return false;
6517  }
6518  llvm::APSInt &addrSpace = *OptAddrSpace;
6519 
6520  // Bounds checking.
6521  if (addrSpace.isSigned()) {
6522  if (addrSpace.isNegative()) {
6523  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_address_space_negative)
6524  << AddrSpace->getSourceRange();
6525  return false;
6526  }
6527  addrSpace.setIsSigned(false);
6528  }
6529 
6530  llvm::APSInt max(addrSpace.getBitWidth());
6531  max =
6532  Qualifiers::MaxAddressSpace - (unsigned)LangAS::FirstTargetAddressSpace;
6533 
6534  if (addrSpace > max) {
6535  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_address_space_too_high)
6536  << (unsigned)max.getZExtValue() << AddrSpace->getSourceRange();
6537  return false;
6538  }
6539 
6540  ASIdx =
6541  getLangASFromTargetAS(static_cast<unsigned>(addrSpace.getZExtValue()));
6542  return true;
6543  }
6544 
6545  // Default value for DependentAddressSpaceTypes
6546  ASIdx = LangAS::Default;
6547  return true;
6548 }
6549 
6550 /// BuildAddressSpaceAttr - Builds a DependentAddressSpaceType if an expression
6551 /// is uninstantiated. If instantiated it will apply the appropriate address
6552 /// space to the type. This function allows dependent template variables to be
6553 /// used in conjunction with the address_space attribute
6554 QualType Sema::BuildAddressSpaceAttr(QualType &T, LangAS ASIdx, Expr *AddrSpace,
6555  SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
6556  if (!AddrSpace->isValueDependent()) {
6557  if (DiagnoseMultipleAddrSpaceAttributes(*this, T.getAddressSpace(), ASIdx,
6558  AttrLoc))
6559  return QualType();
6560 
6561  return Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(T, ASIdx);
6562  }
6563 
6564  // A check with similar intentions as checking if a type already has an
6565  // address space except for on a dependent types, basically if the
6566  // current type is already a DependentAddressSpaceType then its already
6567  // lined up to have another address space on it and we can't have
6568  // multiple address spaces on the one pointer indirection
6569  if (T->getAs<DependentAddressSpaceType>()) {
6570  Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_address_multiple_qualifiers);
6571  return QualType();
6572  }
6573 
6574  return Context.getDependentAddressSpaceType(T, AddrSpace, AttrLoc);
6575 }
6576 
6577 QualType Sema::BuildAddressSpaceAttr(QualType &T, Expr *AddrSpace,
6578  SourceLocation AttrLoc) {
6579  LangAS ASIdx;
6580  if (!BuildAddressSpaceIndex(*this, ASIdx, AddrSpace, AttrLoc))
6581  return QualType();
6582  return BuildAddressSpaceAttr(T, ASIdx, AddrSpace, AttrLoc);
6583 }
6584 
6585 static void HandleBTFTypeTagAttribute(QualType &Type, const ParsedAttr &Attr,
6586  TypeProcessingState &State) {
6587  Sema &S = State.getSema();
6588 
6589  // Check the number of attribute arguments.
6590  if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
6591  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
6592  << Attr << 1;
6593  Attr.setInvalid();
6594  return;
6595  }
6596 
6597  // Ensure the argument is a string.
6598  auto *StrLiteral = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(Attr.getArgAsExpr(0));
6599  if (!StrLiteral) {
6600  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
6601  << Attr << AANT_ArgumentString;
6602  Attr.setInvalid();
6603  return;
6604  }
6605 
6606  ASTContext &Ctx = S.Context;
6607  StringRef BTFTypeTag = StrLiteral->getString();
6608  Type = State.getBTFTagAttributedType(
6609  ::new (Ctx) BTFTypeTagAttr(Ctx, Attr, BTFTypeTag), Type);
6610 }
6611 
6612 /// HandleAddressSpaceTypeAttribute - Process an address_space attribute on the
6613 /// specified type. The attribute contains 1 argument, the id of the address
6614 /// space for the type.
6615 static void HandleAddressSpaceTypeAttribute(QualType &Type,
6616  const ParsedAttr &Attr,
6617  TypeProcessingState &State) {
6618  Sema &S = State.getSema();
6619 
6620  // ISO/IEC TR 18037 S5.3 (amending C99 6.7.3): "A function type shall not be
6621  // qualified by an address-space qualifier."
6622  if (Type->isFunctionType()) {
6623  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_address_function_type);
6624  Attr.setInvalid();
6625  return;
6626  }
6627 
6628  LangAS ASIdx;
6629  if (Attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_AddressSpace) {
6630 
6631  // Check the attribute arguments.
6632  if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
6633  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << Attr
6634  << 1;
6635  Attr.setInvalid();
6636  return;
6637  }
6638 
6639  Expr *ASArgExpr = static_cast<Expr *>(Attr.getArgAsExpr(0));
6640  LangAS ASIdx;
6641  if (!BuildAddressSpaceIndex(S, ASIdx, ASArgExpr, Attr.getLoc())) {
6642  Attr.setInvalid();
6643  return;
6644  }
6645 
6646  ASTContext &Ctx = S.Context;
6647  auto *ASAttr =
6648  ::new (Ctx) AddressSpaceAttr(Ctx, Attr, static_cast<unsigned>(ASIdx));
6649 
6650  // If the expression is not value dependent (not templated), then we can
6651  // apply the address space qualifiers just to the equivalent type.
6652  // Otherwise, we make an AttributedType with the modified and equivalent
6653  // type the same, and wrap it in a DependentAddressSpaceType. When this
6654  // dependent type is resolved, the qualifier is added to the equivalent type
6655  // later.
6656  QualType T;
6657  if (!ASArgExpr->isValueDependent()) {
6658  QualType EquivType =
6659  S.BuildAddressSpaceAttr(Type, ASIdx, ASArgExpr, Attr.getLoc());
6660  if (EquivType.isNull()) {
6661  Attr.setInvalid();
6662  return;
6663  }
6664  T = State.getAttributedType(ASAttr, Type, EquivType);
6665  } else {
6666  T = State.getAttributedType(ASAttr, Type, Type);
6667  T = S.BuildAddressSpaceAttr(T, ASIdx, ASArgExpr, Attr.getLoc());
6668  }
6669 
6670  if (!T.isNull())
6671  Type = T;
6672  else
6673  Attr.setInvalid();
6674  } else {
6675  // The keyword-based type attributes imply which address space to use.
6676  ASIdx = S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice ? Attr.asSYCLLangAS()
6677  : Attr.asOpenCLLangAS();
6678 
6679  if (ASIdx == LangAS::Default)
6680  llvm_unreachable("Invalid address space");
6681 
6682  if (DiagnoseMultipleAddrSpaceAttributes(S, Type.getAddressSpace(), ASIdx,
6683  Attr.getLoc())) {
6684  Attr.setInvalid();
6685  return;
6686  }
6687 
6688  Type = S.Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(Type, ASIdx);
6689  }
6690 }
6691 
6692 static void HandleSYCLFPGAPipeAttribute(QualType &Type, const ParsedAttr &Attr,
6693  TypeProcessingState &State) {
6694  Sema &S = State.getSema();
6695  ASTContext &Ctx = S.Context;
6696 
6697  // Check the attribute arguments.
6698  if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
6699  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
6700  << Attr << 1;
6701  Attr.setInvalid();
6702  return;
6703  }
6704 
6705  if (!Attr.isArgExpr(0)) {
6706  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
6707  << Attr << AANT_ArgumentString;
6708  Attr.setInvalid();
6709  return;
6710  }
6711 
6712  StringRef Str;
6713  if (auto *SL = dyn_cast<StringLiteral>(Attr.getArgAsExpr(0))) {
6714  Str = SL->getString();
6715  } else {
6716  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
6717  << Attr << AANT_ArgumentString;
6718  Attr.setInvalid();
6719  return;
6720  }
6721 
6722  bool isReadOnlyPipe;
6723  if (Str == "write_only")
6724  isReadOnlyPipe = false;
6725  else if (Str == "read_only")
6726  isReadOnlyPipe = true;
6727  else {
6728  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_pipe_attribute_arg_not_allowed) << Str;
6729  Attr.setInvalid();
6730  return;
6731  }
6732 
6733  auto *PipeAttr = ::new (Ctx) SYCLFPGAPipeAttr(Ctx, Attr, Str);
6734 
6735  // Apply pipe qualifiers just to the equivalent type, as the expression is not
6736  // value dependent (not templated).
6737  QualType EquivType = isReadOnlyPipe
6738  ? S.BuildReadPipeType(Type, Attr.getLoc())
6739  : S.BuildWritePipeType(Type, Attr.getLoc());
6740  if (EquivType.isNull()) {
6741  Attr.setInvalid();
6742  return;
6743  }
6744 
6745  QualType T = State.getAttributedType(PipeAttr, Type, EquivType);
6746  if (!T.isNull())
6747  Type = T;
6748  else
6749  Attr.setInvalid();
6750 }
6751 
6752 /// handleObjCOwnershipTypeAttr - Process an objc_ownership
6753 /// attribute on the specified type.
6754 ///
6755 /// Returns 'true' if the attribute was handled.
6756 static bool handleObjCOwnershipTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state,
6757  ParsedAttr &attr, QualType &type) {
6758  bool NonObjCPointer = false;
6759 
6760  if (!type->isDependentType() && !type->isUndeducedType()) {
6761  if (const PointerType *ptr = type->getAs<PointerType>()) {
6762  QualType pointee = ptr->getPointeeType();
6763  if (pointee->isObjCRetainableType() || pointee->isPointerType())
6764  return false;
6765  // It is important not to lose the source info that there was an attribute
6766  // applied to non-objc pointer. We will create an attributed type but
6767  // its type will be the same as the original type.
6768  NonObjCPointer = true;
6769  } else if (!type->isObjCRetainableType()) {
6770  return false;
6771  }
6772 
6773  // Don't accept an ownership attribute in the declspec if it would
6774  // just be the return type of a block pointer.
6775  if (state.isProcessingDeclSpec()) {
6776  Declarator &D = state.getDeclarator();
6777  if (maybeMovePastReturnType(D, D.getNumTypeObjects(),
6778  /*onlyBlockPointers=*/true))
6779  return false;
6780  }
6781  }
6782 
6783  Sema &S = state.getSema();
6784  SourceLocation AttrLoc = attr.getLoc();
6785  if (AttrLoc.isMacroID())
6786  AttrLoc =
6787  S.getSourceManager().getImmediateExpansionRange(AttrLoc).getBegin();
6788 
6789  if (!attr.isArgIdent(0)) {
6790  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attribute_argument_type) << attr
6791  << AANT_ArgumentString;
6792  attr.setInvalid();
6793  return true;
6794  }
6795 
6796  IdentifierInfo *II = attr.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
6797  Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime lifetime;
6798  if (II->isStr("none"))
6799  lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone;
6800  else if (II->isStr("strong"))
6801  lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_Strong;
6802  else if (II->isStr("weak"))
6803  lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_Weak;
6804  else if (II->isStr("autoreleasing"))
6805  lifetime = Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing;
6806  else {
6807  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported) << attr << II;
6808  attr.setInvalid();
6809  return true;
6810  }
6811 
6812  // Just ignore lifetime attributes other than __weak and __unsafe_unretained
6813  // outside of ARC mode.
6814  if (!S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
6815  lifetime != Qualifiers::OCL_Weak &&
6816  lifetime != Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone) {
6817  return true;
6818  }
6819 
6820  SplitQualType underlyingType = type.split();
6821 
6822  // Check for redundant/conflicting ownership qualifiers.
6823  if (Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime previousLifetime
6824  = type.getQualifiers().getObjCLifetime()) {
6825  // If it's written directly, that's an error.
6826  if (S.Context.hasDirectOwnershipQualifier(type)) {
6827  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_attr_objc_ownership_redundant)
6828  << type;
6829  return true;
6830  }
6831 
6832  // Otherwise, if the qualifiers actually conflict, pull sugar off
6833  // and remove the ObjCLifetime qualifiers.
6834  if (previousLifetime != lifetime) {
6835  // It's possible to have multiple local ObjCLifetime qualifiers. We
6836  // can't stop after we reach a type that is directly qualified.
6837  const Type *prevTy = nullptr;
6838  while (!prevTy || prevTy != underlyingType.Ty) {
6839  prevTy = underlyingType.Ty;
6840  underlyingType = underlyingType.getSingleStepDesugaredType();
6841  }
6842  underlyingType.Quals.removeObjCLifetime();
6843  }
6844  }
6845 
6846  underlyingType.Quals.addObjCLifetime(lifetime);
6847 
6848  if (NonObjCPointer) {
6849  StringRef name = attr.getAttrName()->getName();
6850  switch (lifetime) {
6851  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
6852  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
6853  break;
6854  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong: name = "__strong"; break;
6855  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak: name = "__weak"; break;
6856  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing: name = "__autoreleasing"; break;
6857  }
6858  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::warn_type_attribute_wrong_type) << name
6859  << TDS_ObjCObjOrBlock << type;
6860  }
6861 
6862  // Don't actually add the __unsafe_unretained qualifier in non-ARC files,
6863  // because having both 'T' and '__unsafe_unretained T' exist in the type
6864  // system causes unfortunate widespread consistency problems. (For example,
6865  // they're not considered compatible types, and we mangle them identicially
6866  // as template arguments.) These problems are all individually fixable,
6867  // but it's easier to just not add the qualifier and instead sniff it out
6868  // in specific places using isObjCInertUnsafeUnretainedType().
6869  //
6870  // Doing this does means we miss some trivial consistency checks that
6871  // would've triggered in ARC, but that's better than trying to solve all
6872  // the coexistence problems with __unsafe_unretained.
6873  if (!S.getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount &&
6874  lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone) {
6875  type = state.getAttributedType(
6876  createSimpleAttr<ObjCInertUnsafeUnretainedAttr>(S.Context, attr),
6877  type, type);
6878  return true;
6879  }
6880 
6881  QualType origType = type;
6882  if (!NonObjCPointer)
6883  type = S.Context.getQualifiedType(underlyingType);
6884 
6885  // If we have a valid source location for the attribute, use an
6886  // AttributedType instead.
6887  if (AttrLoc.isValid()) {
6888  type = state.getAttributedType(::new (S.Context)
6889  ObjCOwnershipAttr(S.Context, attr, II),
6890  origType, type);
6891  }
6892 
6893  auto diagnoseOrDelay = [](Sema &S, SourceLocation loc,
6894  unsigned diagnostic, QualType type) {
6895  if (S.DelayedDiagnostics.shouldDelayDiagnostics()) {
6896  S.DelayedDiagnostics.add(
6897  sema::DelayedDiagnostic::makeForbiddenType(
6898  S.getSourceManager().getExpansionLoc(loc),
6899  diagnostic, type, /*ignored*/ 0));
6900  } else {
6901  S.Diag(loc, diagnostic);
6902  }
6903  };
6904 
6905  // Sometimes, __weak isn't allowed.
6906  if (lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak &&
6907  !S.getLangOpts().ObjCWeak && !NonObjCPointer) {
6908 
6909  // Use a specialized diagnostic if the runtime just doesn't support them.
6910  unsigned diagnostic =
6911  (S.getLangOpts().ObjCWeakRuntime ? diag::err_arc_weak_disabled
6912  : diag::err_arc_weak_no_runtime);
6913 
6914  // In any case, delay the diagnostic until we know what we're parsing.
6915  diagnoseOrDelay(S, AttrLoc, diagnostic, type);
6916 
6917  attr.setInvalid();
6918  return true;
6919  }
6920 
6921  // Forbid __weak for class objects marked as
6922  // objc_arc_weak_reference_unavailable
6923  if (lifetime == Qualifiers::OCL_Weak) {
6924  if (const ObjCObjectPointerType *ObjT =
6925  type->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
6926  if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *Class = ObjT->getInterfaceDecl()) {
6927  if (Class->isArcWeakrefUnavailable()) {
6928  S.Diag(AttrLoc, diag::err_arc_unsupported_weak_class);
6929  S.Diag(ObjT->getInterfaceDecl()->getLocation(),
6930  diag::note_class_declared);
6931  }
6932  }
6933  }
6934  }
6935 
6936  return true;
6937 }
6938 
6939 /// handleObjCGCTypeAttr - Process the __attribute__((objc_gc)) type
6940 /// attribute on the specified type. Returns true to indicate that
6941 /// the attribute was handled, false to indicate that the type does
6942 /// not permit the attribute.
6943 static bool handleObjCGCTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state, ParsedAttr &attr,
6944  QualType &type) {
6945  Sema &S = state.getSema();
6946 
6947  // Delay if this isn't some kind of pointer.
6948  if (!type->isPointerType() &&
6949  !type->isObjCObjectPointerType() &&
6950  !type->isBlockPointerType())
6951  return false;
6952 
6953  if (type.getObjCGCAttr() != Qualifiers::GCNone) {
6954  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_multiple_objc_gc);
6955  attr.setInvalid();
6956  return true;
6957  }
6958 
6959  // Check the attribute arguments.
6960  if (!attr.isArgIdent(0)) {
6961  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
6962  << attr << AANT_ArgumentString;
6963  attr.setInvalid();
6964  return true;
6965  }
6966  Qualifiers::GC GCAttr;
6967  if (attr.getNumArgs() > 1) {
6968  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << attr
6969  << 1;
6970  attr.setInvalid();
6971  return true;
6972  }
6973 
6974  IdentifierInfo *II = attr.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident;
6975  if (II->isStr("weak"))
6976  GCAttr = Qualifiers::Weak;
6977  else if (II->isStr("strong"))
6978  GCAttr = Qualifiers::Strong;
6979  else {
6980  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_type_not_supported)
6981  << attr << II;
6982  attr.setInvalid();
6983  return true;
6984  }
6985 
6986  QualType origType = type;
6987  type = S.Context.getObjCGCQualType(origType, GCAttr);
6988 
6989  // Make an attributed type to preserve the source information.
6990  if (attr.getLoc().isValid())
6991  type = state.getAttributedType(
6992  ::new (S.Context) ObjCGCAttr(S.Context, attr, II), origType, type);
6993 
6994  return true;
6995 }
6996 
6997 namespace {
6998  /// A helper class to unwrap a type down to a function for the
6999  /// purposes of applying attributes there.
7000  ///
7001  /// Use:
7002  /// FunctionTypeUnwrapper unwrapped(SemaRef, T);
7003  /// if (unwrapped.isFunctionType()) {
7004  /// const FunctionType *fn = unwrapped.get();
7005  /// // change fn somehow
7006  /// T = unwrapped.wrap(fn);
7007  /// }
7008  struct FunctionTypeUnwrapper {
7009  enum WrapKind {
7010  Desugar,
7011  Attributed,
7012  Parens,
7013  Array,
7014  Pointer,
7015  BlockPointer,
7016  Reference,
7017  MemberPointer,
7018  MacroQualified,
7019  };
7020 
7021  QualType Original;
7022  const FunctionType *Fn;
7023  SmallVector<unsigned char /*WrapKind*/, 8> Stack;
7024 
7025  FunctionTypeUnwrapper(Sema &S, QualType T) : Original(T) {
7026  while (true) {
7027  const Type *Ty = T.getTypePtr();
7028  if (isa<FunctionType>(Ty)) {
7029  Fn = cast<FunctionType>(Ty);
7030  return;
7031  } else if (isa<ParenType>(Ty)) {
7032  T = cast<ParenType>(Ty)->getInnerType();
7033  Stack.push_back(Parens);
7034  } else if (isa<ConstantArrayType>(Ty) || isa<VariableArrayType>(Ty) ||
7035  isa<IncompleteArrayType>(Ty)) {
7036  T = cast<ArrayType>(Ty)->getElementType();
7037  Stack.push_back(Array);
7038  } else if (isa<PointerType>(Ty)) {
7039  T = cast<PointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType();
7040  Stack.push_back(Pointer);
7041  } else if (isa<BlockPointerType>(Ty)) {
7042  T = cast<BlockPointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType();
7043  Stack.push_back(BlockPointer);
7044  } else if (isa<MemberPointerType>(Ty)) {
7045  T = cast<MemberPointerType>(Ty)->getPointeeType();
7046  Stack.push_back(MemberPointer);
7047  } else if (isa<ReferenceType>(Ty)) {
7048  T = cast<ReferenceType>(Ty)->getPointeeType();
7049  Stack.push_back(Reference);
7050  } else if (isa<AttributedType>(Ty)) {
7051  T = cast<AttributedType>(Ty)->getEquivalentType();
7052  Stack.push_back(Attributed);
7053  } else if (isa<MacroQualifiedType>(Ty)) {
7054  T = cast<MacroQualifiedType>(Ty)->getUnderlyingType();
7055  Stack.push_back(MacroQualified);
7056  } else {
7057  const Type *DTy = Ty->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
7058  if (Ty == DTy) {
7059  Fn = nullptr;
7060  return;
7061  }
7062 
7063  T = QualType(DTy, 0);
7064  Stack.push_back(Desugar);
7065  }
7066  }
7067  }
7068 
7069  bool isFunctionType() const { return (Fn != nullptr); }
7070  const FunctionType *get() const { return Fn; }
7071 
7072  QualType wrap(Sema &S, const FunctionType *New) {
7073  // If T wasn't modified from the unwrapped type, do nothing.
7074  if (New == get()) return Original;
7075 
7076  Fn = New;
7077  return wrap(S.Context, Original, 0);
7078  }
7079 
7080  private:
7081  QualType wrap(ASTContext &C, QualType Old, unsigned I) {
7082  if (I == Stack.size())
7083  return C.getQualifiedType(Fn, Old.getQualifiers());
7084 
7085  // Build up the inner type, applying the qualifiers from the old
7086  // type to the new type.
7087  SplitQualType SplitOld = Old.split();
7088 
7089  // As a special case, tail-recurse if there are no qualifiers.
7090  if (SplitOld.Quals.empty())
7091  return wrap(C, SplitOld.Ty, I);
7092  return C.getQualifiedType(wrap(C, SplitOld.Ty, I), SplitOld.Quals);
7093  }
7094 
7095  QualType wrap(ASTContext &C, const Type *Old, unsigned I) {
7096  if (I == Stack.size()) return QualType(Fn, 0);
7097 
7098  switch (static_cast<WrapKind>(Stack[I++])) {
7099  case Desugar:
7100  // This is the point at which we potentially lose source
7101  // information.
7102  return wrap(C, Old->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType(), I);
7103 
7104  case Attributed:
7105  return wrap(C, cast<AttributedType>(Old)->getEquivalentType(), I);
7106 
7107  case Parens: {
7108  QualType New = wrap(C, cast<ParenType>(Old)->getInnerType(), I);
7109  return C.getParenType(New);
7110  }
7111 
7112  case MacroQualified:
7113  return wrap(C, cast<MacroQualifiedType>(Old)->getUnderlyingType(), I);
7114 
7115  case Array: {
7116  if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(Old)) {
7117  QualType New = wrap(C, CAT->getElementType(), I);
7118  return C.getConstantArrayType(New, CAT->getSize(), CAT->getSizeExpr(),
7119  CAT->getSizeModifier(),
7120  CAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers());
7121  }
7122 
7123  if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(Old)) {
7124  QualType New = wrap(C, VAT->getElementType(), I);
7125  return C.getVariableArrayType(
7126  New, VAT->getSizeExpr(), VAT->getSizeModifier(),
7127  VAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(), VAT->getBracketsRange());
7128  }
7129 
7130  const auto *IAT = cast<IncompleteArrayType>(Old);
7131  QualType New = wrap(C, IAT->getElementType(), I);
7132  return C.getIncompleteArrayType(New, IAT->getSizeModifier(),
7133  IAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers());
7134  }
7135 
7136  case Pointer: {
7137  QualType New = wrap(C, cast<PointerType>(Old)->getPointeeType(), I);
7138  return C.getPointerType(New);
7139  }
7140 
7141  case BlockPointer: {
7142  QualType New = wrap(C, cast<BlockPointerType>(Old)->getPointeeType(),I);
7143  return C.getBlockPointerType(New);
7144  }
7145 
7146  case MemberPointer: {
7147  const MemberPointerType *OldMPT = cast<MemberPointerType>(Old);
7148  QualType New = wrap(C, OldMPT->getPointeeType(), I);
7149  return C.getMemberPointerType(New, OldMPT->getClass());
7150  }
7151 
7152  case Reference: {
7153  const ReferenceType *OldRef = cast<ReferenceType>(Old);
7154  QualType New = wrap(C, OldRef->getPointeeType(), I);
7155  if (isa<LValueReferenceType>(OldRef))
7156  return C.getLValueReferenceType(New, OldRef->isSpelledAsLValue());
7157  else
7158  return C.getRValueReferenceType(New);
7159  }
7160  }
7161 
7162  llvm_unreachable("unknown wrapping kind");
7163  }
7164  };
7165 } // end anonymous namespace
7166 
7167 static bool handleMSPointerTypeQualifierAttr(TypeProcessingState &State,
7168  ParsedAttr &PAttr, QualType &Type) {
7169  Sema &S = State.getSema();
7170 
7171  Attr *A;
7172  switch (PAttr.getKind()) {
7173  default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown attribute kind");
7174  case ParsedAttr::AT_Ptr32:
7175  A = createSimpleAttr<Ptr32Attr>(S.Context, PAttr);
7176  break;
7177  case ParsedAttr::AT_Ptr64:
7178  A = createSimpleAttr<Ptr64Attr>(S.Context, PAttr);
7179  break;
7180  case ParsedAttr::AT_SPtr:
7181  A = createSimpleAttr<SPtrAttr>(S.Context, PAttr);
7182  break;
7183  case ParsedAttr::AT_UPtr:
7184  A = createSimpleAttr<UPtrAttr>(S.Context, PAttr);
7185  break;
7186  }
7187 
7188  std::bitset<attr::LastAttr> Attrs;
7189  attr::Kind NewAttrKind = A->getKind();
7190  QualType Desugared = Type;
7191  const AttributedType *AT = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Type);
7192  while (AT) {
7193  Attrs[AT->getAttrKind()] = true;
7194  Desugared = AT->getModifiedType();
7195  AT = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Desugared);
7196  }
7197 
7198  // You cannot specify duplicate type attributes, so if the attribute has
7199  // already been applied, flag it.
7200  if (Attrs[NewAttrKind]) {
7201  S.Diag(PAttr.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_attribute_exact) << PAttr;
7202  return true;
7203  }
7204  Attrs[NewAttrKind] = true;
7205 
7206  // You cannot have both __sptr and __uptr on the same type, nor can you
7207  // have __ptr32 and __ptr64.
7208  if (Attrs[attr::Ptr32] && Attrs[attr::Ptr64]) {
7209  S.Diag(PAttr.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
7210  << "'__ptr32'"
7211  << "'__ptr64'";
7212  return true;
7213  } else if (Attrs[attr::SPtr] && Attrs[attr::UPtr]) {
7214  S.Diag(PAttr.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
7215  << "'__sptr'"
7216  << "'__uptr'";
7217  return true;
7218  }
7219 
7220  // Pointer type qualifiers can only operate on pointer types, but not
7221  // pointer-to-member types.
7222  //
7223  // FIXME: Should we really be disallowing this attribute if there is any
7224  // type sugar between it and the pointer (other than attributes)? Eg, this
7225  // disallows the attribute on a parenthesized pointer.
7226  // And if so, should we really allow *any* type attribute?
7227  if (!isa<PointerType>(Desugared)) {
7228  if (Type->isMemberPointerType())
7229  S.Diag(PAttr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_no_member_pointers) << PAttr;
7230  else
7231  S.Diag(PAttr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_pointers_only) << PAttr << 0;
7232  return true;
7233  }
7234 
7235  // Add address space to type based on its attributes.
7236  LangAS ASIdx = LangAS::Default;
7237  uint64_t PtrWidth = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0);
7238  if (PtrWidth == 32) {
7239  if (Attrs[attr::Ptr64])
7240  ASIdx = LangAS::ptr64;
7241  else if (Attrs[attr::UPtr])
7242  ASIdx = LangAS::ptr32_uptr;
7243  } else if (PtrWidth == 64 && Attrs[attr::Ptr32]) {
7244  if (Attrs[attr::UPtr])
7245  ASIdx = LangAS::ptr32_uptr;
7246  else
7247  ASIdx = LangAS::ptr32_sptr;
7248  }
7249 
7250  QualType Pointee = Type->getPointeeType();
7251  if (ASIdx != LangAS::Default)
7252  Pointee = S.Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(
7253  S.Context.removeAddrSpaceQualType(Pointee), ASIdx);
7254  Type = State.getAttributedType(A, Type, S.Context.getPointerType(Pointee));
7255  return false;
7256 }
7257 
7258 /// Map a nullability attribute kind to a nullability kind.
7259 static NullabilityKind mapNullabilityAttrKind(ParsedAttr::Kind kind) {
7260  switch (kind) {
7261  case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNonNull:
7262  return NullabilityKind::NonNull;
7263 
7264  case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullable:
7265  return NullabilityKind::Nullable;
7266 
7267  case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullableResult:
7268  return NullabilityKind::NullableResult;
7269 
7270  case ParsedAttr::AT_TypeNullUnspecified:
7271  return NullabilityKind::Unspecified;
7272 
7273  default:
7274  llvm_unreachable("not a nullability attribute kind");
7275  }
7276 }
7277 
7278 /// Applies a nullability type specifier to the given type, if possible.
7279 ///
7280 /// \param state The type processing state.
7281 ///
7282 /// \param type The type to which the nullability specifier will be
7283 /// added. On success, this type will be updated appropriately.
7284 ///
7285 /// \param attr The attribute as written on the type.
7286 ///
7287 /// \param allowOnArrayType Whether to accept nullability specifiers on an
7288 /// array type (e.g., because it will decay to a pointer).
7289 ///
7290 /// \returns true if a problem has been diagnosed, false on success.
7291 static bool checkNullabilityTypeSpecifier(TypeProcessingState &state,
7292  QualType &type,
7293  ParsedAttr &attr,
7294  bool allowOnArrayType) {
7295  Sema &S = state.getSema();
7296 
7297  NullabilityKind nullability = mapNullabilityAttrKind(attr.getKind());
7298  SourceLocation nullabilityLoc = attr.getLoc();
7299  bool isContextSensitive = attr.isContextSensitiveKeywordAttribute();
7300 
7301  recordNullabilitySeen(S, nullabilityLoc);
7302 
7303  // Check for existing nullability attributes on the type.
7304  QualType desugared = type;
7305  while (auto attributed = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(desugared.getTypePtr())) {
7306  // Check whether there is already a null
7307  if (auto existingNullability = attributed->getImmediateNullability()) {
7308  // Duplicated nullability.
7309  if (nullability == *existingNullability) {
7310  S.Diag(nullabilityLoc, diag::warn_nullability_duplicate)
7311  << DiagNullabilityKind(nullability, isContextSensitive)
7312  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(nullabilityLoc);
7313 
7314  break;
7315  }
7316 
7317  // Conflicting nullability.
7318  S.Diag(nullabilityLoc, diag::err_nullability_conflicting)
7319  << DiagNullabilityKind(nullability, isContextSensitive)
7320  << DiagNullabilityKind(*existingNullability, false);
7321  return true;
7322  }
7323 
7324  desugared = attributed->getModifiedType();
7325  }
7326 
7327  // If there is already a different nullability specifier, complain.
7328  // This (unlike the code above) looks through typedefs that might
7329  // have nullability specifiers on them, which means we cannot
7330  // provide a useful Fix-It.
7331  if (auto existingNullability = desugared->getNullability(S.Context)) {
7332  if (nullability != *existingNullability) {
7333  S.Diag(nullabilityLoc, diag::err_nullability_conflicting)
7334  << DiagNullabilityKind(nullability, isContextSensitive)
7335  << DiagNullabilityKind(*existingNullability, false);
7336 
7337  // Try to find the typedef with the existing nullability specifier.
7338  if (auto typedefType = desugared->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
7339  TypedefNameDecl *typedefDecl = typedefType->getDecl();
7340  QualType underlyingType = typedefDecl->getUnderlyingType();
7341  if (auto typedefNullability
7342  = AttributedType::stripOuterNullability(underlyingType)) {
7343  if (*typedefNullability == *existingNullability) {
7344  S.Diag(typedefDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_nullability_here)
7345  << DiagNullabilityKind(*existingNullability, false);
7346  }
7347  }
7348  }
7349 
7350  return true;
7351  }
7352  }
7353 
7354  // If this definitely isn't a pointer type, reject the specifier.
7355  if (!desugared->canHaveNullability() &&
7356  !(allowOnArrayType && desugared->isArrayType())) {
7357  S.Diag(nullabilityLoc, diag::err_nullability_nonpointer)
7358  << DiagNullabilityKind(nullability, isContextSensitive) << type;
7359  return true;
7360  }
7361 
7362  // For the context-sensitive keywords/Objective-C property
7363  // attributes, require that the type be a single-level pointer.
7364  if (isContextSensitive) {
7365  // Make sure that the pointee isn't itself a pointer type.
7366  const Type *pointeeType = nullptr;
7367  if (desugared->isArrayType())
7368  pointeeType = desugared->getArrayElementTypeNoTypeQual();
7369  else if (desugared->isAnyPointerType())
7370  pointeeType = desugared->getPointeeType().getTypePtr();
7371 
7372  if (pointeeType && (pointeeType->isAnyPointerType() ||
7373  pointeeType->isObjCObjectPointerType() ||
7374  pointeeType->isMemberPointerType())) {
7375  S.Diag(nullabilityLoc, diag::err_nullability_cs_multilevel)
7376  << DiagNullabilityKind(nullability, true)
7377  << type;
7378  S.Diag(nullabilityLoc, diag::note_nullability_type_specifier)
7379  << DiagNullabilityKind(nullability, false)
7380  << type
7381  << FixItHint::CreateReplacement(nullabilityLoc,
7382  getNullabilitySpelling(nullability));
7383  return true;
7384  }
7385  }
7386 
7387  // Form the attributed type.
7388  type = state.getAttributedType(
7389  createNullabilityAttr(S.Context, attr, nullability), type, type);
7390  return false;
7391 }
7392 
7393 /// Check the application of the Objective-C '__kindof' qualifier to
7394 /// the given type.
7395 static bool checkObjCKindOfType(TypeProcessingState &state, QualType &type,
7396  ParsedAttr &attr) {
7397  Sema &S = state.getSema();
7398 
7399  if (isa<ObjCTypeParamType>(type)) {
7400  // Build the attributed type to record where __kindof occurred.
7401  type = state.getAttributedType(
7402  createSimpleAttr<ObjCKindOfAttr>(S.Context, attr), type, type);
7403  return false;
7404  }
7405 
7406  // Find out if it's an Objective-C object or object pointer type;
7407  const ObjCObjectPointerType *ptrType = type->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
7408  const ObjCObjectType *objType = ptrType ? ptrType->getObjectType()
7409  : type->getAs<ObjCObjectType>();
7410 
7411  // If not, we can't apply __kindof.
7412  if (!objType) {
7413  // FIXME: Handle dependent types that aren't yet object types.
7414  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_objc_kindof_nonobject)
7415  << type;
7416  return true;
7417  }
7418 
7419  // Rebuild the "equivalent" type, which pushes __kindof down into
7420  // the object type.
7421  // There is no need to apply kindof on an unqualified id type.
7422  QualType equivType = S.Context.getObjCObjectType(
7423  objType->getBaseType(), objType->getTypeArgsAsWritten(),
7424  objType->getProtocols(),
7425  /*isKindOf=*/objType->isObjCUnqualifiedId() ? false : true);
7426 
7427  // If we started with an object pointer type, rebuild it.
7428  if (ptrType) {
7429  equivType = S.Context.getObjCObjectPointerType(equivType);
7430  if (auto nullability = type->getNullability(S.Context)) {
7431  // We create a nullability attribute from the __kindof attribute.
7432  // Make sure that will make sense.
7433  assert(attr.getAttributeSpellingListIndex() == 0 &&
7434  "multiple spellings for __kindof?");
7435  Attr *A = createNullabilityAttr(S.Context, attr, *nullability);
7436  A->setImplicit(true);
7437  equivType = state.getAttributedType(A, equivType, equivType);
7438  }
7439  }
7440 
7441  // Build the attributed type to record where __kindof occurred.
7442  type = state.getAttributedType(
7443  createSimpleAttr<ObjCKindOfAttr>(S.Context, attr), type, equivType);
7444  return false;
7445 }
7446 
7447 /// Distribute a nullability type attribute that cannot be applied to
7448 /// the type specifier to a pointer, block pointer, or member pointer
7449 /// declarator, complaining if necessary.
7450 ///
7451 /// \returns true if the nullability annotation was distributed, false
7452 /// otherwise.
7453 static bool distributeNullabilityTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state,
7454  QualType type, ParsedAttr &attr) {
7455  Declarator &declarator = state.getDeclarator();
7456 
7457  /// Attempt to move the attribute to the specified chunk.
7458  auto moveToChunk = [&](DeclaratorChunk &chunk, bool inFunction) -> bool {
7459  // If there is already a nullability attribute there, don't add
7460  // one.
7461  if (hasNullabilityAttr(chunk.getAttrs()))
7462  return false;
7463 
7464  // Complain about the nullability qualifier being in the wrong
7465  // place.
7466  enum {
7467  PK_Pointer,
7468  PK_BlockPointer,
7469  PK_MemberPointer,
7470  PK_FunctionPointer,
7471  PK_MemberFunctionPointer,
7472  } pointerKind
7473  = chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::Pointer ? (inFunction ? PK_FunctionPointer
7474  : PK_Pointer)
7475  : chunk.Kind == DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer ? PK_BlockPointer
7476  : inFunction? PK_MemberFunctionPointer : PK_MemberPointer;
7477 
7478  auto diag = state.getSema().Diag(attr.getLoc(),
7479  diag::warn_nullability_declspec)
7480  << DiagNullabilityKind(mapNullabilityAttrKind(attr.getKind()),
7481  attr.isContextSensitiveKeywordAttribute())
7482  << type
7483  << static_cast<unsigned>(pointerKind);
7484 
7485  // FIXME: MemberPointer chunks don't carry the location of the *.
7486  if (chunk.Kind != DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer) {
7487  diag << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(attr.getLoc())
7488  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
7489  state.getSema().getPreprocessor().getLocForEndOfToken(
7490  chunk.Loc),
7491  " " + attr.getAttrName()->getName().str() + " ");
7492  }
7493 
7494  moveAttrFromListToList(attr, state.getCurrentAttributes(),
7495  chunk.getAttrs());
7496  return true;
7497  };
7498 
7499  // Move it to the outermost pointer, member pointer, or block
7500  // pointer declarator.
7501  for (unsigned i = state.getCurrentChunkIndex(); i != 0; --i) {
7502  DeclaratorChunk &chunk = declarator.getTypeObject(i-1);
7503  switch (chunk.Kind) {
7504  case DeclaratorChunk::Pointer:
7505  case DeclaratorChunk::BlockPointer:
7506  case DeclaratorChunk::MemberPointer:
7507  return moveToChunk(chunk, false);
7508 
7509  case DeclaratorChunk::Paren:
7510  case DeclaratorChunk::Array:
7511  continue;
7512 
7513  case DeclaratorChunk::Function:
7514  // Try to move past the return type to a function/block/member
7515  // function pointer.
7516  if (DeclaratorChunk *dest = maybeMovePastReturnType(
7517  declarator, i,
7518  /*onlyBlockPointers=*/false)) {
7519  return moveToChunk(*dest, true);
7520  }
7521 
7522  return false;
7523 
7524  // Don't walk through these.
7525  case DeclaratorChunk::Reference:
7526  case DeclaratorChunk::Pipe:
7527  return false;
7528  }
7529  }
7530 
7531  return false;
7532 }
7533 
7534 static Attr *getCCTypeAttr(ASTContext &Ctx, ParsedAttr &Attr) {
7535  assert(!Attr.isInvalid());
7536  switch (Attr.getKind()) {
7537  default:
7538  llvm_unreachable("not a calling convention attribute");
7539  case ParsedAttr::AT_CDecl:
7540  return createSimpleAttr<CDeclAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7541  case ParsedAttr::AT_FastCall:
7542  return createSimpleAttr<FastCallAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7543  case ParsedAttr::AT_StdCall:
7544  return createSimpleAttr<StdCallAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7545  case ParsedAttr::AT_ThisCall:
7546  return createSimpleAttr<ThisCallAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7547  case ParsedAttr::AT_RegCall:
7548  return createSimpleAttr<RegCallAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7549  case ParsedAttr::AT_Pascal:
7550  return createSimpleAttr<PascalAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7551  case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftCall:
7552  return createSimpleAttr<SwiftCallAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7553  case ParsedAttr::AT_SwiftAsyncCall:
7554  return createSimpleAttr<SwiftAsyncCallAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7555  case ParsedAttr::AT_VectorCall:
7556  return createSimpleAttr<VectorCallAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7557  case ParsedAttr::AT_AArch64VectorPcs:
7558  return createSimpleAttr<AArch64VectorPcsAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7559  case ParsedAttr::AT_Pcs: {
7560  // The attribute may have had a fixit applied where we treated an
7561  // identifier as a string literal. The contents of the string are valid,
7562  // but the form may not be.
7563  StringRef Str;
7564  if (Attr.isArgExpr(0))
7565  Str = cast<StringLiteral>(Attr.getArgAsExpr(0))->getString();
7566  else
7567  Str = Attr.getArgAsIdent(0)->Ident->getName();
7568  PcsAttr::PCSType Type;
7569  if (!PcsAttr::ConvertStrToPCSType(Str, Type))
7570  llvm_unreachable("already validated the attribute");
7571  return ::new (Ctx) PcsAttr(Ctx, Attr, Type);
7572  }
7573  case ParsedAttr::AT_IntelOclBicc:
7574  return createSimpleAttr<IntelOclBiccAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7575  case ParsedAttr::AT_MSABI:
7576  return createSimpleAttr<MSABIAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7577  case ParsedAttr::AT_SysVABI:
7578  return createSimpleAttr<SysVABIAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7579  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveMost:
7580  return createSimpleAttr<PreserveMostAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7581  case ParsedAttr::AT_PreserveAll:
7582  return createSimpleAttr<PreserveAllAttr>(Ctx, Attr);
7583  }
7584  llvm_unreachable("unexpected attribute kind!");
7585 }
7586 
7587 /// Process an individual function attribute. Returns true to
7588 /// indicate that the attribute was handled, false if it wasn't.
7589 static bool handleFunctionTypeAttr(TypeProcessingState &state, ParsedAttr &attr,
7590  QualType &type) {
7591  Sema &S = state.getSema();
7592 
7593  FunctionTypeUnwrapper unwrapped(S, type);
7594 
7595  if (attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_NoReturn) {
7596  if (S.CheckAttrNoArgs(attr))
7597  return true;
7598 
7599  // Delay if this is not a function type.
7600  if (!unwrapped.isFunctionType())
7601  return false;
7602 
7603  // Otherwise we can process right away.
7604  FunctionType::ExtInfo EI = unwrapped.get()->getExtInfo().withNoReturn(true);
7605  type = unwrapped.wrap(S, S.Context.adjustFunctionType(unwrapped.get(), EI));
7606  return true;
7607  }
7608 
7609  if (attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_CmseNSCall) {
7610  // Delay if this is not a function type.
7611  if (!unwrapped.isFunctionType())
7612  return false;
7613 
7614  // Ignore if we don't have CMSE enabled.
7615  if (!S.getLangOpts().Cmse) {
7616  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_attribute_ignored) << attr;
7617  attr.setInvalid();
7618  return true;
7619  }
7620 
7621  // Otherwise we can process right away.
7622  FunctionType::ExtInfo EI =
7623  unwrapped.get()->getExtInfo().withCmseNSCall(true);
7624  type = unwrapped.wrap(S, S.Context.adjustFunctionType(unwrapped.get(), EI));
7625  return true;
7626  }
7627 
7628  // ns_returns_retained is not always a type attribute, but if we got
7629  // here, we're treating it as one right now.
7630  if (attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_NSReturnsRetained) {
7631  if (attr.getNumArgs()) return true;
7632 
7633  // Delay if this is not a function type.
7634  if (!unwrapped.isFunctionType())
7635  return false;
7636 
7637  // Check whether the return type is reasonable.
7638  if (S.checkNSReturnsRetainedReturnType(attr.getLoc(),
7639  unwrapped.get()->getReturnType()))
7640  return true;
7641 
7642  // Only actually change the underlying type in ARC builds.
7643  QualType origType = type;
7644  if (state.getSema().getLangOpts().ObjCAutoRefCount) {
7645  FunctionType::ExtInfo EI
7646  = unwrapped.get()->getExtInfo().withProducesResult(true);
7647  type = unwrapped.wrap(S, S.Context.adjustFunctionType(unwrapped.get(), EI));
7648  }
7649  type = state.getAttributedType(
7650  createSimpleAttr<NSReturnsRetainedAttr>(S.Context, attr),
7651  origType, type);
7652  return true;
7653  }
7654 
7655  if (attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_AnyX86NoCallerSavedRegisters) {
7656  if (S.CheckAttrTarget(attr) || S.CheckAttrNoArgs(attr))
7657  return true;
7658 
7659  // Delay if this is not a function type.
7660  if (!unwrapped.isFunctionType())
7661  return false;
7662 
7663  FunctionType::ExtInfo EI =
7664  unwrapped.get()->getExtInfo().withNoCallerSavedRegs(true);
7665  type = unwrapped.wrap(S, S.Context.adjustFunctionType(unwrapped.get(), EI));
7666  return true;
7667  }
7668 
7669  if (attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_AnyX86NoCfCheck) {
7670  if (!S.getLangOpts().CFProtectionBranch) {
7671  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_nocf_check_attribute_ignored);
7672  attr.setInvalid();
7673  return true;
7674  }
7675 
7676  if (S.CheckAttrTarget(attr) || S.CheckAttrNoArgs(attr))
7677  return true;
7678 
7679  // If this is not a function type, warning will be asserted by subject
7680  // check.
7681  if (!unwrapped.isFunctionType())
7682  return true;
7683 
7684  FunctionType::ExtInfo EI =
7685  unwrapped.get()->getExtInfo().withNoCfCheck(true);
7686  type = unwrapped.wrap(S, S.Context.adjustFunctionType(unwrapped.get(), EI));
7687  return true;
7688  }
7689 
7690  if (attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_Regparm) {
7691  unsigned value;
7692  if (S.CheckRegparmAttr(attr, value))
7693  return true;
7694 
7695  // Delay if this is not a function type.
7696  if (!unwrapped.isFunctionType())
7697  return false;
7698 
7699  // Diagnose regparm with fastcall.
7700  const FunctionType *fn = unwrapped.get();
7701  CallingConv CC = fn->getCallConv();
7702  if (CC == CC_X86FastCall) {
7703  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
7704  << FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(CC)
7705  << "regparm";
7706  attr.setInvalid();
7707  return true;
7708  }
7709 
7710  FunctionType::ExtInfo EI =
7711  unwrapped.get()->getExtInfo().withRegParm(value);
7712  type = unwrapped.wrap(S, S.Context.adjustFunctionType(unwrapped.get(), EI));
7713  return true;
7714  }
7715 
7716  if (attr.getKind() == ParsedAttr::AT_NoThrow) {
7717  // Delay if this is not a function type.
7718  if (!unwrapped.isFunctionType())
7719  return false;
7720 
7721  if (S.CheckAttrNoArgs(attr)) {
7722  attr.setInvalid();
7723  return true;
7724  }
7725 
7726  // Otherwise we can process right away.
7727  auto *Proto = unwrapped.get()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
7728 
7729  // MSVC ignores nothrow if it is in conflict with an explicit exception
7730  // specification.
7731  if (Proto->hasExceptionSpec()) {
7732  switch (Proto->getExceptionSpecType()) {
7733  case EST_None:
7734  llvm_unreachable("This doesn't have an exception spec!");
7735 
7736  case EST_DynamicNone:
7737  case EST_BasicNoexcept:
7738  case EST_NoexceptTrue:
7739  case EST_NoThrow:
7740  // Exception spec doesn't conflict with nothrow, so don't warn.
7741  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
7742  case EST_Unparsed:
7743  case EST_Uninstantiated:
7744  case EST_DependentNoexcept:
7745  case EST_Unevaluated:
7746  // We don't have enough information to properly determine if there is a
7747  // conflict, so suppress the warning.
7748  break;
7749  case EST_Dynamic:
7750  case EST_MSAny:
7751  case EST_NoexceptFalse:
7752  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_nothrow_attribute_ignored);
7753  break;
7754  }
7755  return true;
7756  }
7757 
7758  type = unwrapped.wrap(
7759  S, S.Context
7760  .getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(
7761  QualType{Proto, 0},
7762  FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo{EST_NoThrow})
7763  ->getAs<FunctionType>());
7764  return true;
7765  }
7766 
7767  // Delay if the type didn't work out to a function.
7768  if (!unwrapped.isFunctionType()) return false;
7769 
7770  // Otherwise, a calling convention.
7771  CallingConv CC;
7772  if (S.CheckCallingConvAttr(attr, CC))
7773  return true;
7774 
7775  const FunctionType *fn = unwrapped.get();
7776  CallingConv CCOld = fn->getCallConv();
7777  Attr *CCAttr = getCCTypeAttr(S.Context, attr);
7778 
7779  if (CCOld != CC) {
7780  // Error out on when there's already an attribute on the type
7781  // and the CCs don't match.
7782  if (S.getCallingConvAttributedType(type)) {
7783  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
7784  << FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(CC)
7785  << FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(CCOld);
7786  attr.setInvalid();
7787  return true;
7788  }
7789  }
7790 
7791  // Diagnose use of variadic functions with calling conventions that
7792  // don't support them (e.g. because they're callee-cleanup).
7793  // We delay warning about this on unprototyped function declarations
7794  // until after redeclaration checking, just in case we pick up a
7795  // prototype that way. And apparently we also "delay" warning about
7796  // unprototyped function types in general, despite not necessarily having
7797  // much ability to diagnose it later.
7798  if (!supportsVariadicCall(CC)) {
7799  const FunctionProtoType *FnP = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(fn);
7800  // Disable these diagnostics for SYCL
7801  if (FnP && FnP->isVariadic() && !S.getLangOpts().SYCLIsDevice) {
7802  // stdcall and fastcall are ignored with a warning for GCC and MS
7803  // compatibility.
7804  if (CC == CC_X86StdCall || CC == CC_X86FastCall)
7805  return S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_cconv_unsupported)
7806  << FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(CC)
7807  << (int)Sema::CallingConventionIgnoredReason::VariadicFunction;
7808 
7809  attr.setInvalid();
7810  return S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_cconv_varargs)
7811  << FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(CC);
7812  }
7813  }
7814 
7815  // Also diagnose fastcall with regparm.
7816  if (CC == CC_X86FastCall && fn->getHasRegParm()) {
7817  S.Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attributes_are_not_compatible)
7818  << "regparm" << FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(CC_X86FastCall);
7819  attr.setInvalid();
7820  return true;
7821  }
7822 
7823  // Modify the CC from the wrapped function type, wrap it all back, and then
7824  // wrap the whole thing in an AttributedType as written. The modified type
7825  // might have a different CC if we ignored the attribute.
7826  QualType Equivalent;
7827  if (CCOld == CC) {
7828  Equivalent = type;
7829  } else {
7830  auto EI = unwrapped.get()->getExtInfo().withCallingConv(CC);
7831  Equivalent =
7832  unwrapped.wrap(S, S.Context.adjustFunctionType(unwrapped.get(), EI));
7833  }
7834  type = state.getAttributedType(CCAttr, type, Equivalent);
7835  return true;
7836 }
7837 
7838 bool Sema::hasExplicitCallingConv(QualType T) {
7839  const AttributedType *AT;
7840 
7841  // Stop if we'd be stripping off a typedef sugar node to reach the
7842  // AttributedType.
7843  while ((AT = T->getAs<AttributedType>()) &&
7844  AT->getAs<TypedefType>() == T->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
7845  if (AT->isCallingConv())
7846  return true;
7847  T = AT->getModifiedType();
7848  }
7849  return false;
7850 }
7851 
7852 void Sema::adjustMemberFunctionCC(QualType &T, bool IsStatic, bool IsCtorOrDtor,
7853  SourceLocation Loc) {
7854  FunctionTypeUnwrapper Unwrapped(*this, T);
7855  const FunctionType *FT = Unwrapped.get();
7856  bool IsVariadic = (isa<FunctionProtoType>(FT) &&
7857  cast<FunctionProtoType>(FT)->isVariadic());
7858  CallingConv CurCC = FT->getCallConv();
7859  CallingConv ToCC = Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(IsVariadic, !IsStatic);
7860 
7861  if (CurCC == ToCC)
7862  return;
7863 
7864  // MS compiler ignores explicit calling convention attributes on structors. We
7865  // should do the same.
7866  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() && IsCtorOrDtor) {
7867  // Issue a warning on ignored calling convention -- except of __stdcall.
7868  // Again, this is what MS compiler does.
7869  if (CurCC != CC_X86StdCall)
7870  Diag(Loc, diag::warn_cconv_unsupported)
7871  << FunctionType::getNameForCallConv(CurCC)
7872  << (int)Sema::CallingConventionIgnoredReason::ConstructorDestructor;
7873  // Default adjustment.
7874  } else {
7875  // Only adjust types with the default convention. For example, on Windows
7876  // we should adjust a __cdecl type to __thiscall for instance methods, and a
7877  // __thiscall type to __cdecl for static methods.
7878  CallingConv DefaultCC =
7879  Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(IsVariadic, IsStatic);
7880 
7881  if (CurCC != DefaultCC || DefaultCC == ToCC)
7882  return;
7883 
7884  if (hasExplicitCallingConv(T))
7885  return;
7886  }
7887 
7888  FT = Context.adjustFunctionType(FT, FT->getExtInfo().withCallingConv(ToCC));
7889  QualType Wrapped = Unwrapped.wrap(*this, FT);
7890  T = Context.getAdjustedType(T, Wrapped);
7891 }
7892 
7893 /// HandleVectorSizeAttribute - this attribute is only applicable to integral
7894 /// and float scalars, although arrays, pointers, and function return values are
7895 /// allowed in conjunction with this construct. Aggregates with this attribute
7896 /// are invalid, even if they are of the same size as a corresponding scalar.
7897 /// The raw attribute should contain precisely 1 argument, the vector size for
7898 /// the variable, measured in bytes. If curType and rawAttr are well formed,
7899 /// this routine will return a new vector type.
7900 static void HandleVectorSizeAttr(QualType &CurType, const ParsedAttr &Attr,
7901  Sema &S) {
7902  // Check the attribute arguments.
7903  if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
7904  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << Attr
7905  << 1;
7906  Attr.setInvalid();
7907  return;
7908  }
7909 
7910  Expr *SizeExpr = Attr.getArgAsExpr(0);
7911  QualType T = S.BuildVectorType(CurType, SizeExpr, Attr.getLoc());
7912  if (!T.isNull())
7913  CurType = T;
7914  else
7915  Attr.setInvalid();
7916 }
7917 
7918 /// Process the OpenCL-like ext_vector_type attribute when it occurs on
7919 /// a type.
7920 static void HandleExtVectorTypeAttr(QualType &CurType, const ParsedAttr &Attr,
7921  Sema &S) {
7922  // check the attribute arguments.
7923  if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
7924  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << Attr
7925  << 1;
7926  return;
7927  }
7928 
7929  Expr *SizeExpr = Attr.getArgAsExpr(0);
7930  QualType T = S.BuildExtVectorType(CurType, SizeExpr, Attr.getLoc());
7931  if (!T.isNull())
7932  CurType = T;
7933 }
7934 
7935 static bool isPermittedNeonBaseType(QualType &Ty,
7936  VectorType::VectorKind VecKind, Sema &S) {
7937  const BuiltinType *BTy = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>();
7938  if (!BTy)
7939  return false;
7940 
7941  llvm::Triple Triple = S.Context.getTargetInfo().getTriple();
7942 
7943  // Signed poly is mathematically wrong, but has been baked into some ABIs by
7944  // now.
7945  bool IsPolyUnsigned = Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64 ||
7946  Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64_32 ||
7947  Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64_be;
7948  if (VecKind == VectorType::NeonPolyVector) {
7949  if (IsPolyUnsigned) {
7950  // AArch64 polynomial vectors are unsigned.
7951  return BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::UChar ||
7952  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::UShort ||
7953  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::ULong ||
7954  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::ULongLong;
7955  } else {
7956  // AArch32 polynomial vectors are signed.
7957  return BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::SChar ||
7958  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Short ||
7959  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::LongLong;
7960  }
7961  }
7962 
7963  // Non-polynomial vector types: the usual suspects are allowed, as well as
7964  // float64_t on AArch64.
7965  if ((Triple.isArch64Bit() || Triple.getArch() == llvm::Triple::aarch64_32) &&
7966  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Double)
7967  return true;
7968 
7969  return BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::SChar ||
7970  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::UChar ||
7971  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Short ||
7972  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::UShort ||
7973  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Int ||
7974  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::UInt ||
7975  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Long ||
7976  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::ULong ||
7977  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::LongLong ||
7978  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::ULongLong ||
7979  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Float ||
7980  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::Half ||
7981  BTy->getKind() == BuiltinType::BFloat16;
7982 }
7983 
7984 static bool verifyValidIntegerConstantExpr(Sema &S, const ParsedAttr &Attr,
7985  llvm::APSInt &Result) {
7986  const auto *AttrExpr = Attr.getArgAsExpr(0);
7987  if (!AttrExpr->isTypeDependent()) {
7988  if (Optional<llvm::APSInt> Res =
7989  AttrExpr->getIntegerConstantExpr(S.Context)) {
7990  Result = *Res;
7991  return true;
7992  }
7993  }
7994  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_argument_type)
7995  << Attr << AANT_ArgumentIntegerConstant << AttrExpr->getSourceRange();
7996  Attr.setInvalid();
7997  return false;
7998 }
7999 
8000 /// HandleNeonVectorTypeAttr - The "neon_vector_type" and
8001 /// "neon_polyvector_type" attributes are used to create vector types that
8002 /// are mangled according to ARM's ABI. Otherwise, these types are identical
8003 /// to those created with the "vector_size" attribute. Unlike "vector_size"
8004 /// the argument to these Neon attributes is the number of vector elements,
8005 /// not the vector size in bytes. The vector width and element type must
8006 /// match one of the standard Neon vector types.
8007 static void HandleNeonVectorTypeAttr(QualType &CurType, const ParsedAttr &Attr,
8008  Sema &S, VectorType::VectorKind VecKind) {
8009  // Target must have NEON (or MVE, whose vectors are similar enough
8010  // not to need a separate attribute)
8011  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFeature("neon") &&
8012  !S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFeature("mve")) {
8013  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_unsupported)
8014  << Attr << "'neon' or 'mve'";
8015  Attr.setInvalid();
8016  return;
8017  }
8018  // Check the attribute arguments.
8019  if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
8020  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments) << Attr
8021  << 1;
8022  Attr.setInvalid();
8023  return;
8024  }
8025  // The number of elements must be an ICE.
8026  llvm::APSInt numEltsInt(32);
8027  if (!verifyValidIntegerConstantExpr(S, Attr, numEltsInt))
8028  return;
8029 
8030  // Only certain element types are supported for Neon vectors.
8031  if (!isPermittedNeonBaseType(CurType, VecKind, S)) {
8032  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_invalid_vector_type) << CurType;
8033  Attr.setInvalid();
8034  return;
8035  }
8036 
8037  // The total size of the vector must be 64 or 128 bits.
8038  unsigned typeSize = static_cast<unsigned>(S.Context.getTypeSize(CurType));
8039  unsigned numElts = static_cast<unsigned>(numEltsInt.getZExtValue());
8040  unsigned vecSize = typeSize * numElts;
8041  if (vecSize != 64 && vecSize != 128) {
8042  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_bad_neon_vector_size) << CurType;
8043  Attr.setInvalid();
8044  return;
8045  }
8046 
8047  CurType = S.Context.getVectorType(CurType, numElts, VecKind);
8048 }
8049 
8050 /// HandleArmSveVectorBitsTypeAttr - The "arm_sve_vector_bits" attribute is
8051 /// used to create fixed-length versions of sizeless SVE types defined by
8052 /// the ACLE, such as svint32_t and svbool_t.
8053 static void HandleArmSveVectorBitsTypeAttr(QualType &CurType, ParsedAttr &Attr,
8054  Sema &S) {
8055  // Target must have SVE.
8056  if (!S.Context.getTargetInfo().hasFeature("sve")) {
8057  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_unsupported) << Attr << "'sve'";
8058  Attr.setInvalid();
8059  return;
8060  }
8061 
8062  // Attribute is unsupported if '-msve-vector-bits=<bits>' isn't specified, or
8063  // if <bits>+ syntax is used.
8064  if (!S.getLangOpts().VScaleMin ||
8065  S.getLangOpts().VScaleMin != S.getLangOpts().VScaleMax) {
8066  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_arm_feature_sve_bits_unsupported)
8067  << Attr;
8068  Attr.setInvalid();
8069  return;
8070  }
8071 
8072  // Check the attribute arguments.
8073  if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
8074  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
8075  << Attr << 1;
8076  Attr.setInvalid();
8077  return;
8078  }
8079 
8080  // The vector size must be an integer constant expression.
8081  llvm::APSInt SveVectorSizeInBits(32);
8082  if (!verifyValidIntegerConstantExpr(S, Attr, SveVectorSizeInBits))
8083  return;
8084 
8085  unsigned VecSize = static_cast<unsigned>(SveVectorSizeInBits.getZExtValue());
8086 
8087  // The attribute vector size must match -msve-vector-bits.
8088  if (VecSize != S.getLangOpts().VScaleMin * 128) {
8089  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_bad_sve_vector_size)
8090  << VecSize << S.getLangOpts().VScaleMin * 128;
8091  Attr.setInvalid();
8092  return;
8093  }
8094 
8095  // Attribute can only be attached to a single SVE vector or predicate type.
8096  if (!CurType->isVLSTBuiltinType()) {
8097  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_invalid_sve_type)
8098  << Attr << CurType;
8099  Attr.setInvalid();
8100  return;
8101  }
8102 
8103  const auto *BT = CurType->castAs<BuiltinType>();
8104 
8105  QualType EltType = CurType->getSveEltType(S.Context);
8106  unsigned TypeSize = S.Context.getTypeSize(EltType);
8107  VectorType::VectorKind VecKind = VectorType::SveFixedLengthDataVector;
8108  if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::SveBool) {
8109  // Predicates are represented as i8.
8110  VecSize /= S.Context.getCharWidth() * S.Context.getCharWidth();
8111  VecKind = VectorType::SveFixedLengthPredicateVector;
8112  } else
8113  VecSize /= TypeSize;
8114  CurType = S.Context.getVectorType(EltType, VecSize, VecKind);
8115 }
8116 
8117 static void HandleArmMveStrictPolymorphismAttr(TypeProcessingState &State,
8118  QualType &CurType,
8119  ParsedAttr &Attr) {
8120  const VectorType *VT = dyn_cast<VectorType>(CurType);
8121  if (!VT || VT->getVectorKind() != VectorType::NeonVector) {
8122  State.getSema().Diag(Attr.getLoc(),
8123  diag::err_attribute_arm_mve_polymorphism);
8124  Attr.setInvalid();
8125  return;
8126  }
8127 
8128  CurType =
8129  State.getAttributedType(createSimpleAttr<ArmMveStrictPolymorphismAttr>(
8130  State.getSema().Context, Attr),
8131  CurType, CurType);
8132 }
8133 
8134 /// Handle OpenCL Access Qualifier Attribute.
8135 static void HandleOpenCLAccessAttr(QualType &CurType, const ParsedAttr &Attr,
8136  Sema &S) {
8137  // OpenCL v2.0 s6.6 - Access qualifier can be used only for image and pipe type.
8138  if (!(CurType->isImageType() || CurType->isPipeType())) {
8139  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_opencl_invalid_access_qualifier);
8140  Attr.setInvalid();
8141  return;
8142  }
8143 
8144  if (const TypedefType* TypedefTy = CurType->getAs<TypedefType>()) {
8145  QualType BaseTy = TypedefTy->desugar();
8146 
8147  std::string PrevAccessQual;
8148  if (BaseTy->isPipeType()) {
8149  if (TypedefTy->getDecl()->hasAttr<OpenCLAccessAttr>()) {
8150  OpenCLAccessAttr *Attr =
8151  TypedefTy->getDecl()->getAttr<OpenCLAccessAttr>();
8152  PrevAccessQual = Attr->getSpelling();
8153  } else {
8154  PrevAccessQual = "read_only";
8155  }
8156  } else if (const BuiltinType* ImgType = BaseTy->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
8157 
8158  switch (ImgType->getKind()) {
8159  #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
8160  case BuiltinType::Id: \
8161  PrevAccessQual = #Access; \
8162  break;
8163  #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
8164  default:
8165  llvm_unreachable("Unable to find corresponding image type.");
8166  }
8167  } else {
8168  llvm_unreachable("unexpected type");
8169  }
8170  StringRef AttrName = Attr.getAttrName()->getName();
8171  if (PrevAccessQual == AttrName.ltrim("_")) {
8172  // Duplicated qualifiers
8173  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::warn_duplicate_declspec)
8174  << AttrName << Attr.getRange();
8175  } else {
8176  // Contradicting qualifiers
8177  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_opencl_multiple_access_qualifiers);
8178  }
8179 
8180  S.Diag(TypedefTy->getDecl()->getBeginLoc(),
8181  diag::note_opencl_typedef_access_qualifier) << PrevAccessQual;
8182  } else if (CurType->isPipeType()) {
8183  if (Attr.getSemanticSpelling() == OpenCLAccessAttr::Keyword_write_only) {
8184  QualType ElemType = CurType->castAs<PipeType>()->getElementType();
8185  CurType = S.Context.getWritePipeType(ElemType);
8186  }
8187  }
8188 }
8189 
8190 /// HandleMatrixTypeAttr - "matrix_type" attribute, like ext_vector_type
8191 static void HandleMatrixTypeAttr(QualType &CurType, const ParsedAttr &Attr,
8192  Sema &S) {
8193  if (!S.getLangOpts().MatrixTypes) {
8194  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_builtin_matrix_disabled);
8195  return;
8196  }
8197 
8198  if (Attr.getNumArgs() != 2) {
8199  S.Diag(Attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
8200  << Attr << 2;
8201  return;
8202  }
8203 
8204  Expr *RowsExpr = Attr.getArgAsExpr(0);
8205  Expr *ColsExpr = Attr.getArgAsExpr(1);
8206  QualType T = S.BuildMatrixType(CurType, RowsExpr, ColsExpr, Attr.getLoc());
8207  if (!T.isNull())
8208  CurType = T;
8209 }
8210 
8211 static void HandleLifetimeBoundAttr(TypeProcessingState &State,
8212  QualType &CurType,
8213  ParsedAttr &Attr) {
8214  if (State.getDeclarator().isDeclarationOfFunction()) {
8215  CurType = State.getAttributedType(
8216  createSimpleAttr<LifetimeBoundAttr>(State.getSema().Context, Attr),
8217  CurType, CurType);
8218  }
8219 }
8220 
8221 static bool isAddressSpaceKind(const ParsedAttr &attr) {
8222  auto attrKind = attr.getKind();
8223 
8224  return attrKind == ParsedAttr::AT_AddressSpace ||
8225  attrKind == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLPrivateAddressSpace ||
8226  attrKind == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLGlobalAddressSpace ||
8227  attrKind == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLGlobalDeviceAddressSpace ||
8228  attrKind == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLGlobalHostAddressSpace ||
8229  attrKind == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLLocalAddressSpace ||
8230  attrKind == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLConstantAddressSpace ||
8231  attrKind == ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLGenericAddressSpace;
8232 }
8233 
8234 static void processTypeAttrs(TypeProcessingState &state, QualType &type,
8235  TypeAttrLocation TAL,
8236  const ParsedAttributesView &attrs) {
8237 
8238  state.setParsedNoDeref(false);
8239  if (attrs.empty())
8240  return;
8241 
8242  // Scan through and apply attributes to this type where it makes sense. Some
8243  // attributes (such as __address_space__, __vector_size__, etc) apply to the
8244  // type, but others can be present in the type specifiers even though they
8245  // apply to the decl. Here we apply type attributes and ignore the rest.
8246 
8247  // This loop modifies the list pretty frequently, but we still need to make
8248  // sure we visit every element once. Copy the attributes list, and iterate
8249  // over that.
8250  ParsedAttributesView AttrsCopy{attrs};
8251  for (ParsedAttr &attr : AttrsCopy) {
8252 
8253  // Skip attributes that were marked to be invalid.
8254  if (attr.isInvalid())
8255  continue;
8256 
8257  if (attr.isStandardAttributeSyntax()) {
8258  // [[gnu::...]] attributes are treated as declaration attributes, so may
8259  // not appertain to a DeclaratorChunk. If we handle them as type
8260  // attributes, accept them in that position and diagnose the GCC
8261  // incompatibility.
8262  if (attr.isGNUScope()) {
8263  bool IsTypeAttr = attr.isTypeAttr();
8264  if (TAL == TAL_DeclChunk) {
8265  state.getSema().Diag(attr.getLoc(),
8266  IsTypeAttr
8267  ? diag::warn_gcc_ignores_type_attr
8268  : diag::warn_cxx11_gnu_attribute_on_type)
8269  << attr;
8270  if (!IsTypeAttr)
8271  continue;
8272  }
8273  } else if (TAL != TAL_DeclChunk && !isAddressSpaceKind(attr)) {
8274  // Otherwise, only consider type processing for a C++11 attribute if
8275  // it's actually been applied to a type.
8276  // We also allow C++11 address_space and
8277  // OpenCL language address space attributes to pass through.
8278  continue;
8279  }
