8280  }
8281 
8282  // If this is an attribute we can handle, do so now,
8283  // otherwise, add it to the FnAttrs list for rechaining.
8284  switch (attr.getKind()) {
8285  default:
8286  // A [[]] attribute on a declarator chunk must appertain to a type.
8287  if (attr.isStandardAttributeSyntax() && TAL == TAL_DeclChunk &&
8288  (!state.isProcessingLambdaExpr() ||
8289  !attr.supportsNonconformingLambdaSyntax())) {
8290  state.getSema().Diag(attr.getLoc(), diag::err_attribute_not_type_attr)
8291  << attr;
8292  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8293  }
8294  break;
8295 
8296  case ParsedAttr::UnknownAttribute:
8297  if (attr.isStandardAttributeSyntax() && TAL == TAL_DeclChunk)
8298  state.getSema().Diag(attr.getLoc(),
8299  diag::warn_unknown_attribute_ignored)
8300  << attr << attr.getRange();
8301  break;
8302 
8303  case ParsedAttr::IgnoredAttribute:
8304  break;
8305 
8306  case ParsedAttr::AT_BTFTypeTag:
8307  HandleBTFTypeTagAttribute(type, attr, state);
8308  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8309  break;
8310 
8311  case ParsedAttr::AT_MayAlias:
8312  // FIXME: This attribute needs to actually be handled, but if we ignore
8313  // it it breaks large amounts of Linux software.
8314  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8315  break;
8316  case ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLPrivateAddressSpace:
8317  case ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLGlobalAddressSpace:
8318  case ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLGlobalDeviceAddressSpace:
8319  case ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLGlobalHostAddressSpace:
8320  case ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLLocalAddressSpace:
8321  case ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLConstantAddressSpace:
8322  case ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLGenericAddressSpace:
8323  case ParsedAttr::AT_AddressSpace:
8324  HandleAddressSpaceTypeAttribute(type, attr, state);
8325  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8326  break;
8327  OBJC_POINTER_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST:
8328  if (!handleObjCPointerTypeAttr(state, attr, type))
8329  distributeObjCPointerTypeAttr(state, attr, type);
8330  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8331  break;
8332  case ParsedAttr::AT_VectorSize:
8333  HandleVectorSizeAttr(type, attr, state.getSema());
8334  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8335  break;
8336  case ParsedAttr::AT_ExtVectorType:
8337  HandleExtVectorTypeAttr(type, attr, state.getSema());
8338  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8339  break;
8340  case ParsedAttr::AT_NeonVectorType:
8341  HandleNeonVectorTypeAttr(type, attr, state.getSema(),
8342  VectorType::NeonVector);
8343  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8344  break;
8345  case ParsedAttr::AT_NeonPolyVectorType:
8346  HandleNeonVectorTypeAttr(type, attr, state.getSema(),
8347  VectorType::NeonPolyVector);
8348  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8349  break;
8350  case ParsedAttr::AT_ArmSveVectorBits:
8351  HandleArmSveVectorBitsTypeAttr(type, attr, state.getSema());
8352  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8353  break;
8354  case ParsedAttr::AT_ArmMveStrictPolymorphism: {
8355  HandleArmMveStrictPolymorphismAttr(state, type, attr);
8356  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8357  break;
8358  }
8359  case ParsedAttr::AT_OpenCLAccess:
8360  HandleOpenCLAccessAttr(type, attr, state.getSema());
8361  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8362  break;
8363  case ParsedAttr::AT_SYCLFPGAPipe:
8364  HandleSYCLFPGAPipeAttribute(type, attr, state);
8365  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8366  break;
8367  case ParsedAttr::AT_LifetimeBound:
8368  if (TAL == TAL_DeclChunk)
8369  HandleLifetimeBoundAttr(state, type, attr);
8370  break;
8371 
8372  case ParsedAttr::AT_NoDeref: {
8373  ASTContext &Ctx = state.getSema().Context;
8374  type = state.getAttributedType(createSimpleAttr<NoDerefAttr>(Ctx, attr),
8375  type, type);
8376  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8377  state.setParsedNoDeref(true);
8378  break;
8379  }
8380 
8381  case ParsedAttr::AT_MatrixType:
8382  HandleMatrixTypeAttr(type, attr, state.getSema());
8383  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8384  break;
8385 
8386  MS_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST:
8387  if (!handleMSPointerTypeQualifierAttr(state, attr, type))
8388  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8389  break;
8390 
8391 
8392  NULLABILITY_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST:
8393  // Either add nullability here or try to distribute it. We
8394  // don't want to distribute the nullability specifier past any
8395  // dependent type, because that complicates the user model.
8396  if (type->canHaveNullability() || type->isDependentType() ||
8397  type->isArrayType() ||
8398  !distributeNullabilityTypeAttr(state, type, attr)) {
8399  unsigned endIndex;
8400  if (TAL == TAL_DeclChunk)
8401  endIndex = state.getCurrentChunkIndex();
8402  else
8403  endIndex = state.getDeclarator().getNumTypeObjects();
8404  bool allowOnArrayType =
8405  state.getDeclarator().isPrototypeContext() &&
8406  !hasOuterPointerLikeChunk(state.getDeclarator(), endIndex);
8407  if (checkNullabilityTypeSpecifier(
8408  state,
8409  type,
8410  attr,
8411  allowOnArrayType)) {
8412  attr.setInvalid();
8413  }
8414 
8415  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8416  }
8417  break;
8418 
8419  case ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCKindOf:
8420  // '__kindof' must be part of the decl-specifiers.
8421  switch (TAL) {
8422  case TAL_DeclSpec:
8423  break;
8424 
8425  case TAL_DeclChunk:
8426  case TAL_DeclName:
8427  state.getSema().Diag(attr.getLoc(),
8428  diag::err_objc_kindof_wrong_position)
8429  << FixItHint::CreateRemoval(attr.getLoc())
8430  << FixItHint::CreateInsertion(
8431  state.getDeclarator().getDeclSpec().getBeginLoc(),
8432  "__kindof ");
8433  break;
8434  }
8435 
8436  // Apply it regardless.
8437  if (checkObjCKindOfType(state, type, attr))
8438  attr.setInvalid();
8439  break;
8440 
8441  case ParsedAttr::AT_NoThrow:
8442  // Exception Specifications aren't generally supported in C mode throughout
8443  // clang, so revert to attribute-based handling for C.
8444  if (!state.getSema().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
8445  break;
8446  LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
8447  FUNCTION_TYPE_ATTRS_CASELIST:
8448  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8449 
8450  // Never process function type attributes as part of the
8451  // declaration-specifiers.
8452  if (TAL == TAL_DeclSpec)
8453  distributeFunctionTypeAttrFromDeclSpec(state, attr, type);
8454 
8455  // Otherwise, handle the possible delays.
8456  else if (!handleFunctionTypeAttr(state, attr, type))
8457  distributeFunctionTypeAttr(state, attr, type);
8458  break;
8459  case ParsedAttr::AT_AcquireHandle: {
8460  if (!type->isFunctionType())
8461  return;
8462 
8463  if (attr.getNumArgs() != 1) {
8464  state.getSema().Diag(attr.getLoc(),
8465  diag::err_attribute_wrong_number_arguments)
8466  << attr << 1;
8467  attr.setInvalid();
8468  return;
8469  }
8470 
8471  StringRef HandleType;
8472  if (!state.getSema().checkStringLiteralArgumentAttr(attr, 0, HandleType))
8473  return;
8474  type = state.getAttributedType(
8475  AcquireHandleAttr::Create(state.getSema().Context, HandleType, attr),
8476  type, type);
8477  attr.setUsedAsTypeAttr();
8478  break;
8479  }
8480  }
8481 
8482  // Handle attributes that are defined in a macro. We do not want this to be
8483  // applied to ObjC builtin attributes.
8484  if (isa<AttributedType>(type) && attr.hasMacroIdentifier() &&
8485  !type.getQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime() &&
8486  !type.getQualifiers().hasObjCGCAttr() &&
8487  attr.getKind() != ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCGC &&
8488  attr.getKind() != ParsedAttr::AT_ObjCOwnership) {
8489  const IdentifierInfo *MacroII = attr.getMacroIdentifier();
8490  type = state.getSema().Context.getMacroQualifiedType(type, MacroII);
8491  state.setExpansionLocForMacroQualifiedType(
8492  cast<MacroQualifiedType>(type.getTypePtr()),
8493  attr.getMacroExpansionLoc());
8494  }
8495  }
8496 }
8497 
8498 void Sema::completeExprArrayBound(Expr *E) {
8499  if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(E->IgnoreParens())) {
8500  if (VarDecl *Var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
8501  if (isTemplateInstantiation(Var->getTemplateSpecializationKind())) {
8502  auto *Def = Var->getDefinition();
8503  if (!Def) {
8504  SourceLocation PointOfInstantiation = E->getExprLoc();
8505  runWithSufficientStackSpace(PointOfInstantiation, [&] {
8506  InstantiateVariableDefinition(PointOfInstantiation, Var);
8507  });
8508  Def = Var->getDefinition();
8509 
8510  // If we don't already have a point of instantiation, and we managed
8511  // to instantiate a definition, this is the point of instantiation.
8512  // Otherwise, we don't request an end-of-TU instantiation, so this is
8513  // not a point of instantiation.
8514  // FIXME: Is this really the right behavior?
8515  if (Var->getPointOfInstantiation().isInvalid() && Def) {
8516  assert(Var->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
8517  TSK_ImplicitInstantiation &&
8518  "explicit instantiation with no point of instantiation");
8519  Var->setTemplateSpecializationKind(
8520  Var->getTemplateSpecializationKind(), PointOfInstantiation);
8521  }
8522  }
8523 
8524  // Update the type to the definition's type both here and within the
8525  // expression.
8526  if (Def) {
8527  DRE->setDecl(Def);
8528  QualType T = Def->getType();
8529  DRE->setType(T);
8530  // FIXME: Update the type on all intervening expressions.
8531  E->setType(T);
8532  }
8533 
8534  // We still go on to try to complete the type independently, as it
8535  // may also require instantiations or diagnostics if it remains
8536  // incomplete.
8537  }
8538  }
8539  }
8540 }
8541 
8542 QualType Sema::getCompletedType(Expr *E) {
8543  // Incomplete array types may be completed by the initializer attached to
8544  // their definitions. For static data members of class templates and for
8545  // variable templates, we need to instantiate the definition to get this
8546  // initializer and complete the type.
8547  if (E->getType()->isIncompleteArrayType())
8548  completeExprArrayBound(E);
8549 
8550  // FIXME: Are there other cases which require instantiating something other
8551  // than the type to complete the type of an expression?
8552 
8553  return E->getType();
8554 }
8555 
8556 /// Ensure that the type of the given expression is complete.
8557 ///
8558 /// This routine checks whether the expression \p E has a complete type. If the
8559 /// expression refers to an instantiable construct, that instantiation is
8560 /// performed as needed to complete its type. Furthermore
8561 /// Sema::RequireCompleteType is called for the expression's type (or in the
8562 /// case of a reference type, the referred-to type).
8563 ///
8564 /// \param E The expression whose type is required to be complete.
8565 /// \param Kind Selects which completeness rules should be applied.
8566 /// \param Diagnoser The object that will emit a diagnostic if the type is
8567 /// incomplete.
8568 ///
8569 /// \returns \c true if the type of \p E is incomplete and diagnosed, \c false
8570 /// otherwise.
8571 bool Sema::RequireCompleteExprType(Expr *E, CompleteTypeKind Kind,
8572  TypeDiagnoser &Diagnoser) {
8573  return RequireCompleteType(E->getExprLoc(), getCompletedType(E), Kind,
8574  Diagnoser);
8575 }
8576 
8577 bool Sema::RequireCompleteExprType(Expr *E, unsigned DiagID) {
8578  BoundTypeDiagnoser<> Diagnoser(DiagID);
8579  return RequireCompleteExprType(E, CompleteTypeKind::Default, Diagnoser);
8580 }
8581 
8582 /// Ensure that the type T is a complete type.
8583 ///
8584 /// This routine checks whether the type @p T is complete in any
8585 /// context where a complete type is required. If @p T is a complete
8586 /// type, returns false. If @p T is a class template specialization,
8587 /// this routine then attempts to perform class template
8588 /// instantiation. If instantiation fails, or if @p T is incomplete
8589 /// and cannot be completed, issues the diagnostic @p diag (giving it
8590 /// the type @p T) and returns true.
8591 ///
8592 /// @param Loc The location in the source that the incomplete type
8593 /// diagnostic should refer to.
8594 ///
8595 /// @param T The type that this routine is examining for completeness.
8596 ///
8597 /// @param Kind Selects which completeness rules should be applied.
8598 ///
8599 /// @returns @c true if @p T is incomplete and a diagnostic was emitted,
8600 /// @c false otherwise.
8601 bool Sema::RequireCompleteType(SourceLocation Loc, QualType T,
8602  CompleteTypeKind Kind,
8603  TypeDiagnoser &Diagnoser) {
8604  if (RequireCompleteTypeImpl(Loc, T, Kind, &Diagnoser))
8605  return true;
8606  if (const TagType *Tag = T->getAs<TagType>()) {
8607  if (!Tag->getDecl()->isCompleteDefinitionRequired()) {
8608  Tag->getDecl()->setCompleteDefinitionRequired();
8609  Consumer.HandleTagDeclRequiredDefinition(Tag->getDecl());
8610  }
8611  }
8612  return false;
8613 }
8614 
8615 bool Sema::hasStructuralCompatLayout(Decl *D, Decl *Suggested) {
8616  llvm::DenseSet<std::pair<Decl *, Decl *>> NonEquivalentDecls;
8617  if (!Suggested)
8618  return false;
8619 
8620  // FIXME: Add a specific mode for C11 6.2.7/1 in StructuralEquivalenceContext
8621  // and isolate from other C++ specific checks.
8622  StructuralEquivalenceContext Ctx(
8623  D->getASTContext(), Suggested->getASTContext(), NonEquivalentDecls,
8624  StructuralEquivalenceKind::Default,
8625  false /*StrictTypeSpelling*/, true /*Complain*/,
8626  true /*ErrorOnTagTypeMismatch*/);
8627  return Ctx.IsEquivalent(D, Suggested);
8628 }
8629 
8630 /// Determine whether there is any declaration of \p D that was ever a
8631 /// definition (perhaps before module merging) and is currently visible.
8632 /// \param D The definition of the entity.
8633 /// \param Suggested Filled in with the declaration that should be made visible
8634 /// in order to provide a definition of this entity.
8635 /// \param OnlyNeedComplete If \c true, we only need the type to be complete,
8636 /// not defined. This only matters for enums with a fixed underlying
8637 /// type, since in all other cases, a type is complete if and only if it
8638 /// is defined.
8639 bool Sema::hasVisibleDefinition(NamedDecl *D, NamedDecl **Suggested,
8640  bool OnlyNeedComplete) {
8641  // Easy case: if we don't have modules, all declarations are visible.
8642  if (!getLangOpts().Modules && !getLangOpts().ModulesLocalVisibility)
8643  return true;
8644 
8645  // If this definition was instantiated from a template, map back to the
8646  // pattern from which it was instantiated.
8647  if (isa<TagDecl>(D) && cast<TagDecl>(D)->isBeingDefined()) {
8648  // We're in the middle of defining it; this definition should be treated
8649  // as visible.
8650  return true;
8651  } else if (auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
8652  if (auto *Pattern = RD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
8653  RD = Pattern;
8654  D = RD->getDefinition();
8655  } else if (auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
8656  if (auto *Pattern = ED->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
8657  ED = Pattern;
8658  if (OnlyNeedComplete && (ED->isFixed() || getLangOpts().MSVCCompat)) {
8659  // If the enum has a fixed underlying type, it may have been forward
8660  // declared. In -fms-compatibility, `enum Foo;` will also forward declare
8661  // the enum and assign it the underlying type of `int`. Since we're only
8662  // looking for a complete type (not a definition), any visible declaration
8663  // of it will do.
8664  *Suggested = nullptr;
8665  for (auto *Redecl : ED->redecls()) {
8666  if (isVisible(Redecl))
8667  return true;
8668  if (Redecl->isThisDeclarationADefinition() ||
8669  (Redecl->isCanonicalDecl() && !*Suggested))
8670  *Suggested = Redecl;
8671  }
8672  return false;
8673  }
8674  D = ED->getDefinition();
8675  } else if (auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
8676  if (auto *Pattern = FD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
8677  FD = Pattern;
8678  D = FD->getDefinition();
8679  } else if (auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
8680  if (auto *Pattern = VD->getTemplateInstantiationPattern())
8681  VD = Pattern;
8682  D = VD->getDefinition();
8683  }
8684  assert(D && "missing definition for pattern of instantiated definition");
8685 
8686  *Suggested = D;
8687 
8688  auto DefinitionIsVisible = [&] {
8689  // The (primary) definition might be in a visible module.
8690  if (isVisible(D))
8691  return true;
8692 
8693  // A visible module might have a merged definition instead.
8694  if (D->isModulePrivate() ? hasMergedDefinitionInCurrentModule(D)
8695  : hasVisibleMergedDefinition(D)) {
8696  if (CodeSynthesisContexts.empty() &&
8697  !getLangOpts().ModulesLocalVisibility) {
8698  // Cache the fact that this definition is implicitly visible because
8699  // there is a visible merged definition.
8700  D->setVisibleDespiteOwningModule();
8701  }
8702  return true;
8703  }
8704 
8705  return false;
8706  };
8707 
8708  if (DefinitionIsVisible())
8709  return true;
8710 
8711  // The external source may have additional definitions of this entity that are
8712  // visible, so complete the redeclaration chain now and ask again.
8713  if (auto *Source = Context.getExternalSource()) {
8714  Source->CompleteRedeclChain(D);
8715  return DefinitionIsVisible();
8716  }
8717 
8718  return false;
8719 }
8720 
8721 /// Locks in the inheritance model for the given class and all of its bases.
8722 static void assignInheritanceModel(Sema &S, CXXRecordDecl *RD) {
8723  RD = RD->getMostRecentNonInjectedDecl();
8724  if (!RD->hasAttr<MSInheritanceAttr>()) {
8725  MSInheritanceModel IM;
8726  bool BestCase = false;
8727  switch (S.MSPointerToMemberRepresentationMethod) {
8728  case LangOptions::PPTMK_BestCase:
8729  BestCase = true;
8730  IM = RD->calculateInheritanceModel();
8731  break;
8732  case LangOptions::PPTMK_FullGeneralitySingleInheritance:
8733  IM = MSInheritanceModel::Single;
8734  break;
8735  case LangOptions::PPTMK_FullGeneralityMultipleInheritance:
8736  IM = MSInheritanceModel::Multiple;
8737  break;
8738  case LangOptions::PPTMK_FullGeneralityVirtualInheritance:
8739  IM = MSInheritanceModel::Unspecified;
8740  break;
8741  }
8742 
8743  SourceRange Loc = S.ImplicitMSInheritanceAttrLoc.isValid()
8744  ? S.ImplicitMSInheritanceAttrLoc
8745  : RD->getSourceRange();
8746  RD->addAttr(MSInheritanceAttr::CreateImplicit(
8747  S.getASTContext(), BestCase, Loc, AttributeCommonInfo::AS_Microsoft,
8748  MSInheritanceAttr::Spelling(IM)));
8749  S.Consumer.AssignInheritanceModel(RD);
8750  }
8751 }
8752 
8753 /// The implementation of RequireCompleteType
8754 bool Sema::RequireCompleteTypeImpl(SourceLocation Loc, QualType T,
8755  CompleteTypeKind Kind,
8756  TypeDiagnoser *Diagnoser) {
8757  // FIXME: Add this assertion to make sure we always get instantiation points.
8758  // assert(!Loc.isInvalid() && "Invalid location in RequireCompleteType");
8759  // FIXME: Add this assertion to help us flush out problems with
8760  // checking for dependent types and type-dependent expressions.
8761  //
8762  // assert(!T->isDependentType() &&
8763  // "Can't ask whether a dependent type is complete");
8764 
8765  if (const MemberPointerType *MPTy = T->getAs<MemberPointerType>()) {
8766  if (!MPTy->getClass()->isDependentType()) {
8767  if (getLangOpts().CompleteMemberPointers &&
8768  !MPTy->getClass()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()->isBeingDefined() &&
8769  RequireCompleteType(Loc, QualType(MPTy->getClass(), 0), Kind,
8770  diag::err_memptr_incomplete))
8771  return true;
8772 
8773  // We lock in the inheritance model once somebody has asked us to ensure
8774  // that a pointer-to-member type is complete.
8775  if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
8776  (void)isCompleteType(Loc, QualType(MPTy->getClass(), 0));
8777  assignInheritanceModel(*this, MPTy->getMostRecentCXXRecordDecl());
8778  }
8779  }
8780  }
8781 
8782  NamedDecl *Def = nullptr;
8783  bool AcceptSizeless = (Kind == CompleteTypeKind::AcceptSizeless);
8784  bool Incomplete = (T->isIncompleteType(&Def) ||
8785  (!AcceptSizeless && T->isSizelessBuiltinType()));
8786 
8787  // Check that any necessary explicit specializations are visible. For an
8788  // enum, we just need the declaration, so don't check this.
8789  if (Def && !isa<EnumDecl>(Def))
8790  checkSpecializationVisibility(Loc, Def);
8791 
8792  // If we have a complete type, we're done.
8793  if (!Incomplete) {
8794  // If we know about the definition but it is not visible, complain.
8795  NamedDecl *SuggestedDef = nullptr;
8796  if (Def &&
8797  !hasVisibleDefinition(Def, &SuggestedDef, /*OnlyNeedComplete*/true)) {
8798  // If the user is going to see an error here, recover by making the
8799  // definition visible.
8800  bool TreatAsComplete = Diagnoser && !isSFINAEContext();
8801  if (Diagnoser && SuggestedDef)
8802  diagnoseMissingImport(Loc, SuggestedDef, MissingImportKind::Definition,
8803  /*Recover*/TreatAsComplete);
8804  return !TreatAsComplete;
8805  } else if (Def && !TemplateInstCallbacks.empty()) {
8806  CodeSynthesisContext TempInst;
8807  TempInst.Kind = CodeSynthesisContext::Memoization;
8808  TempInst.Template = Def;
8809  TempInst.Entity = Def;
8810  TempInst.PointOfInstantiation = Loc;
8811  atTemplateBegin(TemplateInstCallbacks, *this, TempInst);
8812  atTemplateEnd(TemplateInstCallbacks, *this, TempInst);
8813  }
8814 
8815  return false;
8816  }
8817 
8818  TagDecl *Tag = dyn_cast_or_null<TagDecl>(Def);
8819  ObjCInterfaceDecl *IFace = dyn_cast_or_null<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(Def);
8820 
8821  // Give the external source a chance to provide a definition of the type.
8822  // This is kept separate from completing the redeclaration chain so that
8823  // external sources such as LLDB can avoid synthesizing a type definition
8824  // unless it's actually needed.
8825  if (Tag || IFace) {
8826  // Avoid diagnosing invalid decls as incomplete.
8827  if (Def->isInvalidDecl())
8828  return true;
8829 
8830  // Give the external AST source a chance to complete the type.
8831  if (auto *Source = Context.getExternalSource()) {
8832  if (Tag && Tag->hasExternalLexicalStorage())
8833  Source->CompleteType(Tag);
8834  if (IFace && IFace->hasExternalLexicalStorage())
8835  Source->CompleteType(IFace);
8836  // If the external source completed the type, go through the motions
8837  // again to ensure we're allowed to use the completed type.
8838  if (!T->isIncompleteType())
8839  return RequireCompleteTypeImpl(Loc, T, Kind, Diagnoser);
8840  }
8841  }
8842 
8843  // If we have a class template specialization or a class member of a
8844  // class template specialization, or an array with known size of such,
8845  // try to instantiate it.
8846  if (auto *RD = dyn_cast_or_null<CXXRecordDecl>(Tag)) {
8847  bool Instantiated = false;
8848  bool Diagnosed = false;
8849  if (RD->isDependentContext()) {
8850  // Don't try to instantiate a dependent class (eg, a member template of
8851  // an instantiated class template specialization).
8852  // FIXME: Can this ever happen?
8853  } else if (auto *ClassTemplateSpec =
8854  dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD)) {
8855  if (ClassTemplateSpec->getSpecializationKind() == TSK_Undeclared) {
8856  runWithSufficientStackSpace(Loc, [&] {
8857  Diagnosed = InstantiateClassTemplateSpecialization(
8858  Loc, ClassTemplateSpec, TSK_ImplicitInstantiation,
8859  /*Complain=*/Diagnoser);
8860  });
8861  Instantiated = true;
8862  }
8863  } else {
8864  CXXRecordDecl *Pattern = RD->getInstantiatedFromMemberClass();
8865  if (!RD->isBeingDefined() && Pattern) {
8866  MemberSpecializationInfo *MSI = RD->getMemberSpecializationInfo();
8867  assert(MSI && "Missing member specialization information?");
8868  // This record was instantiated from a class within a template.
8869  if (MSI->getTemplateSpecializationKind() !=
8870  TSK_ExplicitSpecialization) {
8871  runWithSufficientStackSpace(Loc, [&] {
8872  Diagnosed = InstantiateClass(Loc, RD, Pattern,
8873  getTemplateInstantiationArgs(RD),
8874  TSK_ImplicitInstantiation,
8875  /*Complain=*/Diagnoser);
8876  });
8877  Instantiated = true;
8878  }
8879  }
8880  }
8881 
8882  if (Instantiated) {
8883  // Instantiate* might have already complained that the template is not
8884  // defined, if we asked it to.
8885  if (Diagnoser && Diagnosed)
8886  return true;
8887  // If we instantiated a definition, check that it's usable, even if
8888  // instantiation produced an error, so that repeated calls to this
8889  // function give consistent answers.
8890  if (!T->isIncompleteType())
8891  return RequireCompleteTypeImpl(Loc, T, Kind, Diagnoser);
8892  }
8893  }
8894 
8895  // FIXME: If we didn't instantiate a definition because of an explicit
8896  // specialization declaration, check that it's visible.
8897 
8898  if (!Diagnoser)
8899  return true;
8900 
8901  Diagnoser->diagnose(*this, Loc, T);
8902 
8903  // If the type was a forward declaration of a class/struct/union
8904  // type, produce a note.
8905  if (Tag && !Tag->isInvalidDecl() && !Tag->getLocation().isInvalid())
8906  Diag(Tag->getLocation(),
8907  Tag->isBeingDefined() ? diag::note_type_being_defined
8908  : diag::note_forward_declaration)
8909  << Context.getTagDeclType(Tag);
8910 
8911  // If the Objective-C class was a forward declaration, produce a note.
8912  if (IFace && !IFace->isInvalidDecl() && !IFace->getLocation().isInvalid())
8913  Diag(IFace->getLocation(), diag::note_forward_class);
8914 
8915  // If we have external information that we can use to suggest a fix,
8916  // produce a note.
8917  if (ExternalSource)
8918  ExternalSource->MaybeDiagnoseMissingCompleteType(Loc, T);
8919 
8920  return true;
8921 }
8922 
8923 bool Sema::RequireCompleteType(SourceLocation Loc, QualType T,
8924  CompleteTypeKind Kind, unsigned DiagID) {
8925  BoundTypeDiagnoser<> Diagnoser(DiagID);
8926  return RequireCompleteType(Loc, T, Kind, Diagnoser);
8927 }
8928 
8929 /// Get diagnostic %select index for tag kind for
8930 /// literal type diagnostic message.
8931 /// WARNING: Indexes apply to particular diagnostics only!
8932 ///
8933 /// \returns diagnostic %select index.
8934 static unsigned getLiteralDiagFromTagKind(TagTypeKind Tag) {
8935  switch (Tag) {
8936  case TTK_Struct: return 0;
8937  case TTK_Interface: return 1;
8938  case TTK_Class: return 2;
8939  default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid tag kind for literal type diagnostic!");
8940  }
8941 }
8942 
8943 /// Ensure that the type T is a literal type.
8944 ///
8945 /// This routine checks whether the type @p T is a literal type. If @p T is an
8946 /// incomplete type, an attempt is made to complete it. If @p T is a literal
8947 /// type, or @p AllowIncompleteType is true and @p T is an incomplete type,
8948 /// returns false. Otherwise, this routine issues the diagnostic @p PD (giving
8949 /// it the type @p T), along with notes explaining why the type is not a
8950 /// literal type, and returns true.
8951 ///
8952 /// @param Loc The location in the source that the non-literal type
8953 /// diagnostic should refer to.
8954 ///
8955 /// @param T The type that this routine is examining for literalness.
8956 ///
8957 /// @param Diagnoser Emits a diagnostic if T is not a literal type.
8958 ///
8959 /// @returns @c true if @p T is not a literal type and a diagnostic was emitted,
8960 /// @c false otherwise.
8961 bool Sema::RequireLiteralType(SourceLocation Loc, QualType T,
8962  TypeDiagnoser &Diagnoser) {
8963  assert(!T->isDependentType() && "type should not be dependent");
8964 
8965  QualType ElemType = Context.getBaseElementType(T);
8966  if ((isCompleteType(Loc, ElemType) || ElemType->isVoidType()) &&
8967  T->isLiteralType(Context))
8968  return false;
8969 
8970  Diagnoser.diagnose(*this, Loc, T);
8971 
8972  if (T->isVariableArrayType())
8973  return true;
8974 
8975  const RecordType *RT = ElemType->getAs<RecordType>();
8976  if (!RT)
8977  return true;
8978 
8979  const CXXRecordDecl *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RT->getDecl());
8980 
8981  // A partially-defined class type can't be a literal type, because a literal
8982  // class type must have a trivial destructor (which can't be checked until
8983  // the class definition is complete).
8984  if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, ElemType, diag::note_non_literal_incomplete, T))
8985  return true;
8986 
8987  // [expr.prim.lambda]p3:
8988  // This class type is [not] a literal type.
8989  if (RD->isLambda() && !getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17) {
8990  Diag(RD->getLocation(), diag::note_non_literal_lambda);
8991  return true;
8992  }
8993 
8994  // If the class has virtual base classes, then it's not an aggregate, and
8995  // cannot have any constexpr constructors or a trivial default constructor,
8996  // so is non-literal. This is better to diagnose than the resulting absence
8997  // of constexpr constructors.
8998  if (RD->getNumVBases()) {
8999  Diag(RD->getLocation(), diag::note_non_literal_virtual_base)
9000  << getLiteralDiagFromTagKind(RD->getTagKind()) << RD->getNumVBases();
9001  for (const auto &I : RD->vbases())
9002  Diag(I.getBeginLoc(), diag::note_constexpr_virtual_base_here)
9003  << I.getSourceRange();
9004  } else if (!RD->isAggregate() && !RD->hasConstexprNonCopyMoveConstructor() &&
9005  !RD->hasTrivialDefaultConstructor()) {
9006  Diag(RD->getLocation(), diag::note_non_literal_no_constexpr_ctors) << RD;
9007  } else if (RD->hasNonLiteralTypeFieldsOrBases()) {
9008  for (const auto &I : RD->bases()) {
9009  if (!I.getType()->isLiteralType(Context)) {
9010  Diag(I.getBeginLoc(), diag::note_non_literal_base_class)
9011  << RD << I.getType() << I.getSourceRange();
9012  return true;
9013  }
9014  }
9015  for (const auto *I : RD->fields()) {
9016  if (!I->getType()->isLiteralType(Context) ||
9017  I->getType().isVolatileQualified()) {
9018  Diag(I->getLocation(), diag::note_non_literal_field)
9019  << RD << I << I->getType()
9020  << I->getType().isVolatileQualified();
9021  return true;
9022  }
9023  }
9024  } else if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20 ? !RD->hasConstexprDestructor()
9025  : !RD->hasTrivialDestructor()) {
9026  // All fields and bases are of literal types, so have trivial or constexpr
9027  // destructors. If this class's destructor is non-trivial / non-constexpr,
9028  // it must be user-declared.
9029  CXXDestructorDecl *Dtor = RD->getDestructor();
9030  assert(Dtor && "class has literal fields and bases but no dtor?");
9031  if (!Dtor)
9032  return true;
9033 
9034  if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus20) {
9035  Diag(Dtor->getLocation(), diag::note_non_literal_non_constexpr_dtor)
9036  << RD;
9037  } else {
9038  Diag(Dtor->getLocation(), Dtor->isUserProvided()
9039  ? diag::note_non_literal_user_provided_dtor
9040  : diag::note_non_literal_nontrivial_dtor)
9041  << RD;
9042  if (!Dtor->isUserProvided())
9043  SpecialMemberIsTrivial(Dtor, CXXDestructor, TAH_IgnoreTrivialABI,
9044  /*Diagnose*/ true);
9045  }
9046  }
9047 
9048  return true;
9049 }
9050 
9051 bool Sema::RequireLiteralType(SourceLocation Loc, QualType T, unsigned DiagID) {
9052  BoundTypeDiagnoser<> Diagnoser(DiagID);
9053  return RequireLiteralType(Loc, T, Diagnoser);
9054 }

9056 /// Retrieve a version of the type 'T' that is elaborated by Keyword, qualified
9057 /// by the nested-name-specifier contained in SS, and that is (re)declared by
9058 /// OwnedTagDecl, which is nullptr if this is not a (re)declaration.
9059 QualType Sema::getElaboratedType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
9060  const CXXScopeSpec &SS, QualType T,
9061  TagDecl *OwnedTagDecl) {
9062  if (T.isNull())
9063  return T;
9064  NestedNameSpecifier *NNS;
9065  if (SS.isValid())
9066  NNS = SS.getScopeRep();
9067  else {
9068  if (Keyword == ETK_None)
9069  return T;
9070  NNS = nullptr;
9071  }
9072  return Context.getElaboratedType(Keyword, NNS, T, OwnedTagDecl);
9073 }

9075 QualType Sema::BuildTypeofExprType(Expr *E) {
9076  assert(!E->hasPlaceholderType() && "unexpected placeholder");
9077 
9078  if (!getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && E->refersToBitField())
9079  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::err_sizeof_alignof_typeof_bitfield) << 2;
9080 
9081  if (!E->isTypeDependent()) {
9082  QualType T = E->getType();
9083  if (const TagType *TT = T->getAs<TagType>())
9084  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(TT->getDecl(), E->getExprLoc());
9085  }
9086  return Context.getTypeOfExprType(E);
9087 }
9088 
9089 /// getDecltypeForExpr - Given an expr, will return the decltype for
9090 /// that expression, according to the rules in C++11
9091 /// [dcl.type.simple]p4 and C++11 [expr.lambda.prim]p18.
9092 QualType Sema::getDecltypeForExpr(Expr *E) {
9093  if (E->isTypeDependent())
9094  return Context.DependentTy;
9095 
9096  Expr *IDExpr = E;
9097  if (auto *ImplCastExpr = dyn_cast<ImplicitCastExpr>(E))
9098  IDExpr = ImplCastExpr->getSubExpr();
9099 
9100  // C++11 [dcl.type.simple]p4:
9101  // The type denoted by decltype(e) is defined as follows:
9102 
9103  // C++20:
9104  // - if E is an unparenthesized id-expression naming a non-type
9105  // template-parameter (13.2), decltype(E) is the type of the
9106  // template-parameter after performing any necessary type deduction
9107  // Note that this does not pick up the implicit 'const' for a template
9108  // parameter object. This rule makes no difference before C++20 so we apply
9109  // it unconditionally.
9110  if (const auto *SNTTPE = dyn_cast<SubstNonTypeTemplateParmExpr>(IDExpr))
9111  return SNTTPE->getParameterType(Context);
9112 
9113  // - if e is an unparenthesized id-expression or an unparenthesized class
9114  // member access (5.2.5), decltype(e) is the type of the entity named
9115  // by e. If there is no such entity, or if e names a set of overloaded
9116  // functions, the program is ill-formed;
9117  //
9118  // We apply the same rules for Objective-C ivar and property references.
9119  if (const auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(IDExpr)) {
9120  const ValueDecl *VD = DRE->getDecl();
9121  QualType T = VD->getType();
9122  return isa<TemplateParamObjectDecl>(VD) ? T.getUnqualifiedType() : T;
9123  }
9124  if (const auto *ME = dyn_cast<MemberExpr>(IDExpr)) {
9125  if (const auto *VD = ME->getMemberDecl())
9126  if (isa<FieldDecl>(VD) || isa<VarDecl>(VD))
9127  return VD->getType();
9128  } else if (const auto *IR = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarRefExpr>(IDExpr)) {
9129  return IR->getDecl()->getType();
9130  } else if (const auto *PR = dyn_cast<ObjCPropertyRefExpr>(IDExpr)) {
9131  if (PR->isExplicitProperty())
9132  return PR->getExplicitProperty()->getType();
9133  } else if (const auto *PE = dyn_cast<PredefinedExpr>(IDExpr)) {
9134  return PE->getType();
9135  }
9136 
9137  // C++11 [expr.lambda.prim]p18:
9138  // Every occurrence of decltype((x)) where x is a possibly
9139  // parenthesized id-expression that names an entity of automatic
9140  // storage duration is treated as if x were transformed into an
9141  // access to a corresponding data member of the closure type that
9142  // would have been declared if x were an odr-use of the denoted
9143  // entity.
9144  if (getCurLambda() && isa<ParenExpr>(IDExpr)) {
9145  if (auto *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(IDExpr->IgnoreParens())) {
9146  if (auto *Var = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(DRE->getDecl())) {
9147  QualType T = getCapturedDeclRefType(Var, DRE->getLocation());
9148  if (!T.isNull())
9149  return Context.getLValueReferenceType(T);
9150  }
9151  }
9152  }
9153 
9154  return Context.getReferenceQualifiedType(E);
9155 }
9156 
9157 QualType Sema::BuildDecltypeType(Expr *E, bool AsUnevaluated) {
9158  assert(!E->hasPlaceholderType() && "unexpected placeholder");
9159 
9160  if (AsUnevaluated && CodeSynthesisContexts.empty() &&
9161  !E->isInstantiationDependent() && E->HasSideEffects(Context, false)) {
9162  // The expression operand for decltype is in an unevaluated expression
9163  // context, so side effects could result in unintended consequences.
9164  // Exclude instantiation-dependent expressions, because 'decltype' is often
9165  // used to build SFINAE gadgets.
9166  Diag(E->getExprLoc(), diag::warn_side_effects_unevaluated_context);
9167  }
9168  return Context.getDecltypeType(E, getDecltypeForExpr(E));
9169 }
9170 
9171 QualType Sema::BuildUnaryTransformType(QualType BaseType,
9172  UnaryTransformType::UTTKind UKind,
9173  SourceLocation Loc) {
9174  switch (UKind) {
9175  case UnaryTransformType::EnumUnderlyingType:
9176  if (!BaseType->isDependentType() && !BaseType->isEnumeralType()) {
9177  Diag(Loc, diag::err_only_enums_have_underlying_types);
9178  return QualType();
9179  } else {
9180  QualType Underlying = BaseType;
9181  if (!BaseType->isDependentType()) {
9182  // The enum could be incomplete if we're parsing its definition or
9183  // recovering from an error.
9184  NamedDecl *FwdDecl = nullptr;
9185  if (BaseType->isIncompleteType(&FwdDecl)) {
9186  Diag(Loc, diag::err_underlying_type_of_incomplete_enum) << BaseType;
9187  Diag(FwdDecl->getLocation(), diag::note_forward_declaration) << FwdDecl;
9188  return QualType();
9189  }
9190 
9191  EnumDecl *ED = BaseType->castAs<EnumType>()->getDecl();
9192  assert(ED && "EnumType has no EnumDecl");
9193 
9194  DiagnoseUseOfDecl(ED, Loc);
9195 
9196  Underlying = ED->getIntegerType();
9197  assert(!Underlying.isNull());
9198  }
9199  return Context.getUnaryTransformType(BaseType, Underlying,
9200  UnaryTransformType::EnumUnderlyingType);
9201  }
9202  }
9203  llvm_unreachable("unknown unary transform type");
9204 }
9205 
9206 QualType Sema::BuildAtomicType(QualType T, SourceLocation Loc) {
9207  if (!isDependentOrGNUAutoType(T)) {
9208  // FIXME: It isn't entirely clear whether incomplete atomic types
9209  // are allowed or not; for simplicity, ban them for the moment.
9210  if (RequireCompleteType(Loc, T, diag::err_atomic_specifier_bad_type, 0))
9211  return QualType();
9212 
9213  int DisallowedKind = -1;
9214  if (T->isArrayType())
9215  DisallowedKind = 1;
9216  else if (T->isFunctionType())
9217  DisallowedKind = 2;
9218  else if (T->isReferenceType())
9219  DisallowedKind = 3;
9220  else if (T->isAtomicType())
9221  DisallowedKind = 4;
9222  else if (T.hasQualifiers())
9223  DisallowedKind = 5;
9224  else if (T->isSizelessType())
9225  DisallowedKind = 6;
9226  else if (!T.isTriviallyCopyableType(Context))
9227  // Some other non-trivially-copyable type (probably a C++ class)
9228  DisallowedKind = 7;
9229  else if (T->isBitIntType())
9230  DisallowedKind = 8;
9231 
9232  if (DisallowedKind != -1) {
9233  Diag(Loc, diag::err_atomic_specifier_bad_type) << DisallowedKind << T;
9234  return QualType();
9235  }
9236 
9237  // FIXME: Do we need any handling for ARC here?
9238  }
9239 
9240  // Build the pointer type.
9241  return Context.getAtomicType(T);
9242 }
